86  std::string ASTImportError::toString() const {
87  // FIXME: Improve error texts.
88  switch (Error) {
89  case NameConflict:
90  return "NameConflict";
91  case UnsupportedConstruct:
92  return "UnsupportedConstruct";
93  case Unknown:
94  return "Unknown error";
95  }
96  llvm_unreachable("Invalid error code.");
97  return "Invalid error code.";
98  }

108  template <class T>
109  SmallVector<Decl *, 2>
110  getCanonicalForwardRedeclChain(Redeclarable<T>* D) {
111  SmallVector<Decl *, 2> Redecls;
112  for (auto *R : D->getFirstDecl()->redecls()) {
113  if (R != D->getFirstDecl())
114  Redecls.push_back(R);
115  }
116  Redecls.push_back(D->getFirstDecl());
117  std::reverse(Redecls.begin(), Redecls.end());
118  return Redecls;
119  }
120 
121  SmallVector<Decl*, 2> getCanonicalForwardRedeclChain(Decl* D) {
122  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
123  return getCanonicalForwardRedeclChain<FunctionDecl>(FD);
124  if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
125  return getCanonicalForwardRedeclChain<VarDecl>(VD);
126  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D))
127  return getCanonicalForwardRedeclChain<TagDecl>(TD);
128  llvm_unreachable("Bad declaration kind");
129  }

131  void updateFlags(const Decl *From, Decl *To) {
132  // Check if some flags or attrs are new in 'From' and copy into 'To'.
133  // FIXME: Other flags or attrs?
134  if (From->isUsed(false) && !To->isUsed(false))
135  To->setIsUsed();
136  }

138  /// How to handle import errors that occur when import of a child declaration
139  /// of a DeclContext fails.
140  class ChildErrorHandlingStrategy {
141  /// This context is imported (in the 'from' domain).
142  /// It is nullptr if a non-DeclContext is imported.
143  const DeclContext *const FromDC;
144  /// Ignore import errors of the children.
145  /// If true, the context can be imported successfully if a child
146  /// of it failed to import. Otherwise the import errors of the child nodes
147  /// are accumulated (joined) into the import error object of the parent.
148  /// (Import of a parent can fail in other ways.)
149  bool const IgnoreChildErrors;
150 
151  public:
152  ChildErrorHandlingStrategy(const DeclContext *FromDC)
153  : FromDC(FromDC), IgnoreChildErrors(!isa<TagDecl>(FromDC)) {}
154  ChildErrorHandlingStrategy(const Decl *FromD)
155  : FromDC(dyn_cast<DeclContext>(FromD)),
156  IgnoreChildErrors(!isa<TagDecl>(FromD)) {}
157 
158  /// Process the import result of a child (of the current declaration).
159  /// \param ResultErr The import error that can be used as result of
160  /// importing the parent. This may be changed by the function.
161  /// \param ChildErr Result of importing a child. Can be success or error.
162  void handleChildImportResult(Error &ResultErr, Error &&ChildErr) {
163  if (ChildErr && !IgnoreChildErrors)
164  ResultErr = joinErrors(std::move(ResultErr), std::move(ChildErr));
165  else
166  consumeError(std::move(ChildErr));
167  }
168 
169  /// Determine if import failure of a child does not cause import failure of
170  /// its parent.
171  bool ignoreChildErrorOnParent(Decl *FromChildD) const {
172  if (!IgnoreChildErrors || !FromDC)
173  return false;
174  return FromDC->containsDecl(FromChildD);
175  }
176  };

183  // Use this instead of Importer.importInto .
184  template <typename ImportT>
185  [[nodiscard]] Error importInto(ImportT &To, const ImportT &From) {
186  return Importer.importInto(To, From);
187  }
188 
189  // Use this to import pointers of specific type.
190  template <typename ImportT>
191  [[nodiscard]] Error importInto(ImportT *&To, ImportT *From) {
192  auto ToOrErr = Importer.Import(From);
193  if (ToOrErr)
194  To = cast_or_null<ImportT>(*ToOrErr);
195  return ToOrErr.takeError();
196  }
197 
198  // Call the import function of ASTImporter for a baseclass of type `T` and
199  // cast the return value to `T`.
200  template <typename T>
201  auto import(T *From)
202  -> std::conditional_t<std::is_base_of_v<Type, T>, Expected<const T *>,
203  Expected<T *>> {
204  auto ToOrErr = Importer.Import(From);
205  if (!ToOrErr)
206  return ToOrErr.takeError();
207  return cast_or_null<T>(*ToOrErr);
208  }
209 
210  template <typename T>
211  auto import(const T *From) {
212  return import(const_cast<T *>(From));
213  }
214 
215  // Call the import function of ASTImporter for type `T`.
216  template <typename T>
217  Expected<T> import(const T &From) {
218  return Importer.Import(From);
219  }
220 
221  // Import an std::optional<T> by importing the contained T, if any.
222  template <typename T>
223  Expected<std::optional<T>> import(std::optional<T> From) {
224  if (!From)
225  return std::nullopt;
226  return import(*From);
227  }

232  // Wrapper for an overload set.
233  template <typename ToDeclT> struct CallOverloadedCreateFun {
234  template <typename... Args> decltype(auto) operator()(Args &&... args) {
235  return ToDeclT::Create(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
236  }
237  };
238 
239  // Always use these functions to create a Decl during import. There are
240  // certain tasks which must be done after the Decl was created, e.g. we
241  // must immediately register that as an imported Decl. The parameter `ToD`
242  // will be set to the newly created Decl or if had been imported before
243  // then to the already imported Decl. Returns a bool value set to true if
244  // the `FromD` had been imported before.
245  template <typename ToDeclT, typename FromDeclT, typename... Args>
246  [[nodiscard]] bool GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToDeclT *&ToD, FromDeclT *FromD,
247  Args &&...args) {
248  // There may be several overloads of ToDeclT::Create. We must make sure
249  // to call the one which would be chosen by the arguments, thus we use a
250  // wrapper for the overload set.
251  CallOverloadedCreateFun<ToDeclT> OC;
252  return GetImportedOrCreateSpecialDecl(ToD, OC, FromD,
253  std::forward<Args>(args)...);
254  }
255  // Use this overload if a special Type is needed to be created. E.g if we
256  // want to create a `TypeAliasDecl` and assign that to a `TypedefNameDecl`
257  // then:
258  // TypedefNameDecl *ToTypedef;
259  // GetImportedOrCreateDecl<TypeAliasDecl>(ToTypedef, FromD, ...);
260  template <typename NewDeclT, typename ToDeclT, typename FromDeclT,
261  typename... Args>
262  [[nodiscard]] bool GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToDeclT *&ToD, FromDeclT *FromD,
263  Args &&...args) {
264  CallOverloadedCreateFun<NewDeclT> OC;
265  return GetImportedOrCreateSpecialDecl(ToD, OC, FromD,
266  std::forward<Args>(args)...);
267  }
268  // Use this version if a special create function must be
269  // used, e.g. CXXRecordDecl::CreateLambda .
270  template <typename ToDeclT, typename CreateFunT, typename FromDeclT,
271  typename... Args>
272  [[nodiscard]] bool
273  GetImportedOrCreateSpecialDecl(ToDeclT *&ToD, CreateFunT CreateFun,
274  FromDeclT *FromD, Args &&...args) {
275  if (Importer.getImportDeclErrorIfAny(FromD)) {
276  ToD = nullptr;
277  return true; // Already imported but with error.
278  }
279  ToD = cast_or_null<ToDeclT>(Importer.GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(FromD));
280  if (ToD)
281  return true; // Already imported.
282  ToD = CreateFun(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
283  // Keep track of imported Decls.
284  Importer.RegisterImportedDecl(FromD, ToD);
285  Importer.SharedState->markAsNewDecl(ToD);
286  InitializeImportedDecl(FromD, ToD);
287  return false; // A new Decl is created.
288  }
289 
290  void InitializeImportedDecl(Decl *FromD, Decl *ToD) {
291  ToD->IdentifierNamespace = FromD->IdentifierNamespace;
292  if (FromD->isUsed())
293  ToD->setIsUsed();
294  if (FromD->isImplicit())
295  ToD->setImplicit();
296  }
297 
298  // Check if we have found an existing definition. Returns with that
299  // definition if yes, otherwise returns null.
300  Decl *FindAndMapDefinition(FunctionDecl *D, FunctionDecl *FoundFunction) {
301  const FunctionDecl *Definition = nullptr;
302  if (D->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody() &&
303  FoundFunction->hasBody(Definition))
304  return Importer.MapImported(D, const_cast<FunctionDecl *>(Definition));
305  return nullptr;
306  }
307 
308  void addDeclToContexts(Decl *FromD, Decl *ToD) {
309  if (Importer.isMinimalImport()) {
310  // In minimal import case the decl must be added even if it is not
311  // contained in original context, for LLDB compatibility.
312  // FIXME: Check if a better solution is possible.
313  if (!FromD->getDescribedTemplate() &&
314  FromD->getFriendObjectKind() == Decl::FOK_None)
315  ToD->getLexicalDeclContext()->addDeclInternal(ToD);
316  return;
317  }
318 
319  DeclContext *FromDC = FromD->getDeclContext();
320  DeclContext *FromLexicalDC = FromD->getLexicalDeclContext();
321  DeclContext *ToDC = ToD->getDeclContext();
322  DeclContext *ToLexicalDC = ToD->getLexicalDeclContext();
323 
324  bool Visible = false;
325  if (FromDC->containsDeclAndLoad(FromD)) {
326  ToDC->addDeclInternal(ToD);
327  Visible = true;
328  }
329  if (ToDC != ToLexicalDC && FromLexicalDC->containsDeclAndLoad(FromD)) {
330  ToLexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToD);
331  Visible = true;
332  }
333 
334  // If the Decl was added to any context, it was made already visible.
335  // Otherwise it is still possible that it should be visible.
336  if (!Visible) {
337  if (auto *FromNamed = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(FromD)) {
338  auto *ToNamed = cast<NamedDecl>(ToD);
339  DeclContextLookupResult FromLookup =
340  FromDC->lookup(FromNamed->getDeclName());
341  if (llvm::is_contained(FromLookup, FromNamed))
342  ToDC->makeDeclVisibleInContext(ToNamed);
343  }
344  }
345  }
346 
347  void updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(TemplateParameterList &Params,
348  DeclContext *OldDC) {
349  ASTImporterLookupTable *LT = Importer.SharedState->getLookupTable();
350  if (!LT)
351  return;
352 
353  for (NamedDecl *TP : Params)
354  LT->update(TP, OldDC);
355  }
356 
357  void updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(TemplateParameterList &Params) {
358  updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(
359  Params, Importer.getToContext().getTranslationUnitDecl());
360  }

395  /// What we should import from the definition.
396  enum ImportDefinitionKind {
397  /// Import the default subset of the definition, which might be
398  /// nothing (if minimal import is set) or might be everything (if minimal
399  /// import is not set).
400  IDK_Default,
401  /// Import everything.
402  IDK_Everything,
403  /// Import only the bare bones needed to establish a valid
404  /// DeclContext.
405  IDK_Basic
406  };
407 
408  bool shouldForceImportDeclContext(ImportDefinitionKind IDK) {
409  return IDK == IDK_Everything ||
410  (IDK == IDK_Default && !Importer.isMinimalImport());
411  }

645  // Helper for chaining together multiple imports. If an error is detected,
646  // subsequent imports will return default constructed nodes, so that failure
647  // can be detected with a single conditional branch after a sequence of
648  // imports.
649  template <typename T> T importChecked(Error &Err, const T &From) {
650  // Don't attempt to import nodes if we hit an error earlier.
651  if (Err)
652  return T{};
653  Expected<T> MaybeVal = import(From);
654  if (!MaybeVal) {
655  Err = MaybeVal.takeError();
656  return T{};
657  }
658  return *MaybeVal;
659  }
660 
661  template<typename IIter, typename OIter>
662  Error ImportArrayChecked(IIter Ibegin, IIter Iend, OIter Obegin) {
663  using ItemT = std::remove_reference_t<decltype(*Obegin)>;
664  for (; Ibegin != Iend; ++Ibegin, ++Obegin) {
665  Expected<ItemT> ToOrErr = import(*Ibegin);
666  if (!ToOrErr)
667  return ToOrErr.takeError();
668  *Obegin = *ToOrErr;
669  }
670  return Error::success();
671  }
672 
673  // Import every item from a container structure into an output container.
674  // If error occurs, stops at first error and returns the error.
675  // The output container should have space for all needed elements (it is not
676  // expanded, new items are put into from the beginning).
677  template<typename InContainerTy, typename OutContainerTy>
678  Error ImportContainerChecked(
679  const InContainerTy &InContainer, OutContainerTy &OutContainer) {
680  return ImportArrayChecked(
681  InContainer.begin(), InContainer.end(), OutContainer.begin());
682  }
683 
684  template<typename InContainerTy, typename OIter>
685  Error ImportArrayChecked(const InContainerTy &InContainer, OIter Obegin) {
686  return ImportArrayChecked(InContainer.begin(), InContainer.end(), Obegin);
687  }
688 
689  Error ImportOverriddenMethods(CXXMethodDecl *ToMethod,
690  CXXMethodDecl *FromMethod);
691 
692  Expected<FunctionDecl *> FindFunctionTemplateSpecialization(
693  FunctionDecl *FromFD);
694 
695  // Returns true if the given function has a placeholder return type and
696  // that type is declared inside the body of the function.
697  // E.g. auto f() { struct X{}; return X(); }
698  bool hasReturnTypeDeclaredInside(FunctionDecl *D);
699  };

701 template <typename InContainerTy>
702 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(
703  SourceLocation FromLAngleLoc, SourceLocation FromRAngleLoc,
704  const InContainerTy &Container, TemplateArgumentListInfo &Result) {
705  auto ToLAngleLocOrErr = import(FromLAngleLoc);
706  if (!ToLAngleLocOrErr)
707  return ToLAngleLocOrErr.takeError();
708  auto ToRAngleLocOrErr = import(FromRAngleLoc);
709  if (!ToRAngleLocOrErr)
710  return ToRAngleLocOrErr.takeError();
711 
712  TemplateArgumentListInfo ToTAInfo(*ToLAngleLocOrErr, *ToRAngleLocOrErr);
713  if (auto Err = ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(Container, ToTAInfo))
714  return Err;
715  Result = ToTAInfo;
716  return Error::success();
717 }

723  From.getLAngleLoc(), From.getRAngleLoc(), From.arguments(), Result);
724 }

735 Expected<ASTNodeImporter::FunctionTemplateAndArgsTy>
736 ASTNodeImporter::ImportFunctionTemplateWithTemplateArgsFromSpecialization(
737  FunctionDecl *FromFD) {
738  assert(FromFD->getTemplatedKind() ==
739  FunctionDecl::TK_FunctionTemplateSpecialization);
740 
741  FunctionTemplateAndArgsTy Result;
742 
743  auto *FTSInfo = FromFD->getTemplateSpecializationInfo();
744  if (Error Err = importInto(std::get<0>(Result), FTSInfo->getTemplate()))
745  return std::move(Err);
746 
747  // Import template arguments.
748  if (Error Err = ImportTemplateArguments(FTSInfo->TemplateArguments->asArray(),
749  std::get<1>(Result)))
750  return std::move(Err);
751 
752  return Result;
753 }

755 template <>
756 Expected<TemplateParameterList *>
757 ASTNodeImporter::import(TemplateParameterList *From) {
758  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> To(From->size());
759  if (Error Err = ImportContainerChecked(*From, To))
760  return std::move(Err);
761 
762  ExpectedExpr ToRequiresClause = import(From->getRequiresClause());
763  if (!ToRequiresClause)
764  return ToRequiresClause.takeError();
765 
766  auto ToTemplateLocOrErr = import(From->getTemplateLoc());
767  if (!ToTemplateLocOrErr)
768  return ToTemplateLocOrErr.takeError();
769  auto ToLAngleLocOrErr = import(From->getLAngleLoc());
770  if (!ToLAngleLocOrErr)
771  return ToLAngleLocOrErr.takeError();
772  auto ToRAngleLocOrErr = import(From->getRAngleLoc());
773  if (!ToRAngleLocOrErr)
774  return ToRAngleLocOrErr.takeError();
775 
776  return TemplateParameterList::Create(
777  Importer.getToContext(),
778  *ToTemplateLocOrErr,
779  *ToLAngleLocOrErr,
780  To,
781  *ToRAngleLocOrErr,
782  *ToRequiresClause);
783 }

785 template <>
786 Expected<TemplateArgument>
787 ASTNodeImporter::import(const TemplateArgument &From) {
788  switch (From.getKind()) {
789  case TemplateArgument::Null:
790  return TemplateArgument();
791 
792  case TemplateArgument::Type: {
793  ExpectedType ToTypeOrErr = import(From.getAsType());
794  if (!ToTypeOrErr)
795  return ToTypeOrErr.takeError();
796  return TemplateArgument(*ToTypeOrErr, /*isNullPtr*/ false,
797  From.getIsDefaulted());
798  }
799 
800  case TemplateArgument::Integral: {
801  ExpectedType ToTypeOrErr = import(From.getIntegralType());
802  if (!ToTypeOrErr)
803  return ToTypeOrErr.takeError();
804  return TemplateArgument(From, *ToTypeOrErr);
805  }
806 
807  case TemplateArgument::Declaration: {
808  Expected<ValueDecl *> ToOrErr = import(From.getAsDecl());
809  if (!ToOrErr)
810  return ToOrErr.takeError();
811  ExpectedType ToTypeOrErr = import(From.getParamTypeForDecl());
812  if (!ToTypeOrErr)
813  return ToTypeOrErr.takeError();
814  return TemplateArgument(dyn_cast<ValueDecl>((*ToOrErr)->getCanonicalDecl()),
815  *ToTypeOrErr, From.getIsDefaulted());
816  }
817 
818  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr: {
819  ExpectedType ToTypeOrErr = import(From.getNullPtrType());
820  if (!ToTypeOrErr)
821  return ToTypeOrErr.takeError();
822  return TemplateArgument(*ToTypeOrErr, /*isNullPtr*/ true,
823  From.getIsDefaulted());
824  }
825 
826  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue: {
827  ExpectedType ToTypeOrErr = import(From.getStructuralValueType());
828  if (!ToTypeOrErr)
829  return ToTypeOrErr.takeError();
830  Expected<APValue> ToValueOrErr = import(From.getAsStructuralValue());
831  if (!ToValueOrErr)
832  return ToValueOrErr.takeError();
833  return TemplateArgument(Importer.getToContext(), *ToTypeOrErr,
834  *ToValueOrErr);
835  }
836 
837  case TemplateArgument::Template: {
838  Expected<TemplateName> ToTemplateOrErr = import(From.getAsTemplate());
839  if (!ToTemplateOrErr)
840  return ToTemplateOrErr.takeError();
841 
842  return TemplateArgument(*ToTemplateOrErr, From.getIsDefaulted());
843  }
844 
845  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion: {
846  Expected<TemplateName> ToTemplateOrErr =
847  import(From.getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern());
848  if (!ToTemplateOrErr)
849  return ToTemplateOrErr.takeError();
850 
851  return TemplateArgument(*ToTemplateOrErr, From.getNumTemplateExpansions(),
852  From.getIsDefaulted());
853  }
854 
855  case TemplateArgument::Expression:
856  if (ExpectedExpr ToExpr = import(From.getAsExpr()))
857  return TemplateArgument(*ToExpr, From.getIsDefaulted());
858  else
859  return ToExpr.takeError();
860 
861  case TemplateArgument::Pack: {
862  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 2> ToPack;
863  ToPack.reserve(From.pack_size());
864  if (Error Err = ImportTemplateArguments(From.pack_elements(), ToPack))
865  return std::move(Err);
866 
867  return TemplateArgument(
868  llvm::ArrayRef(ToPack).copy(Importer.getToContext()));
869  }
870  }
871 
872  llvm_unreachable("Invalid template argument kind");
873 }
874 
875 template <>
876 Expected<TemplateArgumentLoc>
877 ASTNodeImporter::import(const TemplateArgumentLoc &TALoc) {
878  Expected<TemplateArgument> ArgOrErr = import(TALoc.getArgument());
879  if (!ArgOrErr)
880  return ArgOrErr.takeError();
881  TemplateArgument Arg = *ArgOrErr;
882 
883  TemplateArgumentLocInfo FromInfo = TALoc.getLocInfo();
884 
885  TemplateArgumentLocInfo ToInfo;
886  if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Expression) {
887  ExpectedExpr E = import(FromInfo.getAsExpr());
888  if (!E)
889  return E.takeError();
890  ToInfo = TemplateArgumentLocInfo(*E);
891  } else if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Type) {
892  if (auto TSIOrErr = import(FromInfo.getAsTypeSourceInfo()))
893  ToInfo = TemplateArgumentLocInfo(*TSIOrErr);
894  else
895  return TSIOrErr.takeError();
896  } else {
897  auto ToTemplateQualifierLocOrErr =
898  import(FromInfo.getTemplateQualifierLoc());
899  if (!ToTemplateQualifierLocOrErr)
900  return ToTemplateQualifierLocOrErr.takeError();
901  auto ToTemplateNameLocOrErr = import(FromInfo.getTemplateNameLoc());
902  if (!ToTemplateNameLocOrErr)
903  return ToTemplateNameLocOrErr.takeError();
904  auto ToTemplateEllipsisLocOrErr =
905  import(FromInfo.getTemplateEllipsisLoc());
906  if (!ToTemplateEllipsisLocOrErr)
907  return ToTemplateEllipsisLocOrErr.takeError();
908  ToInfo = TemplateArgumentLocInfo(
909  Importer.getToContext(), *ToTemplateQualifierLocOrErr,
910  *ToTemplateNameLocOrErr, *ToTemplateEllipsisLocOrErr);
911  }
912 
913  return TemplateArgumentLoc(Arg, ToInfo);
914 }
915 
916 template <>
917 Expected<DeclGroupRef> ASTNodeImporter::import(const DeclGroupRef &DG) {
918  if (DG.isNull())
919  return DeclGroupRef::Create(Importer.getToContext(), nullptr, 0);
920  size_t NumDecls = DG.end() - DG.begin();
921  SmallVector<Decl *, 1> ToDecls;
922  ToDecls.reserve(NumDecls);
923  for (Decl *FromD : DG) {
924  if (auto ToDOrErr = import(FromD))
925  ToDecls.push_back(*ToDOrErr);
926  else
927  return ToDOrErr.takeError();
928  }
929  return DeclGroupRef::Create(Importer.getToContext(),
930  ToDecls.begin(),
931  NumDecls);
932 }

934 template <>
935 Expected<ASTNodeImporter::Designator>
936 ASTNodeImporter::import(const Designator &D) {
937  if (D.isFieldDesignator()) {
938  IdentifierInfo *ToFieldName = Importer.Import(D.getFieldName());
939 
940  ExpectedSLoc ToDotLocOrErr = import(D.getDotLoc());
941  if (!ToDotLocOrErr)
942  return ToDotLocOrErr.takeError();
943 
944  ExpectedSLoc ToFieldLocOrErr = import(D.getFieldLoc());
945  if (!ToFieldLocOrErr)
946  return ToFieldLocOrErr.takeError();
947 
948  return DesignatedInitExpr::Designator::CreateFieldDesignator(
949  ToFieldName, *ToDotLocOrErr, *ToFieldLocOrErr);
950  }
951 
952  ExpectedSLoc ToLBracketLocOrErr = import(D.getLBracketLoc());
953  if (!ToLBracketLocOrErr)
954  return ToLBracketLocOrErr.takeError();
955 
956  ExpectedSLoc ToRBracketLocOrErr = import(D.getRBracketLoc());
957  if (!ToRBracketLocOrErr)
958  return ToRBracketLocOrErr.takeError();
959 
960  if (D.isArrayDesignator())
961  return Designator::CreateArrayDesignator(D.getArrayIndex(),
962  *ToLBracketLocOrErr,
963  *ToRBracketLocOrErr);
964 
965  ExpectedSLoc ToEllipsisLocOrErr = import(D.getEllipsisLoc());
966  if (!ToEllipsisLocOrErr)
967  return ToEllipsisLocOrErr.takeError();
968 
969  assert(D.isArrayRangeDesignator());
970  return Designator::CreateArrayRangeDesignator(
971  D.getArrayIndex(), *ToLBracketLocOrErr, *ToEllipsisLocOrErr,
972  *ToRBracketLocOrErr);
973 }

975 template <>
976 Expected<ConceptReference *> ASTNodeImporter::import(ConceptReference *From) {
977  Error Err = Error::success();
978  auto ToNNS = importChecked(Err, From->getNestedNameSpecifierLoc());
979  auto ToTemplateKWLoc = importChecked(Err, From->getTemplateKWLoc());
980  auto ToConceptNameLoc =
981  importChecked(Err, From->getConceptNameInfo().getLoc());
982  auto ToConceptName = importChecked(Err, From->getConceptNameInfo().getName());
983  auto ToFoundDecl = importChecked(Err, From->getFoundDecl());
984  auto ToNamedConcept = importChecked(Err, From->getNamedConcept());
985  if (Err)
986  return std::move(Err);
987  TemplateArgumentListInfo ToTAInfo;
988  const auto *ASTTemplateArgs = From->getTemplateArgsAsWritten();
989  if (ASTTemplateArgs)
990  if (Error Err = ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(*ASTTemplateArgs, ToTAInfo))
991  return std::move(Err);
992  auto *ConceptRef = ConceptReference::Create(
993  Importer.getToContext(), ToNNS, ToTemplateKWLoc,
994  DeclarationNameInfo(ToConceptName, ToConceptNameLoc), ToFoundDecl,
995  ToNamedConcept,
996  ASTTemplateArgs ? ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo::Create(
997  Importer.getToContext(), ToTAInfo)
998  : nullptr);
999  return ConceptRef;
1000 }

1002 template <>
1003 Expected<LambdaCapture> ASTNodeImporter::import(const LambdaCapture &From) {
1004  ValueDecl *Var = nullptr;
1005  if (From.capturesVariable()) {
1006  if (auto VarOrErr = import(From.getCapturedVar()))
1007  Var = *VarOrErr;
1008  else
1009  return VarOrErr.takeError();
1010  }
1011 
1012  auto LocationOrErr = import(From.getLocation());
1013  if (!LocationOrErr)
1014  return LocationOrErr.takeError();
1015 
1016  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
1017  if (From.isPackExpansion())
1018  if (Error Err = importInto(EllipsisLoc, From.getEllipsisLoc()))
1019  return std::move(Err);
1020 
1021  return LambdaCapture(
1022  *LocationOrErr, From.isImplicit(), From.getCaptureKind(), Var,
1023  EllipsisLoc);
1024 }

1026 template <typename T>
1027 bool ASTNodeImporter::hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(T *Found, T *From) {
1028  if (Found->getLinkageInternal() != From->getLinkageInternal())
1029  return false;
1030 
1031  if (From->hasExternalFormalLinkage())
1032  return Found->hasExternalFormalLinkage();
1033  if (Importer.GetFromTU(Found) != From->getTranslationUnitDecl())
1034  return false;
1035  if (From->isInAnonymousNamespace())
1036  return Found->isInAnonymousNamespace();
1037  else
1038  return !Found->isInAnonymousNamespace() &&
1039  !Found->hasExternalFormalLinkage();
1040 }
1041 
1042 template <>
1043 bool ASTNodeImporter::hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(TypedefNameDecl *Found,
1044  TypedefNameDecl *From) {
1045  if (Found->getLinkageInternal() != From->getLinkageInternal())
1046  return false;
1047 
1048  if (From->isInAnonymousNamespace() && Found->isInAnonymousNamespace())
1049  return Importer.GetFromTU(Found) == From->getTranslationUnitDecl();
1050  return From->isInAnonymousNamespace() == Found->isInAnonymousNamespace();
1051 }

1075 ExpectedType ASTNodeImporter::VisitBuiltinType(const BuiltinType *T) {
1076  switch (T->getKind()) {
1077 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
1078  case BuiltinType::Id: \
1079  return Importer.getToContext().SingletonId;
1080 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
1081 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
1082  case BuiltinType::Sampled##Id: \
1083  return Importer.getToContext().Sampled##SingletonId;
1084 #define IMAGE_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
1085 #define IMAGE_READ_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
1086 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
1087 #define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
1088  case BuiltinType::Id: \
1089  return Importer.getToContext().Id##Ty;
1090 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
1091 #define SVE_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) \
1092  case BuiltinType::Id: \
1093  return Importer.getToContext().SingletonId;
1094 #include "clang/Basic/AArch64SVEACLETypes.def"
1095 #define PPC_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, Size) \
1096  case BuiltinType::Id: \
1097  return Importer.getToContext().Id##Ty;
1098 #include "clang/Basic/PPCTypes.def"
1099 #define RVV_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) \
1100  case BuiltinType::Id: \
1101  return Importer.getToContext().SingletonId;
1102 #include "clang/Basic/RISCVVTypes.def"
1103 #define WASM_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) \
1104  case BuiltinType::Id: \
1105  return Importer.getToContext().SingletonId;
1106 #include "clang/Basic/WebAssemblyReferenceTypes.def"
1107 #define SHARED_SINGLETON_TYPE(Expansion)
1108 #define BUILTIN_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) \
1109  case BuiltinType::Id: return Importer.getToContext().SingletonId;
1110 #include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
1111 
1112  // FIXME: for Char16, Char32, and NullPtr, make sure that the "to"
1113  // context supports C++.
1114 
1115  // FIXME: for ObjCId, ObjCClass, and ObjCSel, make sure that the "to"
1116  // context supports ObjC.
1117 
1118  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
1119  // The context we're importing from has an unsigned 'char'. If we're
1120  // importing into a context with a signed 'char', translate to
1121  // 'unsigned char' instead.
1122  if (Importer.getToContext().getLangOpts().CharIsSigned)
1123  return Importer.getToContext().UnsignedCharTy;
1124 
1125  return Importer.getToContext().CharTy;
1126 
1127  case BuiltinType::Char_S:
1128  // The context we're importing from has an unsigned 'char'. If we're
1129  // importing into a context with a signed 'char', translate to
1130  // 'unsigned char' instead.
1131  if (!Importer.getToContext().getLangOpts().CharIsSigned)
1132  return Importer.getToContext().SignedCharTy;
1133 
1134  return Importer.getToContext().CharTy;
1135 
1136  case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
1137  case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
1138  // FIXME: If not in C++, shall we translate to the C equivalent of
1139  // wchar_t?
1140  return Importer.getToContext().WCharTy;
1141  }
1142 
1143  llvm_unreachable("Invalid BuiltinType Kind!");
1144 }

1308 ASTNodeImporter::VisitFunctionNoProtoType(const FunctionNoProtoType *T) {
1309  // FIXME: What happens if we're importing a function without a prototype
1310  // into C++? Should we make it variadic?

1312  if (!ToReturnTypeOrErr)

1318 
1319 ExpectedType
1320 ASTNodeImporter::VisitFunctionProtoType(const FunctionProtoType *T) {
1321  ExpectedType ToReturnTypeOrErr = import(T->getReturnType());
1322  if (!ToReturnTypeOrErr)
1323  return ToReturnTypeOrErr.takeError();
1324 
1325  // Import argument types
1326  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ArgTypes;
1327  for (const auto &A : T->param_types()) {
1328  ExpectedType TyOrErr = import(A);
1329  if (!TyOrErr)
1330  return TyOrErr.takeError();
1331  ArgTypes.push_back(*TyOrErr);
1332  }
1333 
1334  // Import exception types
1335  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ExceptionTypes;
1336  for (const auto &E : T->exceptions()) {
1337  ExpectedType TyOrErr = import(E);
1338  if (!TyOrErr)
1339  return TyOrErr.takeError();
1340  ExceptionTypes.push_back(*TyOrErr);
1341  }
1342 
1343  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo FromEPI = T->getExtProtoInfo();
1344  Error Err = Error::success();
1345  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo ToEPI;
1346  ToEPI.ExtInfo = FromEPI.ExtInfo;
1347  ToEPI.Variadic = FromEPI.Variadic;
1348  ToEPI.HasTrailingReturn = FromEPI.HasTrailingReturn;
1349  ToEPI.TypeQuals = FromEPI.TypeQuals;
1350  ToEPI.RefQualifier = FromEPI.RefQualifier;
1351  ToEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = FromEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type;
1352  ToEPI.ExceptionSpec.NoexceptExpr =
1353  importChecked(Err, FromEPI.ExceptionSpec.NoexceptExpr);
1354  ToEPI.ExceptionSpec.SourceDecl =
1355  importChecked(Err, FromEPI.ExceptionSpec.SourceDecl);
1356  ToEPI.ExceptionSpec.SourceTemplate =
1357  importChecked(Err, FromEPI.ExceptionSpec.SourceTemplate);
1358  ToEPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions = ExceptionTypes;
1359 
1360  if (Err)
1361  return std::move(Err);
1362 
1363  return Importer.getToContext().getFunctionType(
1364  *ToReturnTypeOrErr, ArgTypes, ToEPI);
1365 }

1549  return ToWrappedTypeOrErr.takeError();

1563  *ToWrappedTypeOrErr, CountExpr, T->isCountInBytes(), T->isOrNull(),
1564  ArrayRef(CoupledDecls.data(), CoupledDecls.size()));

1873 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1874 // Import Declarations
1875 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1876 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportDeclParts(
1877  NamedDecl *D, DeclContext *&DC, DeclContext *&LexicalDC,
1878  DeclarationName &Name, NamedDecl *&ToD, SourceLocation &Loc) {
1879  // Check if RecordDecl is in FunctionDecl parameters to avoid infinite loop.
1880  // example: int struct_in_proto(struct data_t{int a;int b;} *d);
1881  // FIXME: We could support these constructs by importing a different type of
1882  // this parameter and by importing the original type of the parameter only
1883  // after the FunctionDecl is created. See
1884  // VisitFunctionDecl::UsedDifferentProtoType.
1885  DeclContext *OrigDC = D->getDeclContext();
1886  FunctionDecl *FunDecl;
1887  if (isa<RecordDecl>(D) && (FunDecl = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(OrigDC)) &&
1888  FunDecl->hasBody()) {
1889  auto getLeafPointeeType = [](const Type *T) {
1890  while (T->isPointerType() || T->isArrayType()) {
1891  T = T->getPointeeOrArrayElementType();
1892  }
1893  return T;
1894  };
1895  for (const ParmVarDecl *P : FunDecl->parameters()) {
1896  const Type *LeafT =
1897  getLeafPointeeType(P->getType().getCanonicalType().getTypePtr());
1898  auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(LeafT);
1899  if (RT && RT->getDecl() == D) {
1900  Importer.FromDiag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_unsupported_ast_node)
1901  << D->getDeclKindName();
1902  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::UnsupportedConstruct);
1903  }
1904  }
1905  }
1906 
1907  // Import the context of this declaration.
1908  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D, DC, LexicalDC))
1909  return Err;
1910 
1911  // Import the name of this declaration.
1912  if (Error Err = importInto(Name, D->getDeclName()))
1913  return Err;
1914 
1915  // Import the location of this declaration.
1916  if (Error Err = importInto(Loc, D->getLocation()))
1917  return Err;
1918 
1919  ToD = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(Importer.GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(D));
1920  if (ToD)
1921  if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinitionIfNeeded(D, ToD))
1922  return Err;
1923 
1924  return Error::success();
1925 }
1926 
1927 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportDeclParts(NamedDecl *D, DeclarationName &Name,
1928  NamedDecl *&ToD, SourceLocation &Loc) {
1929 
1930  // Import the name of this declaration.
1931  if (Error Err = importInto(Name, D->getDeclName()))
1932  return Err;
1933 
1934  // Import the location of this declaration.
1935  if (Error Err = importInto(Loc, D->getLocation()))
1936  return Err;
1937 
1938  ToD = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(Importer.GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(D));
1939  if (ToD)
1940  if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinitionIfNeeded(D, ToD))
1941  return Err;
1942 
1943  return Error::success();
1944 }
1945 
1946 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportDefinitionIfNeeded(Decl *FromD, Decl *ToD) {
1947  if (!FromD)
1948  return Error::success();
1949 
1950  if (!ToD)
1951  if (Error Err = importInto(ToD, FromD))
1952  return Err;
1953 
1954  if (RecordDecl *FromRecord = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(FromD)) {
1955  if (RecordDecl *ToRecord = cast<RecordDecl>(ToD)) {
1956  if (FromRecord->getDefinition() && FromRecord->isCompleteDefinition() &&
1957  !ToRecord->getDefinition()) {
1958  if (Error Err = ImportDefinition(FromRecord, ToRecord))
1959  return Err;
1960  }
1961  }
1962  return Error::success();
1963  }
1964 
1965  if (EnumDecl *FromEnum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(FromD)) {
1966  if (EnumDecl *ToEnum = cast<EnumDecl>(ToD)) {
1967  if (FromEnum->getDefinition() && !ToEnum->getDefinition()) {
1968  if (Error Err = ImportDefinition(FromEnum, ToEnum))
1969  return Err;
1970  }
1971  }
1972  return Error::success();
1973  }
1974 
1975  return Error::success();
1976 }
1977 
1978 Error
1979 ASTNodeImporter::ImportDeclarationNameLoc(
1980  const DeclarationNameInfo &From, DeclarationNameInfo& To) {
1981  // NOTE: To.Name and To.Loc are already imported.
1982  // We only have to import To.LocInfo.
1983  switch (To.getName().getNameKind()) {
1984  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
1985  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
1986  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
1987  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
1988  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
1989  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
1990  return Error::success();
1991 
1992  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName: {
1993  if (auto ToRangeOrErr = import(From.getCXXOperatorNameRange()))
1994  To.setCXXOperatorNameRange(*ToRangeOrErr);
1995  else
1996  return ToRangeOrErr.takeError();
1997  return Error::success();
1998  }
1999  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName: {
2000  if (ExpectedSLoc LocOrErr = import(From.getCXXLiteralOperatorNameLoc()))
2001  To.setCXXLiteralOperatorNameLoc(*LocOrErr);
2002  else
2003  return LocOrErr.takeError();
2004  return Error::success();
2005  }
2006  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
2007  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
2008  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName: {
2009  if (auto ToTInfoOrErr = import(From.getNamedTypeInfo()))
2010  To.setNamedTypeInfo(*ToTInfoOrErr);
2011  else
2012  return ToTInfoOrErr.takeError();
2013  return Error::success();
2014  }
2015  }
2016  llvm_unreachable("Unknown name kind.");
2017 }
2018 
2019 Error
2020 ASTNodeImporter::ImportDeclContext(DeclContext *FromDC, bool ForceImport) {
2021  if (Importer.isMinimalImport() && !ForceImport) {
2022  auto ToDCOrErr = Importer.ImportContext(FromDC);
2023  return ToDCOrErr.takeError();
2024  }
2025 
2026  // We use strict error handling in case of records and enums, but not
2027  // with e.g. namespaces.
2028  //
2029  // FIXME Clients of the ASTImporter should be able to choose an
2030  // appropriate error handling strategy for their needs. For instance,
2031  // they may not want to mark an entire namespace as erroneous merely
2032  // because there is an ODR error with two typedefs. As another example,
2033  // the client may allow EnumConstantDecls with same names but with
2034  // different values in two distinct translation units.
2035  ChildErrorHandlingStrategy HandleChildErrors(FromDC);
2036 
2037  auto MightNeedReordering = [](const Decl *D) {
2038  return isa<FieldDecl>(D) || isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(D) || isa<FriendDecl>(D);
2039  };
2040 
2041  // Import everything that might need reordering first.
2042  Error ChildErrors = Error::success();
2043  for (auto *From : FromDC->decls()) {
2044  if (!MightNeedReordering(From))
2045  continue;
2046 
2047  ExpectedDecl ImportedOrErr = import(From);
2048 
2049  // If we are in the process of ImportDefinition(...) for a RecordDecl we
2050  // want to make sure that we are also completing each FieldDecl. There
2051  // are currently cases where this does not happen and this is correctness
2052  // fix since operations such as code generation will expect this to be so.
2053  if (!ImportedOrErr) {
2054  HandleChildErrors.handleChildImportResult(ChildErrors,
2055  ImportedOrErr.takeError());
2056  continue;
2057  }
2058  FieldDecl *FieldFrom = dyn_cast_or_null<FieldDecl>(From);
2059  Decl *ImportedDecl = *ImportedOrErr;
2060  FieldDecl *FieldTo = dyn_cast_or_null<FieldDecl>(ImportedDecl);
2061  if (FieldFrom && FieldTo) {
2062  Error Err = ImportFieldDeclDefinition(FieldFrom, FieldTo);
2063  HandleChildErrors.handleChildImportResult(ChildErrors, std::move(Err));
2064  }
2065  }
2066 
2067  // We reorder declarations in RecordDecls because they may have another order
2068  // in the "to" context than they have in the "from" context. This may happen
2069  // e.g when we import a class like this:
2070  // struct declToImport {
2071  // int a = c + b;
2072  // int b = 1;
2073  // int c = 2;
2074  // };
2075  // During the import of `a` we import first the dependencies in sequence,
2076  // thus the order would be `c`, `b`, `a`. We will get the normal order by
2077  // first removing the already imported members and then adding them in the
2078  // order as they appear in the "from" context.
2079  //
2080  // Keeping field order is vital because it determines structure layout.
2081  //
2082  // Here and below, we cannot call field_begin() method and its callers on
2083  // ToDC if it has an external storage. Calling field_begin() will
2084  // automatically load all the fields by calling
2085  // LoadFieldsFromExternalStorage(). LoadFieldsFromExternalStorage() would
2086  // call ASTImporter::Import(). This is because the ExternalASTSource
2087  // interface in LLDB is implemented by the means of the ASTImporter. However,
2088  // calling an import at this point would result in an uncontrolled import, we
2089  // must avoid that.
2090 
2091  auto ToDCOrErr = Importer.ImportContext(FromDC);
2092  if (!ToDCOrErr) {
2093  consumeError(std::move(ChildErrors));
2094  return ToDCOrErr.takeError();
2095  }
2096 
2097  if (const auto *FromRD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(FromDC)) {
2098  DeclContext *ToDC = *ToDCOrErr;
2099  // Remove all declarations, which may be in wrong order in the
2100  // lexical DeclContext and then add them in the proper order.
2101  for (auto *D : FromRD->decls()) {
2102  if (!MightNeedReordering(D))
2103  continue;
2104 
2105  assert(D && "DC contains a null decl");
2106  if (Decl *ToD = Importer.GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(D)) {
2107  // Remove only the decls which we successfully imported.
2108  assert(ToDC == ToD->getLexicalDeclContext() && ToDC->containsDecl(ToD));
2109  // Remove the decl from its wrong place in the linked list.
2110  ToDC->removeDecl(ToD);
2111  // Add the decl to the end of the linked list.
2112  // This time it will be at the proper place because the enclosing for
2113  // loop iterates in the original (good) order of the decls.
2114  ToDC->addDeclInternal(ToD);
2115  }
2116  }
2117  }
2118 
2119  // Import everything else.
2120  for (auto *From : FromDC->decls()) {
2121  if (MightNeedReordering(From))
2122  continue;
2123 
2124  ExpectedDecl ImportedOrErr = import(From);
2125  if (!ImportedOrErr)
2126  HandleChildErrors.handleChildImportResult(ChildErrors,
2127  ImportedOrErr.takeError());
2128  }
2129 
2130  return ChildErrors;
2131 }
2132 
2133 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportFieldDeclDefinition(const FieldDecl *From,
2134  const FieldDecl *To) {
2135  RecordDecl *FromRecordDecl = nullptr;
2136  RecordDecl *ToRecordDecl = nullptr;
2137  // If we have a field that is an ArrayType we need to check if the array
2138  // element is a RecordDecl and if so we need to import the definition.
2139  QualType FromType = From->getType();
2140  QualType ToType = To->getType();
2141  if (FromType->isArrayType()) {
2142  // getBaseElementTypeUnsafe(...) handles multi-dimensonal arrays for us.
2143  FromRecordDecl = FromType->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAsRecordDecl();
2144  ToRecordDecl = ToType->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAsRecordDecl();
2145  }
2146 
2147  if (!FromRecordDecl || !ToRecordDecl) {
2148  const RecordType *RecordFrom = FromType->getAs<RecordType>();
2149  const RecordType *RecordTo = ToType->getAs<RecordType>();
2150 
2151  if (RecordFrom && RecordTo) {
2152  FromRecordDecl = RecordFrom->getDecl();
2153  ToRecordDecl = RecordTo->getDecl();
2154  }
2155  }
2156 
2157  if (FromRecordDecl && ToRecordDecl) {
2158  if (FromRecordDecl->isCompleteDefinition() &&
2159  !ToRecordDecl->isCompleteDefinition())
2160  return ImportDefinition(FromRecordDecl, ToRecordDecl);
2161  }
2162 
2163  return Error::success();
2164 }
2165 
2166 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportDeclContext(
2167  Decl *FromD, DeclContext *&ToDC, DeclContext *&ToLexicalDC) {
2168  auto ToDCOrErr = Importer.ImportContext(FromD->getDeclContext());
2169  if (!ToDCOrErr)
2170  return ToDCOrErr.takeError();
2171  ToDC = *ToDCOrErr;
2172 
2173  if (FromD->getDeclContext() != FromD->getLexicalDeclContext()) {
2174  auto ToLexicalDCOrErr = Importer.ImportContext(
2175  FromD->getLexicalDeclContext());
2176  if (!ToLexicalDCOrErr)
2177  return ToLexicalDCOrErr.takeError();
2178  ToLexicalDC = *ToLexicalDCOrErr;
2179  } else
2180  ToLexicalDC = ToDC;
2181 
2182  return Error::success();
2183 }

2185 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportImplicitMethods(

2188  "Import implicit methods to or from non-definition");
2189

2191  if (FromM->isImplicit()) {
2192  Expected<CXXMethodDecl *> ToMOrErr = import(FromM);
2193  if (!ToMOrErr)
2194  return ToMOrErr.takeError();

2196 
2197  return Error::success();

2200 static Error setTypedefNameForAnonDecl(TagDecl *From, TagDecl *To,
2201  ASTImporter &Importer) {
2202  if (TypedefNameDecl *FromTypedef = From->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl()) {
2203  if (ExpectedDecl ToTypedefOrErr = Importer.Import(FromTypedef))
2204  To->setTypedefNameForAnonDecl(cast<TypedefNameDecl>(*ToTypedefOrErr));
2205  else
2206  return ToTypedefOrErr.takeError();

2210 
2211 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportDefinition(
2212  RecordDecl *From, RecordDecl *To, ImportDefinitionKind Kind) {
2213  auto DefinitionCompleter = [To]() {
2214  // There are cases in LLDB when we first import a class without its
2215  // members. The class will have DefinitionData, but no members. Then,
2216  // importDefinition is called from LLDB, which tries to get the members, so
2217  // when we get here, the class already has the DefinitionData set, so we
2218  // must unset the CompleteDefinition here to be able to complete again the
2219  // definition.
2220  To->setCompleteDefinition(false);
2221  To->completeDefinition();
2222  };
2223 
2224  if (To->getDefinition() || To->isBeingDefined()) {
2225  if (Kind == IDK_Everything ||
2226  // In case of lambdas, the class already has a definition ptr set, but
2227  // the contained decls are not imported yet. Also, isBeingDefined was
2228  // set in CXXRecordDecl::CreateLambda. We must import the contained
2229  // decls here and finish the definition.
2230  (To->isLambda() && shouldForceImportDeclContext(Kind))) {
2231  if (To->isLambda()) {
2232  auto *FromCXXRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(From);
2233  SmallVector<LambdaCapture, 8> ToCaptures;
2234  ToCaptures.reserve(FromCXXRD->capture_size());
2235  for (const auto &FromCapture : FromCXXRD->captures()) {
2236  if (auto ToCaptureOrErr = import(FromCapture))
2237  ToCaptures.push_back(*ToCaptureOrErr);
2238  else
2239  return ToCaptureOrErr.takeError();
2240  }
2241  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(To)->setCaptures(Importer.getToContext(),
2242  ToCaptures);
2243  }
2244 
2245  Error Result = ImportDeclContext(From, /*ForceImport=*/true);
2246  // Finish the definition of the lambda, set isBeingDefined to false.
2247  if (To->isLambda())
2248  DefinitionCompleter();
2249  return Result;
2250  }
2251 
2252  return Error::success();
2253  }
2254 
2255  To->startDefinition();
2256  // Set the definition to complete even if it is really not complete during
2257  // import. Some AST constructs (expressions) require the record layout
2258  // to be calculated (see 'clang::computeDependence') at the time they are
2259  // constructed. Import of such AST node is possible during import of the
2260  // same record, there is no way to have a completely defined record (all
2261  // fields imported) at that time without multiple AST import passes.
2262  if (!Importer.isMinimalImport())
2263  To->setCompleteDefinition(true);
2264  // Complete the definition even if error is returned.
2265  // The RecordDecl may be already part of the AST so it is better to
2266  // have it in complete state even if something is wrong with it.
2267  auto DefinitionCompleterScopeExit =
2268  llvm::make_scope_exit(DefinitionCompleter);
2269 
2270  if (Error Err = setTypedefNameForAnonDecl(From, To, Importer))
2271  return Err;
2272 
2273  // Add base classes.
2274  auto *ToCXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(To);
2275  auto *FromCXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(From);
2276  if (ToCXX && FromCXX && ToCXX->dataPtr() && FromCXX->dataPtr()) {
2277 
2278  struct CXXRecordDecl::DefinitionData &ToData = ToCXX->data();
2279  struct CXXRecordDecl::DefinitionData &FromData = FromCXX->data();
2280 
2281  #define FIELD(Name, Width, Merge) \
2282  ToData.Name = FromData.Name;
2283  #include "clang/AST/CXXRecordDeclDefinitionBits.def"
2284 
2285  // Copy over the data stored in RecordDeclBits
2286  ToCXX->setArgPassingRestrictions(FromCXX->getArgPassingRestrictions());
2287 
2288  SmallVector<CXXBaseSpecifier *, 4> Bases;
2289  for (const auto &Base1 : FromCXX->bases()) {
2290  ExpectedType TyOrErr = import(Base1.getType());
2291  if (!TyOrErr)
2292  return TyOrErr.takeError();
2293 
2294  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
2295  if (Base1.isPackExpansion()) {
2296  if (ExpectedSLoc LocOrErr = import(Base1.getEllipsisLoc()))
2297  EllipsisLoc = *LocOrErr;
2298  else
2299  return LocOrErr.takeError();
2300  }
2301 
2302  // Ensure that we have a definition for the base.
2303  if (Error Err =
2304  ImportDefinitionIfNeeded(Base1.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()))
2305  return Err;
2306 
2307  auto RangeOrErr = import(Base1.getSourceRange());
2308  if (!RangeOrErr)
2309  return RangeOrErr.takeError();
2310 
2311  auto TSIOrErr = import(Base1.getTypeSourceInfo());
2312  if (!TSIOrErr)
2313  return TSIOrErr.takeError();
2314 
2315  Bases.push_back(
2316  new (Importer.getToContext()) CXXBaseSpecifier(
2317  *RangeOrErr,
2318  Base1.isVirtual(),
2319  Base1.isBaseOfClass(),
2320  Base1.getAccessSpecifierAsWritten(),
2321  *TSIOrErr,
2322  EllipsisLoc));
2323  }
2324  if (!Bases.empty())
2325  ToCXX->setBases(Bases.data(), Bases.size());
2326  }
2327 
2328  if (shouldForceImportDeclContext(Kind)) {
2329  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(From, /*ForceImport=*/true))
2330  return Err;
2331  }
2332 
2333  return Error::success();
2334 }

2336 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportInitializer(VarDecl *From, VarDecl *To) {
2337  if (To->getAnyInitializer())
2338  return Error::success();
2339 
2340  Expr *FromInit = From->getInit();
2341  if (!FromInit)
2342  return Error::success();
2343 
2344  ExpectedExpr ToInitOrErr = import(FromInit);
2345  if (!ToInitOrErr)
2346  return ToInitOrErr.takeError();
2347 
2348  To->setInit(*ToInitOrErr);
2349  if (EvaluatedStmt *FromEval = From->getEvaluatedStmt()) {
2350  EvaluatedStmt *ToEval = To->ensureEvaluatedStmt();
2351  ToEval->HasConstantInitialization = FromEval->HasConstantInitialization;
2352  ToEval->HasConstantDestruction = FromEval->HasConstantDestruction;
2353  // FIXME: Also import the initializer value.
2354  }
2355 
2356  // FIXME: Other bits to merge?
2357  return Error::success();
2358 }

2360 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportDefinition(
2361  EnumDecl *From, EnumDecl *To, ImportDefinitionKind Kind) {
2362  if (To->getDefinition() || To->isBeingDefined()) {
2363  if (Kind == IDK_Everything)
2364  return ImportDeclContext(From, /*ForceImport=*/true);
2365  return Error::success();
2366  }
2367 
2368  To->startDefinition();
2369 
2370  if (Error Err = setTypedefNameForAnonDecl(From, To, Importer))
2371  return Err;
2372 
2373  ExpectedType ToTypeOrErr =
2374  import(Importer.getFromContext().getTypeDeclType(From));
2375  if (!ToTypeOrErr)
2376  return ToTypeOrErr.takeError();
2377 
2378  ExpectedType ToPromotionTypeOrErr = import(From->getPromotionType());
2379  if (!ToPromotionTypeOrErr)
2380  return ToPromotionTypeOrErr.takeError();
2381 
2382  if (shouldForceImportDeclContext(Kind))
2383  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(From, /*ForceImport=*/true))
2384  return Err;
2385 
2386  // FIXME: we might need to merge the number of positive or negative bits
2387  // if the enumerator lists don't match.
2388  To->completeDefinition(*ToTypeOrErr, *ToPromotionTypeOrErr,
2389  From->getNumPositiveBits(),
2390  From->getNumNegativeBits());
2391  return Error::success();
2392 }

2400  else

2402  }

2405 }

2426 getStructuralEquivalenceKind(const ASTImporter &Importer) {

2431 bool ASTNodeImporter::IsStructuralMatch(Decl *From, Decl *To, bool Complain,
2432  bool IgnoreTemplateParmDepth) {
2433  // Eliminate a potential failure point where we attempt to re-import
2434  // something we're trying to import while completing ToRecord.
2435  Decl *ToOrigin = Importer.GetOriginalDecl(To);
2436  if (ToOrigin) {
2437  To = ToOrigin;
2438  }
2439 
2440  StructuralEquivalenceContext Ctx(
2441  Importer.getFromContext(), Importer.getToContext(),
2442  Importer.getNonEquivalentDecls(), getStructuralEquivalenceKind(Importer),
2443  /*StrictTypeSpelling=*/false, Complain, /*ErrorOnTagTypeMismatch=*/false,
2444  IgnoreTemplateParmDepth);
2445  return Ctx.IsEquivalent(From, To);
2446 }

2571 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitNamespaceDecl(NamespaceDecl *D) {
2572  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this namespace.
2573  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
2574  DeclarationName Name;
2575  SourceLocation Loc;
2576  NamedDecl *ToD;
2577  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
2578  return std::move(Err);
2579  if (ToD)
2580  return ToD;
2581 
2582  NamespaceDecl *MergeWithNamespace = nullptr;
2583  if (!Name) {
2584  // This is an anonymous namespace. Adopt an existing anonymous
2585  // namespace if we can.
2586  // FIXME: Not testable.
2587  if (auto *TU = dyn_cast<TranslationUnitDecl>(DC))
2588  MergeWithNamespace = TU->getAnonymousNamespace();
2589  else
2590  MergeWithNamespace = cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)->getAnonymousNamespace();
2591  } else {
2592  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
2593  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
2594  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
2595  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(Decl::IDNS_Namespace))
2596  continue;
2597 
2598  if (auto *FoundNS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
2599  MergeWithNamespace = FoundNS;
2600  ConflictingDecls.clear();
2601  break;
2602  }
2603 
2604  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
2605  }
2606 
2607  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty()) {
2608  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
2609  Name, DC, Decl::IDNS_Namespace, ConflictingDecls.data(),
2610  ConflictingDecls.size());
2611  if (NameOrErr)
2612  Name = NameOrErr.get();
2613  else
2614  return NameOrErr.takeError();
2615  }
2616  }
2617 
2618  ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = import(D->getBeginLoc());
2619  if (!BeginLocOrErr)
2620  return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
2621  ExpectedSLoc RBraceLocOrErr = import(D->getRBraceLoc());
2622  if (!RBraceLocOrErr)
2623  return RBraceLocOrErr.takeError();
2624 
2625  // Create the "to" namespace, if needed.
2626  NamespaceDecl *ToNamespace = MergeWithNamespace;
2627  if (!ToNamespace) {
2628  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToNamespace, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC,
2629  D->isInline(), *BeginLocOrErr, Loc,
2630  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(),
2631  /*PrevDecl=*/nullptr, D->isNested()))
2632  return ToNamespace;
2633  ToNamespace->setRBraceLoc(*RBraceLocOrErr);
2634  ToNamespace->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2635  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToNamespace);
2636 
2637  // If this is an anonymous namespace, register it as the anonymous
2638  // namespace within its context.
2639  if (!Name) {
2640  if (auto *TU = dyn_cast<TranslationUnitDecl>(DC))
2641  TU->setAnonymousNamespace(ToNamespace);
2642  else
2643  cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)->setAnonymousNamespace(ToNamespace);
2644  }
2645  }
2646  Importer.MapImported(D, ToNamespace);
2647 
2648  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D))
2649  return std::move(Err);
2650 
2651  return ToNamespace;
2652 }
2653 
2654 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitNamespaceAliasDecl(NamespaceAliasDecl *D) {
2655  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this namespace.
2656  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
2657  DeclarationName Name;
2658  SourceLocation Loc;
2659  NamedDecl *LookupD;
2660  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, LookupD, Loc))
2661  return std::move(Err);
2662  if (LookupD)
2663  return LookupD;
2664 
2665  // NOTE: No conflict resolution is done for namespace aliases now.
2666 
2667  Error Err = Error::success();
2668  auto ToNamespaceLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getNamespaceLoc());
2669  auto ToAliasLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getAliasLoc());
2670  auto ToQualifierLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getQualifierLoc());
2671  auto ToTargetNameLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getTargetNameLoc());
2672  auto ToNamespace = importChecked(Err, D->getNamespace());
2673  if (Err)
2674  return std::move(Err);
2675 
2676  IdentifierInfo *ToIdentifier = Importer.Import(D->getIdentifier());
2677 
2678  NamespaceAliasDecl *ToD;
2679  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
2680  ToD, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, ToNamespaceLoc, ToAliasLoc,
2681  ToIdentifier, ToQualifierLoc, ToTargetNameLoc, ToNamespace))
2682  return ToD;
2683 
2684  ToD->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2685  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToD);
2686 
2687  return ToD;
2688 }
2689 
2690 ExpectedDecl
2691 ASTNodeImporter::VisitTypedefNameDecl(TypedefNameDecl *D, bool IsAlias) {
2692  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this typedef.
2693  DeclarationName Name;
2694  SourceLocation Loc;
2695  NamedDecl *ToD;
2696  // Do not import the DeclContext, we will import it once the TypedefNameDecl
2697  // is created.
2698  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, Name, ToD, Loc))
2699  return std::move(Err);
2700  if (ToD)
2701  return ToD;
2702 
2703  DeclContext *DC = cast_or_null<DeclContext>(
2704  Importer.GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(cast<Decl>(D->getDeclContext())));
2705  DeclContext *LexicalDC =
2706  cast_or_null<DeclContext>(Importer.GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(
2707  cast<Decl>(D->getLexicalDeclContext())));
2708 
2709  // If this typedef is not in block scope, determine whether we've
2710  // seen a typedef with the same name (that we can merge with) or any
2711  // other entity by that name (which name lookup could conflict with).
2712  // Note: Repeated typedefs are not valid in C99:
2713  // 'typedef int T; typedef int T;' is invalid
2714  // We do not care about this now.
2715  if (DC && !DC->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
2716  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
2717  unsigned IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
2718  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
2719  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
2720  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(IDNS))
2721  continue;
2722  if (auto *FoundTypedef = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
2723  if (!hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(FoundTypedef, D))
2724  continue;
2725 
2726  QualType FromUT = D->getUnderlyingType();
2727  QualType FoundUT = FoundTypedef->getUnderlyingType();
2728  if (Importer.IsStructurallyEquivalent(FromUT, FoundUT)) {
2729  // If the underlying declarations are unnamed records these can be
2730  // imported as different types. We should create a distinct typedef
2731  // node in this case.
2732  // If we found an existing underlying type with a record in a
2733  // different context (than the imported), this is already reason for
2734  // having distinct typedef nodes for these.
2735  // Again this can create situation like
2736  // 'typedef int T; typedef int T;' but this is hard to avoid without
2737  // a rename strategy at import.
2738  if (!FromUT.isNull() && !FoundUT.isNull()) {
2739  RecordDecl *FromR = FromUT->getAsRecordDecl();
2740  RecordDecl *FoundR = FoundUT->getAsRecordDecl();
2741  if (FromR && FoundR &&
2742  !hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(FoundR, FromR))
2743  continue;
2744  }
2745  // If the "From" context has a complete underlying type but we
2746  // already have a complete underlying type then return with that.
2747  if (!FromUT->isIncompleteType() && !FoundUT->isIncompleteType())
2748  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundTypedef);
2749  // FIXME Handle redecl chain. When you do that make consistent changes
2750  // in ASTImporterLookupTable too.
2751  } else {
2752  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
2753  }
2754  }
2755  }
2756 
2757  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty()) {
2758  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
2759  Name, DC, IDNS, ConflictingDecls.data(), ConflictingDecls.size());
2760  if (NameOrErr)
2761  Name = NameOrErr.get();
2762  else
2763  return NameOrErr.takeError();
2764  }
2765  }
2766 
2767  Error Err = Error::success();
2768  auto ToUnderlyingType = importChecked(Err, D->getUnderlyingType());
2769  auto ToTypeSourceInfo = importChecked(Err, D->getTypeSourceInfo());
2770  auto ToBeginLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getBeginLoc());
2771  if (Err)
2772  return std::move(Err);
2773 
2774  // Create the new typedef node.
2775  // FIXME: ToUnderlyingType is not used.
2776  (void)ToUnderlyingType;
2777  TypedefNameDecl *ToTypedef;
2778  if (IsAlias) {
2779  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl<TypeAliasDecl>(
2780  ToTypedef, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, ToBeginLoc, Loc,
2781  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(), ToTypeSourceInfo))
2782  return ToTypedef;
2783  } else if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl<TypedefDecl>(
2784  ToTypedef, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, ToBeginLoc, Loc,
2785  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(), ToTypeSourceInfo))
2786  return ToTypedef;
2787 
2788  // Import the DeclContext and set it to the Typedef.
2789  if ((Err = ImportDeclContext(D, DC, LexicalDC)))
2790  return std::move(Err);
2791  ToTypedef->setDeclContext(DC);
2792  ToTypedef->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2793  // Add to the lookupTable because we could not do that in MapImported.
2794  Importer.AddToLookupTable(ToTypedef);
2795 
2796  ToTypedef->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2797 
2798  // Templated declarations should not appear in DeclContext.
2799  TypeAliasDecl *FromAlias = IsAlias ? cast<TypeAliasDecl>(D) : nullptr;
2800  if (!FromAlias || !FromAlias->getDescribedAliasTemplate())
2801  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToTypedef);
2802 
2803  return ToTypedef;
2804 }
2805 
2806 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitTypedefDecl(TypedefDecl *D) {
2807  return VisitTypedefNameDecl(D, /*IsAlias=*/false);
2808 }
2809 
2810 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitTypeAliasDecl(TypeAliasDecl *D) {
2811  return VisitTypedefNameDecl(D, /*IsAlias=*/true);
2812 }
2813 
2814 ExpectedDecl
2815 ASTNodeImporter::VisitTypeAliasTemplateDecl(TypeAliasTemplateDecl *D) {
2816  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this typedef.
2817  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
2818  DeclarationName Name;
2819  SourceLocation Loc;
2820  NamedDecl *FoundD;
2821  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, FoundD, Loc))
2822  return std::move(Err);
2823  if (FoundD)
2824  return FoundD;
2825 
2826  // If this typedef is not in block scope, determine whether we've
2827  // seen a typedef with the same name (that we can merge with) or any
2828  // other entity by that name (which name lookup could conflict with).
2829  if (!DC->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
2830  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
2831  unsigned IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
2832  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
2833  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
2834  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(IDNS))
2835  continue;
2836  if (auto *FoundAlias = dyn_cast<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
2837  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundAlias))
2838  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundAlias);
2839  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
2840  }
2841  }
2842 
2843  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty()) {
2844  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
2845  Name, DC, IDNS, ConflictingDecls.data(), ConflictingDecls.size());
2846  if (NameOrErr)
2847  Name = NameOrErr.get();
2848  else
2849  return NameOrErr.takeError();
2850  }
2851  }
2852 
2853  Error Err = Error::success();
2854  auto ToTemplateParameters = importChecked(Err, D->getTemplateParameters());
2855  auto ToTemplatedDecl = importChecked(Err, D->getTemplatedDecl());
2856  if (Err)
2857  return std::move(Err);
2858 
2859  TypeAliasTemplateDecl *ToAlias;
2860  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToAlias, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, Loc,
2861  Name, ToTemplateParameters, ToTemplatedDecl))
2862  return ToAlias;
2863 
2864  ToTemplatedDecl->setDescribedAliasTemplate(ToAlias);
2865 
2866  ToAlias->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2867  ToAlias->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2868  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToAlias);
2869  if (DC != Importer.getToContext().getTranslationUnitDecl())
2870  updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(*ToTemplateParameters);
2871  return ToAlias;
2872 }
2873 
2874 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitLabelDecl(LabelDecl *D) {
2875  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this label.
2876  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
2877  DeclarationName Name;
2878  SourceLocation Loc;
2879  NamedDecl *ToD;
2880  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
2881  return std::move(Err);
2882  if (ToD)
2883  return ToD;
2884 
2885  assert(LexicalDC->isFunctionOrMethod());
2886 
2887  LabelDecl *ToLabel;
2888  if (D->isGnuLocal()) {
2889  ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = import(D->getBeginLoc());
2890  if (!BeginLocOrErr)
2891  return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
2892  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToLabel, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, Loc,
2893  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(), *BeginLocOrErr))
2894  return ToLabel;
2895 
2896  } else {
2897  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToLabel, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, Loc,
2898  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo()))
2899  return ToLabel;
2900 
2901  }
2902 
2903  Expected<LabelStmt *> ToStmtOrErr = import(D->getStmt());
2904  if (!ToStmtOrErr)
2905  return ToStmtOrErr.takeError();
2906 
2907  ToLabel->setStmt(*ToStmtOrErr);
2908  ToLabel->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2909  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToLabel);
2910  return ToLabel;
2911 }

2913 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitEnumDecl(EnumDecl *D) {
2914  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this enum.
2915  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
2916  DeclarationName Name;
2917  SourceLocation Loc;
2918  NamedDecl *ToD;
2919  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
2920  return std::move(Err);
2921  if (ToD)
2922  return ToD;
2923 
2924  // Figure out what enum name we're looking for.
2925  unsigned IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Tag;
2926  DeclarationName SearchName = Name;
2927  if (!SearchName && D->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl()) {
2928  if (Error Err = importInto(
2929  SearchName, D->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl()->getDeclName()))
2930  return std::move(Err);
2931  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
2932  } else if (Importer.getToContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
2933  IDNS |= Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
2934 
2935  // We may already have an enum of the same name; try to find and match it.
2936  EnumDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
2937  if (!DC->isFunctionOrMethod() && SearchName) {
2938  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
2939  auto FoundDecls =
2940  Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, SearchName);
2941  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
2942  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(IDNS))
2943  continue;
2944 
2945  if (auto *Typedef = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
2946  if (const auto *Tag = Typedef->getUnderlyingType()->getAs<TagType>())
2947  FoundDecl = Tag->getDecl();
2948  }
2949 
2950  if (auto *FoundEnum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
2951  if (!hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(FoundEnum, D))
2952  continue;
2953  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundEnum)) {
2954  EnumDecl *FoundDef = FoundEnum->getDefinition();
2955  if (D->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && FoundDef)
2956  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundDef);
2957  PrevDecl = FoundEnum->getMostRecentDecl();
2958  break;
2959  }
2960  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
2961  }
2962  }
2963 
2964  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty()) {
2965  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
2966  SearchName, DC, IDNS, ConflictingDecls.data(),
2967  ConflictingDecls.size());
2968  if (NameOrErr)
2969  Name = NameOrErr.get();
2970  else
2971  return NameOrErr.takeError();
2972  }
2973  }
2974 
2975  Error Err = Error::success();
2976  auto ToBeginLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getBeginLoc());
2977  auto ToQualifierLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getQualifierLoc());
2978  auto ToIntegerType = importChecked(Err, D->getIntegerType());
2979  auto ToBraceRange = importChecked(Err, D->getBraceRange());
2980  if (Err)
2981  return std::move(Err);
2982 
2983  // Create the enum declaration.
2984  EnumDecl *D2;
2985  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
2986  D2, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, ToBeginLoc,
2987  Loc, Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(), PrevDecl, D->isScoped(),
2988  D->isScopedUsingClassTag(), D->isFixed()))
2989  return D2;
2990 
2991  D2->setQualifierInfo(ToQualifierLoc);
2992  D2->setIntegerType(ToIntegerType);
2993  D2->setBraceRange(ToBraceRange);
2994  D2->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2995  D2->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2996  addDeclToContexts(D, D2);
2997 
2998  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MemberInfo = D->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
2999  TemplateSpecializationKind SK = MemberInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
3000  EnumDecl *FromInst = D->getInstantiatedFromMemberEnum();
3001  if (Expected<EnumDecl *> ToInstOrErr = import(FromInst))
3002  D2->setInstantiationOfMemberEnum(*ToInstOrErr, SK);
3003  else
3004  return ToInstOrErr.takeError();
3005  if (ExpectedSLoc POIOrErr = import(MemberInfo->getPointOfInstantiation()))
3006  D2->getMemberSpecializationInfo()->setPointOfInstantiation(*POIOrErr);
3007  else
3008  return POIOrErr.takeError();
3009  }
3010 
3011  // Import the definition
3012  if (D->isCompleteDefinition())
3013  if (Error Err = ImportDefinition(D, D2))
3014  return std::move(Err);
3015 
3016  return D2;
3017 }
3018 
3019 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitRecordDecl(RecordDecl *D) {
3020  bool IsFriendTemplate = false;
3021  if (auto *DCXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
3022  IsFriendTemplate =
3023  DCXX->getDescribedClassTemplate() &&
3024  DCXX->getDescribedClassTemplate()->getFriendObjectKind() !=
3025  Decl::FOK_None;
3026  }
3027 
3028  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this record.
3029  DeclContext *DC = nullptr, *LexicalDC = nullptr;
3030  DeclarationName Name;
3031  SourceLocation Loc;
3032  NamedDecl *ToD = nullptr;
3033  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
3034  return std::move(Err);
3035  if (ToD)
3036  return ToD;
3037 
3038  // Figure out what structure name we're looking for.
3039  unsigned IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Tag;
3040  DeclarationName SearchName = Name;
3041  if (!SearchName && D->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl()) {
3042  if (Error Err = importInto(
3043  SearchName, D->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl()->getDeclName()))
3044  return std::move(Err);
3045  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
3046  } else if (Importer.getToContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3047  IDNS |= Decl::IDNS_Ordinary | Decl::IDNS_TagFriend;
3048 
3049  bool IsDependentContext = DC != LexicalDC ? LexicalDC->isDependentContext()
3050  : DC->isDependentContext();
3051  bool DependentFriend = IsFriendTemplate && IsDependentContext;
3052 
3053  // We may already have a record of the same name; try to find and match it.
3054  RecordDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
3055  if (!DependentFriend && !DC->isFunctionOrMethod() && !D->isLambda()) {
3056  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
3057  auto FoundDecls =
3058  Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, SearchName);
3059  if (!FoundDecls.empty()) {
3060  // We're going to have to compare D against potentially conflicting Decls,
3061  // so complete it.
3062  if (D->hasExternalLexicalStorage() && !D->isCompleteDefinition())
3063  D->getASTContext().getExternalSource()->CompleteType(D);
3064  }
3065 
3066  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
3067  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(IDNS))
3068  continue;
3069 
3070  Decl *Found = FoundDecl;
3071  if (auto *Typedef = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(Found)) {
3072  if (const auto *Tag = Typedef->getUnderlyingType()->getAs<TagType>())
3073  Found = Tag->getDecl();
3074  }
3075 
3076  if (auto *FoundRecord = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(Found)) {
3077  // Do not emit false positive diagnostic in case of unnamed
3078  // struct/union and in case of anonymous structs. Would be false
3079  // because there may be several anonymous/unnamed structs in a class.
3080  // E.g. these are both valid:
3081  // struct A { // unnamed structs
3082  // struct { struct A *next; } entry0;
3083  // struct { struct A *next; } entry1;
3084  // };
3085  // struct X { struct { int a; }; struct { int b; }; }; // anon structs
3086  if (!SearchName)
3087  if (!IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundRecord, false))
3088  continue;
3089 
3090  if (!hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(FoundRecord, D))
3091  continue;
3092 
3093  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundRecord)) {
3094  RecordDecl *FoundDef = FoundRecord->getDefinition();
3095  if (D->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && FoundDef) {
3096  // FIXME: Structural equivalence check should check for same
3097  // user-defined methods.
3098  Importer.MapImported(D, FoundDef);
3099  if (const auto *DCXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
3100  auto *FoundCXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(FoundDef);
3101  assert(FoundCXX && "Record type mismatch");
3102 
3103  if (!Importer.isMinimalImport())
3104  // FoundDef may not have every implicit method that D has
3105  // because implicit methods are created only if they are used.
3106  if (Error Err = ImportImplicitMethods(DCXX, FoundCXX))
3107  return std::move(Err);
3108  }
3109  }
3110  PrevDecl = FoundRecord->getMostRecentDecl();
3111  break;
3112  }
3113  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
3114  } // kind is RecordDecl
3115  } // for
3116 
3117  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty() && SearchName) {
3118  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
3119  SearchName, DC, IDNS, ConflictingDecls.data(),
3120  ConflictingDecls.size());
3121  if (NameOrErr)
3122  Name = NameOrErr.get();
3123  else
3124  return NameOrErr.takeError();
3125  }
3126  }
3127 
3128  ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = import(D->getBeginLoc());
3129  if (!BeginLocOrErr)
3130  return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
3131 
3132  // Create the record declaration.
3133  RecordDecl *D2 = nullptr;
3134  CXXRecordDecl *D2CXX = nullptr;
3135  if (auto *DCXX = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
3136  if (DCXX->isLambda()) {
3137  auto TInfoOrErr = import(DCXX->getLambdaTypeInfo());
3138  if (!TInfoOrErr)
3139  return TInfoOrErr.takeError();
3140  if (GetImportedOrCreateSpecialDecl(
3141  D2CXX, CXXRecordDecl::CreateLambda, D, Importer.getToContext(),
3142  DC, *TInfoOrErr, Loc, DCXX->getLambdaDependencyKind(),
3143  DCXX->isGenericLambda(), DCXX->getLambdaCaptureDefault()))
3144  return D2CXX;
3145  CXXRecordDecl::LambdaNumbering Numbering = DCXX->getLambdaNumbering();
3146  ExpectedDecl CDeclOrErr = import(Numbering.ContextDecl);
3147  if (!CDeclOrErr)
3148  return CDeclOrErr.takeError();
3149  Numbering.ContextDecl = *CDeclOrErr;
3150  D2CXX->setLambdaNumbering(Numbering);
3151  } else if (DCXX->isInjectedClassName()) {
3152  // We have to be careful to do a similar dance to the one in
3153  // Sema::ActOnStartCXXMemberDeclarations
3154  const bool DelayTypeCreation = true;
3155  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
3156  D2CXX, D, Importer.getToContext(), D->getTagKind(), DC,
3157  *BeginLocOrErr, Loc, Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(),
3158  cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(PrevDecl), DelayTypeCreation))
3159  return D2CXX;
3160  Importer.getToContext().getTypeDeclType(
3161  D2CXX, dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC));
3162  } else {
3163  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(D2CXX, D, Importer.getToContext(),
3164  D->getTagKind(), DC, *BeginLocOrErr, Loc,
3165  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(),
3166  cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(PrevDecl)))
3167  return D2CXX;
3168  }
3169 
3170  D2 = D2CXX;
3171  D2->setAccess(D->getAccess());
3172  D2->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
3173  addDeclToContexts(D, D2);
3174 
3175  if (ClassTemplateDecl *FromDescribed =
3176  DCXX->getDescribedClassTemplate()) {
3177  ClassTemplateDecl *ToDescribed;
3178  if (Error Err = importInto(ToDescribed, FromDescribed))
3179  return std::move(Err);
3180  D2CXX->setDescribedClassTemplate(ToDescribed);
3181  if (!DCXX->isInjectedClassName() && !IsFriendTemplate) {
3182  // In a record describing a template the type should be an
3183  // InjectedClassNameType (see Sema::CheckClassTemplate). Update the
3184  // previously set type to the correct value here (ToDescribed is not
3185  // available at record create).
3186  CXXRecordDecl *Injected = nullptr;
3187  for (NamedDecl *Found : D2CXX->noload_lookup(Name)) {
3188  auto *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Found);
3189  if (Record && Record->isInjectedClassName()) {
3190  Injected = Record;
3191  break;
3192  }
3193  }
3194  // Create an injected type for the whole redecl chain.
3195  // The chain may contain an already existing injected type at the start,
3196  // if yes this should be reused. We must ensure that only one type
3197  // object exists for the injected type (including the injected record
3198  // declaration), ASTContext does not check it.
3199  SmallVector<Decl *, 2> Redecls =
3200  getCanonicalForwardRedeclChain(D2CXX);
3201  const Type *FrontTy =
3202  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Redecls.front())->getTypeForDecl();
3203  QualType InjSpec;
3204  if (auto *InjTy = FrontTy->getAs<InjectedClassNameType>())
3205  InjSpec = InjTy->getInjectedSpecializationType();
3206  else
3207  InjSpec = ToDescribed->getInjectedClassNameSpecialization();
3208  for (auto *R : Redecls) {
3209  auto *RI = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(R);
3210  if (R != Redecls.front() ||
3211  !isa<InjectedClassNameType>(RI->getTypeForDecl()))
3212  RI->setTypeForDecl(nullptr);
3213  // This function tries to get the injected type from getTypeForDecl,
3214  // then from the previous declaration if possible. If not, it creates
3215  // a new type.
3216  Importer.getToContext().getInjectedClassNameType(RI, InjSpec);
3217  }
3218  // Set the new type for the injected decl too.
3219  if (Injected) {
3220  Injected->setTypeForDecl(nullptr);
3221  // This function will copy the injected type from D2CXX into Injected.
3222  // The injected decl does not have a previous decl to copy from.
3223  Importer.getToContext().getTypeDeclType(Injected, D2CXX);
3224  }
3225  }
3226  } else if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MemberInfo =
3227  DCXX->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
3228  TemplateSpecializationKind SK =
3229  MemberInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
3230  CXXRecordDecl *FromInst = DCXX->getInstantiatedFromMemberClass();
3231 
3232  if (Expected<CXXRecordDecl *> ToInstOrErr = import(FromInst))
3233  D2CXX->setInstantiationOfMemberClass(*ToInstOrErr, SK);
3234  else
3235  return ToInstOrErr.takeError();
3236 
3237  if (ExpectedSLoc POIOrErr =
3238  import(MemberInfo->getPointOfInstantiation()))
3239  D2CXX->getMemberSpecializationInfo()->setPointOfInstantiation(
3240  *POIOrErr);
3241  else
3242  return POIOrErr.takeError();
3243  }
3244 
3245  } else {
3246  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(D2, D, Importer.getToContext(),
3247  D->getTagKind(), DC, *BeginLocOrErr, Loc,
3248  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(), PrevDecl))
3249  return D2;
3250  D2->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
3251  addDeclToContexts(D, D2);
3252  }
3253 
3254  if (auto BraceRangeOrErr = import(D->getBraceRange()))
3255  D2->setBraceRange(*BraceRangeOrErr);
3256  else
3257  return BraceRangeOrErr.takeError();
3258  if (auto QualifierLocOrErr = import(D->getQualifierLoc()))
3259  D2->setQualifierInfo(*QualifierLocOrErr);
3260  else
3261  return QualifierLocOrErr.takeError();
3262 
3263  if (D->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
3264  D2->setAnonymousStructOrUnion(true);
3265 
3266  if (D->isCompleteDefinition())
3267  if (Error Err = ImportDefinition(D, D2, IDK_Default))
3268  return std::move(Err);
3269 
3270  return D2;
3271 }

3273 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitEnumConstantDecl(EnumConstantDecl *D) {
3274  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this enumerator.
3275  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
3276  DeclarationName Name;
3277  SourceLocation Loc;
3278  NamedDecl *ToD;
3279  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
3280  return std::move(Err);
3281  if (ToD)
3282  return ToD;
3283 
3284  // Determine whether there are any other declarations with the same name and
3285  // in the same context.
3286  if (!LexicalDC->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
3287  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
3288  unsigned IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
3289  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
3290  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
3291  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(IDNS))
3292  continue;
3293 
3294  if (auto *FoundEnumConstant = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
3295  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundEnumConstant))
3296  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundEnumConstant);
3297  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
3298  }
3299  }
3300 
3301  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty()) {
3302  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
3303  Name, DC, IDNS, ConflictingDecls.data(), ConflictingDecls.size());
3304  if (NameOrErr)
3305  Name = NameOrErr.get();
3306  else
3307  return NameOrErr.takeError();
3308  }
3309  }
3310 
3311  ExpectedType TypeOrErr = import(D->getType());
3312  if (!TypeOrErr)
3313  return TypeOrErr.takeError();
3314 
3315  ExpectedExpr InitOrErr = import(D->getInitExpr());
3316  if (!InitOrErr)
3317  return InitOrErr.takeError();
3318 
3319  EnumConstantDecl *ToEnumerator;
3320  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
3321  ToEnumerator, D, Importer.getToContext(), cast<EnumDecl>(DC), Loc,
3322  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(), *TypeOrErr, *InitOrErr, D->getInitVal()))
3323  return ToEnumerator;
3324 
3325  ToEnumerator->setAccess(D->getAccess());
3326  ToEnumerator->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
3327  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToEnumerator);
3328  return ToEnumerator;
3329 }
