5416 
5417 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportDefinition(
5418  ObjCInterfaceDecl *From, ObjCInterfaceDecl *To, ImportDefinitionKind Kind) {
5419  if (To->getDefinition()) {
5420  // Check consistency of superclass.
5421  ObjCInterfaceDecl *FromSuper = From->getSuperClass();
5422  if (FromSuper) {
5423  if (auto FromSuperOrErr = import(FromSuper))
5424  FromSuper = *FromSuperOrErr;
5425  else
5426  return FromSuperOrErr.takeError();
5427  }
5428 
5429  ObjCInterfaceDecl *ToSuper = To->getSuperClass();
5430  if ((bool)FromSuper != (bool)ToSuper ||
5431  (FromSuper && !declaresSameEntity(FromSuper, ToSuper))) {
5432  Importer.ToDiag(To->getLocation(),
5433  diag::warn_odr_objc_superclass_inconsistent)
5434  << To->getDeclName();
5435  if (ToSuper)
5436  Importer.ToDiag(To->getSuperClassLoc(), diag::note_odr_objc_superclass)
5437  << To->getSuperClass()->getDeclName();
5438  else
5439  Importer.ToDiag(To->getLocation(),
5440  diag::note_odr_objc_missing_superclass);
5441  if (From->getSuperClass())
5442  Importer.FromDiag(From->getSuperClassLoc(),
5443  diag::note_odr_objc_superclass)
5444  << From->getSuperClass()->getDeclName();
5445  else
5446  Importer.FromDiag(From->getLocation(),
5447  diag::note_odr_objc_missing_superclass);
5448  }
5449 
5450  if (shouldForceImportDeclContext(Kind))
5451  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(From))
5452  return Err;
5453  return Error::success();
5454  }
5455 
5456  // Start the definition.
5457  To->startDefinition();
5458 
5459  // If this class has a superclass, import it.
5460  if (From->getSuperClass()) {
5461  if (auto SuperTInfoOrErr = import(From->getSuperClassTInfo()))
5462  To->setSuperClass(*SuperTInfoOrErr);
5463  else
5464  return SuperTInfoOrErr.takeError();
5465  }
5466 
5467  // Import protocols
5468  SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 4> Protocols;
5469  SmallVector<SourceLocation, 4> ProtocolLocs;
5470  ObjCInterfaceDecl::protocol_loc_iterator FromProtoLoc =
5471  From->protocol_loc_begin();
5472 
5473  for (ObjCInterfaceDecl::protocol_iterator FromProto = From->protocol_begin(),
5474  FromProtoEnd = From->protocol_end();
5475  FromProto != FromProtoEnd;
5476  ++FromProto, ++FromProtoLoc) {
5477  if (Expected<ObjCProtocolDecl *> ToProtoOrErr = import(*FromProto))
5478  Protocols.push_back(*ToProtoOrErr);
5479  else
5480  return ToProtoOrErr.takeError();
5481 
5482  if (ExpectedSLoc ToProtoLocOrErr = import(*FromProtoLoc))
5483  ProtocolLocs.push_back(*ToProtoLocOrErr);
5484  else
5485  return ToProtoLocOrErr.takeError();
5486 
5487  }
5488 
5489  // FIXME: If we're merging, make sure that the protocol list is the same.
5490  To->setProtocolList(Protocols.data(), Protocols.size(),
5491  ProtocolLocs.data(), Importer.getToContext());
5492 
5493  // Import categories. When the categories themselves are imported, they'll
5494  // hook themselves into this interface.
5495  for (auto *Cat : From->known_categories()) {
5496  auto ToCatOrErr = import(Cat);
5497  if (!ToCatOrErr)
5498  return ToCatOrErr.takeError();
5499  }
5500 
5501  // If we have an @implementation, import it as well.
5502  if (From->getImplementation()) {
5503  if (Expected<ObjCImplementationDecl *> ToImplOrErr =
5504  import(From->getImplementation()))
5505  To->setImplementation(*ToImplOrErr);
5506  else
5507  return ToImplOrErr.takeError();
5508  }
5509 
5510  // Import all of the members of this class.
5511  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(From, /*ForceImport=*/true))
5512  return Err;
5513 
5514  return Error::success();
5515 }
5516 
5517 Expected<ObjCTypeParamList *>
5518 ASTNodeImporter::ImportObjCTypeParamList(ObjCTypeParamList *list) {
5519  if (!list)
5520  return nullptr;
5521 
5522  SmallVector<ObjCTypeParamDecl *, 4> toTypeParams;
5523  for (auto *fromTypeParam : *list) {
5524  if (auto toTypeParamOrErr = import(fromTypeParam))
5525  toTypeParams.push_back(*toTypeParamOrErr);
5526  else
5527  return toTypeParamOrErr.takeError();
5528  }
5529 
5530  auto LAngleLocOrErr = import(list->getLAngleLoc());
5531  if (!LAngleLocOrErr)
5532  return LAngleLocOrErr.takeError();
5533 
5534  auto RAngleLocOrErr = import(list->getRAngleLoc());
5535  if (!RAngleLocOrErr)
5536  return RAngleLocOrErr.takeError();
5537 
5538  return ObjCTypeParamList::create(Importer.getToContext(),
5539  *LAngleLocOrErr,
5540  toTypeParams,
5541  *RAngleLocOrErr);
5542 }
5543 
5544 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitObjCInterfaceDecl(ObjCInterfaceDecl *D) {
5545  // If this class has a definition in the translation unit we're coming from,
5546  // but this particular declaration is not that definition, import the
5547  // definition and map to that.
5548  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Definition = D->getDefinition();
5549  if (Definition && Definition != D) {
5550  if (ExpectedDecl ImportedDefOrErr = import(Definition))
5551  return Importer.MapImported(D, *ImportedDefOrErr);
5552  else
5553  return ImportedDefOrErr.takeError();
5554  }
5555 
5556  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of an @interface.
5557  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
5558  DeclarationName Name;
5559  SourceLocation Loc;
5560  NamedDecl *ToD;
5561  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
5562  return std::move(Err);
5563  if (ToD)
5564  return ToD;
5565 
5566  // Look for an existing interface with the same name.
5567  ObjCInterfaceDecl *MergeWithIface = nullptr;
5568  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
5569  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
5570  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(Decl::IDNS_Ordinary))
5571  continue;
5572 
5573  if ((MergeWithIface = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(FoundDecl)))
5574  break;
5575  }
5576 
5577  // Create an interface declaration, if one does not already exist.
5578  ObjCInterfaceDecl *ToIface = MergeWithIface;
5579  if (!ToIface) {
5580  ExpectedSLoc AtBeginLocOrErr = import(D->getAtStartLoc());
5581  if (!AtBeginLocOrErr)
5582  return AtBeginLocOrErr.takeError();
5583 
5584  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
5585  ToIface, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC,
5586  *AtBeginLocOrErr, Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(),
5587  /*TypeParamList=*/nullptr,
5588  /*PrevDecl=*/nullptr, Loc, D->isImplicitInterfaceDecl()))
5589  return ToIface;
5590  ToIface->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
5591  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToIface);
5592  }
5593  Importer.MapImported(D, ToIface);
5594  // Import the type parameter list after MapImported, to avoid
5595  // loops when bringing in their DeclContext.
5596  if (auto ToPListOrErr =
5597  ImportObjCTypeParamList(D->getTypeParamListAsWritten()))
5598  ToIface->setTypeParamList(*ToPListOrErr);
5599  else
5600  return ToPListOrErr.takeError();
5601 
5602  if (D->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
5603  if (Error Err = ImportDefinition(D, ToIface))
5604  return std::move(Err);
5605 
5606  return ToIface;
5607 }
5608 
5609 ExpectedDecl
5610 ASTNodeImporter::VisitObjCCategoryImplDecl(ObjCCategoryImplDecl *D) {
5611  ObjCCategoryDecl *Category;
5612  if (Error Err = importInto(Category, D->getCategoryDecl()))
5613  return std::move(Err);
5614 
5615  ObjCCategoryImplDecl *ToImpl = Category->getImplementation();
5616  if (!ToImpl) {
5617  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
5618  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D, DC, LexicalDC))
5619  return std::move(Err);
5620 
5621  Error Err = Error::success();
5622  auto ToLocation = importChecked(Err, D->getLocation());
5623  auto ToAtStartLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getAtStartLoc());
5624  auto ToCategoryNameLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getCategoryNameLoc());
5625  if (Err)
5626  return std::move(Err);
5627 
5628  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
5629  ToImpl, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC,
5630  Importer.Import(D->getIdentifier()), Category->getClassInterface(),
5631  ToLocation, ToAtStartLoc, ToCategoryNameLoc))
5632  return ToImpl;
5633 
5634  ToImpl->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
5635  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToImpl);
5636  Category->setImplementation(ToImpl);
5637  }
5638 
5639  Importer.MapImported(D, ToImpl);
5640  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D))
5641  return std::move(Err);
5642 
5643  return ToImpl;
5644 }
5645 
5646 ExpectedDecl
5647 ASTNodeImporter::VisitObjCImplementationDecl(ObjCImplementationDecl *D) {
5648  // Find the corresponding interface.
5649  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Iface;
5650  if (Error Err = importInto(Iface, D->getClassInterface()))
5651  return std::move(Err);
5652 
5653  // Import the superclass, if any.
5654  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super;
5655  if (Error Err = importInto(Super, D->getSuperClass()))
5656  return std::move(Err);
5657 
5658  ObjCImplementationDecl *Impl = Iface->getImplementation();
5659  if (!Impl) {
5660  // We haven't imported an implementation yet. Create a new @implementation
5661  // now.
5662  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
5663  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D, DC, LexicalDC))
5664  return std::move(Err);
5665 
5666  Error Err = Error::success();
5667  auto ToLocation = importChecked(Err, D->getLocation());
5668  auto ToAtStartLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getAtStartLoc());
5669  auto ToSuperClassLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getSuperClassLoc());
5670  auto ToIvarLBraceLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getIvarLBraceLoc());
5671  auto ToIvarRBraceLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getIvarRBraceLoc());
5672  if (Err)
5673  return std::move(Err);
5674 
5675  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(Impl, D, Importer.getToContext(),
5676  DC, Iface, Super,
5677  ToLocation,
5678  ToAtStartLoc,
5679  ToSuperClassLoc,
5680  ToIvarLBraceLoc,
5681  ToIvarRBraceLoc))
5682  return Impl;
5683 
5684  Impl->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
5685 
5686  // Associate the implementation with the class it implements.
5687  Iface->setImplementation(Impl);
5688  Importer.MapImported(D, Iface->getImplementation());
5689  } else {
5690  Importer.MapImported(D, Iface->getImplementation());
5691 
5692  // Verify that the existing @implementation has the same superclass.
5693  if ((Super && !Impl->getSuperClass()) ||
5694  (!Super && Impl->getSuperClass()) ||
5695  (Super && Impl->getSuperClass() &&
5696  !declaresSameEntity(Super->getCanonicalDecl(),
5697  Impl->getSuperClass()))) {
5698  Importer.ToDiag(Impl->getLocation(),
5699  diag::warn_odr_objc_superclass_inconsistent)
5700  << Iface->getDeclName();
5701  // FIXME: It would be nice to have the location of the superclass
5702  // below.
5703  if (Impl->getSuperClass())
5704  Importer.ToDiag(Impl->getLocation(),
5705  diag::note_odr_objc_superclass)
5706  << Impl->getSuperClass()->getDeclName();
5707  else
5708  Importer.ToDiag(Impl->getLocation(),
5709  diag::note_odr_objc_missing_superclass);
5710  if (D->getSuperClass())
5711  Importer.FromDiag(D->getLocation(),
5712  diag::note_odr_objc_superclass)
5713  << D->getSuperClass()->getDeclName();
5714  else
5715  Importer.FromDiag(D->getLocation(),
5716  diag::note_odr_objc_missing_superclass);
5717 
5718  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::NameConflict);
5719  }
5720  }
5721 
5722  // Import all of the members of this @implementation.
5723  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D))
5724  return std::move(Err);
5725 
5726  return Impl;
5727 }
5728 
5729 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitObjCPropertyDecl(ObjCPropertyDecl *D) {
5730  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of an @property.
5731  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
5732  DeclarationName Name;
5733  SourceLocation Loc;
5734  NamedDecl *ToD;
5735  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
5736  return std::move(Err);
5737  if (ToD)
5738  return ToD;
5739 
5740  // Check whether we have already imported this property.
5741  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
5742  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
5743  if (auto *FoundProp = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
5744  // Instance and class properties can share the same name but are different
5745  // declarations.
5746  if (FoundProp->isInstanceProperty() != D->isInstanceProperty())
5747  continue;
5748 
5749  // Check property types.
5750  if (!Importer.IsStructurallyEquivalent(D->getType(),
5751  FoundProp->getType())) {
5752  Importer.ToDiag(Loc, diag::warn_odr_objc_property_type_inconsistent)
5753  << Name << D->getType() << FoundProp->getType();
5754  Importer.ToDiag(FoundProp->getLocation(), diag::note_odr_value_here)
5755  << FoundProp->getType();
5756 
5757  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::NameConflict);
5758  }
5759 
5760  // FIXME: Check property attributes, getters, setters, etc.?
5761 
5762  // Consider these properties to be equivalent.
5763  Importer.MapImported(D, FoundProp);
5764  return FoundProp;
5765  }
5766  }
5767 
5768  Error Err = Error::success();
5769  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, D->getType());
5770  auto ToTypeSourceInfo = importChecked(Err, D->getTypeSourceInfo());
5771  auto ToAtLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getAtLoc());
5772  auto ToLParenLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getLParenLoc());
5773  if (Err)
5774  return std::move(Err);
5775 
5776  // Create the new property.
5777  ObjCPropertyDecl *ToProperty;
5778  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
5779  ToProperty, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, Loc,
5780  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(), ToAtLoc,
5781  ToLParenLoc, ToType,
5782  ToTypeSourceInfo, D->getPropertyImplementation()))
5783  return ToProperty;
5784 
5785  auto ToGetterName = importChecked(Err, D->getGetterName());
5786  auto ToSetterName = importChecked(Err, D->getSetterName());
5787  auto ToGetterNameLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getGetterNameLoc());
5788  auto ToSetterNameLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getSetterNameLoc());
5789  auto ToGetterMethodDecl = importChecked(Err, D->getGetterMethodDecl());
5790  auto ToSetterMethodDecl = importChecked(Err, D->getSetterMethodDecl());
5791  auto ToPropertyIvarDecl = importChecked(Err, D->getPropertyIvarDecl());
5792  if (Err)
5793  return std::move(Err);
5794 
5795  ToProperty->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
5796  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToProperty);
5797 
5798  ToProperty->setPropertyAttributes(D->getPropertyAttributes());
5799  ToProperty->setPropertyAttributesAsWritten(
5800  D->getPropertyAttributesAsWritten());
5801  ToProperty->setGetterName(ToGetterName, ToGetterNameLoc);
5802  ToProperty->setSetterName(ToSetterName, ToSetterNameLoc);
5803  ToProperty->setGetterMethodDecl(ToGetterMethodDecl);
5804  ToProperty->setSetterMethodDecl(ToSetterMethodDecl);
5805  ToProperty->setPropertyIvarDecl(ToPropertyIvarDecl);
5806  return ToProperty;
5807 }
5808 
5809 ExpectedDecl
5810 ASTNodeImporter::VisitObjCPropertyImplDecl(ObjCPropertyImplDecl *D) {
5811  ObjCPropertyDecl *Property;
5812  if (Error Err = importInto(Property, D->getPropertyDecl()))
5813  return std::move(Err);
5814 
5815  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
5816  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D, DC, LexicalDC))
5817  return std::move(Err);
5818 
5819  auto *InImpl = cast<ObjCImplDecl>(LexicalDC);
5820 
5821  // Import the ivar (for an @synthesize).
5822  ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar = nullptr;
5823  if (Error Err = importInto(Ivar, D->getPropertyIvarDecl()))
5824  return std::move(Err);
5825 
5826  ObjCPropertyImplDecl *ToImpl
5827  = InImpl->FindPropertyImplDecl(Property->getIdentifier(),
5828  Property->getQueryKind());
5829  if (!ToImpl) {
5830 
5831  Error Err = Error::success();
5832  auto ToBeginLoc = importChecked(Err, D->getBeginLoc());
5833  auto ToLocation = importChecked(Err, D->getLocation());
5834  auto ToPropertyIvarDeclLoc =
5835  importChecked(Err, D->getPropertyIvarDeclLoc());
5836  if (Err)
5837  return std::move(Err);
5838 
5839  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToImpl, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC,
5840  ToBeginLoc,
5841  ToLocation, Property,
5842  D->getPropertyImplementation(), Ivar,
5843  ToPropertyIvarDeclLoc))
5844  return ToImpl;
5845 
5846  ToImpl->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
5847  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToImpl);
5848  } else {
5849  // Check that we have the same kind of property implementation (@synthesize
5850  // vs. @dynamic).
5851  if (D->getPropertyImplementation() != ToImpl->getPropertyImplementation()) {
5852  Importer.ToDiag(ToImpl->getLocation(),
5853  diag::warn_odr_objc_property_impl_kind_inconsistent)
5854  << Property->getDeclName()
5855  << (ToImpl->getPropertyImplementation()
5856  == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Dynamic);
5857  Importer.FromDiag(D->getLocation(),
5858  diag::note_odr_objc_property_impl_kind)
5859  << D->getPropertyDecl()->getDeclName()
5860  << (D->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Dynamic);
5861 
5862  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::NameConflict);
5863  }
5864 
5865  // For @synthesize, check that we have the same
5866  if (D->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Synthesize &&
5867  Ivar != ToImpl->getPropertyIvarDecl()) {
5868  Importer.ToDiag(ToImpl->getPropertyIvarDeclLoc(),
5869  diag::warn_odr_objc_synthesize_ivar_inconsistent)
5870  << Property->getDeclName()
5871  << ToImpl->getPropertyIvarDecl()->getDeclName()
5872  << Ivar->getDeclName();
5873  Importer.FromDiag(D->getPropertyIvarDeclLoc(),
5874  diag::note_odr_objc_synthesize_ivar_here)
5875  << D->getPropertyIvarDecl()->getDeclName();
5876 
5877  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::NameConflict);
5878  }
5879 
5880  // Merge the existing implementation with the new implementation.
5881  Importer.MapImported(D, ToImpl);
5882  }
5883 
5884  return ToImpl;
5885 }

5888 ASTNodeImporter::VisitTemplateTypeParmDecl(TemplateTypeParmDecl *D) {
5889  // For template arguments, we adopt the translation unit as our declaration
5890  // context. This context will be fixed when the actual template declaration
5891  // is created.
5892 
5893  ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = import(D->getBeginLoc());
5894  if (!BeginLocOrErr)
5895  return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
5896 
5897  ExpectedSLoc LocationOrErr = import(D->getLocation());
5898  if (!LocationOrErr)
5899  return LocationOrErr.takeError();
5900

5902  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
5903  ToD, D, Importer.getToContext(),
5904  Importer.getToContext().getTranslationUnitDecl(),
5905  *BeginLocOrErr, *LocationOrErr,
5906  D->getDepth(), D->getIndex(), Importer.Import(D->getIdentifier()),
5907  D->wasDeclaredWithTypename(), D->isParameterPack(),
5908  D->hasTypeConstraint()))
5909  return ToD;
5910 
5911  // Import the type-constraint
5912  if (const TypeConstraint *TC = D->getTypeConstraint()) {
5913 
5914  Error Err = Error::success();

5916  auto ToIDC = importChecked(Err, TC->getImmediatelyDeclaredConstraint());
5917  if (Err)
5918  return std::move(Err);
5919 
5920  ToD->setTypeConstraint(ToConceptRef, ToIDC);
5921  }
5922 
5923  if (D->hasDefaultArgument()) {
5924  Expected<TypeSourceInfo *> ToDefaultArgOrErr =
5925  import(D->getDefaultArgumentInfo());
5926  if (!ToDefaultArgOrErr)
5927  return ToDefaultArgOrErr.takeError();
5928  ToD->setDefaultArgument(*ToDefaultArgOrErr);
5929  }
5930 
5931  return ToD;
5932 }

6002 // Returns the definition for a (forward) declaration of a TemplateDecl, if
6003 // it has any definition in the redecl chain.
6004 template <typename T> static auto getTemplateDefinition(T *D) -> T * {
6005  assert(D->getTemplatedDecl() && "Should be called on templates only");
6006  auto *ToTemplatedDef = D->getTemplatedDecl()->getDefinition();
6007  if (!ToTemplatedDef)
6008  return nullptr;
6009  auto *TemplateWithDef = ToTemplatedDef->getDescribedTemplate();
6010  return cast_or_null<T>(TemplateWithDef);
6011 }
6012 
6013 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitClassTemplateDecl(ClassTemplateDecl *D) {
6014 
6015  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this class template.
6016  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
6017  DeclarationName Name;
6018  SourceLocation Loc;
6019  NamedDecl *ToD;
6020  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
6021  return std::move(Err);
6022  if (ToD)
6023  return ToD;
6024 
6025  // Should check if a declaration is friend in a dependent context.
6026  // Such templates are not linked together in a declaration chain.
6027  // The ASTImporter strategy is to map existing forward declarations to
6028  // imported ones only if strictly necessary, otherwise import these as new
6029  // forward declarations. In case of the "dependent friend" declarations, new
6030  // declarations are created, but not linked in a declaration chain.
6031  auto IsDependentFriend = [](ClassTemplateDecl *TD) {
6032  return TD->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None &&
6033  TD->getLexicalDeclContext()->isDependentContext();
6034  };
6035  bool DependentFriend = IsDependentFriend(D);
6036 
6037  ClassTemplateDecl *FoundByLookup = nullptr;
6038 
6039  // We may already have a template of the same name; try to find and match it.
6040  if (!DC->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
6041  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
6042  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
6043  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
6044  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(Decl::IDNS_Ordinary |
6045  Decl::IDNS_TagFriend))
6046  continue;
6047 
6048  Decl *Found = FoundDecl;
6049  auto *FoundTemplate = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(Found);
6050  if (FoundTemplate) {
6051  if (!hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(FoundTemplate, D))
6052  continue;
6053 
6054  // FIXME: sufficient conditon for 'IgnoreTemplateParmDepth'?
6055  bool IgnoreTemplateParmDepth =
6056  (FoundTemplate->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None) !=
6057  (D->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None);
6058  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundTemplate, /*Complain=*/true,
6059  IgnoreTemplateParmDepth)) {
6060  if (DependentFriend || IsDependentFriend(FoundTemplate))
6061  continue;
6062 
6063  ClassTemplateDecl *TemplateWithDef =
6064  getTemplateDefinition(FoundTemplate);
6065  if (D->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && TemplateWithDef)
6066  return Importer.MapImported(D, TemplateWithDef);
6067  if (!FoundByLookup)
6068  FoundByLookup = FoundTemplate;
6069  // Search in all matches because there may be multiple decl chains,
6070  // see ASTTests test ImportExistingFriendClassTemplateDef.
6071  continue;
6072  }
6073  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
6074  }
6075  }
6076 
6077  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty()) {
6078  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
6079  Name, DC, Decl::IDNS_Ordinary, ConflictingDecls.data(),
6080  ConflictingDecls.size());
6081  if (NameOrErr)
6082  Name = NameOrErr.get();
6083  else
6084  return NameOrErr.takeError();
6085  }
6086  }
6087 
6088  CXXRecordDecl *FromTemplated = D->getTemplatedDecl();
6089 
6090  auto TemplateParamsOrErr = import(D->getTemplateParameters());
6091  if (!TemplateParamsOrErr)
6092  return TemplateParamsOrErr.takeError();
6093 
6094  // Create the declaration that is being templated.
6095  CXXRecordDecl *ToTemplated;
6096  if (Error Err = importInto(ToTemplated, FromTemplated))
6097  return std::move(Err);
6098 
6099  // Create the class template declaration itself.
6100  ClassTemplateDecl *D2;
6101  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(D2, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, Loc, Name,
6102  *TemplateParamsOrErr, ToTemplated))
6103  return D2;
6104 
6105  ToTemplated->setDescribedClassTemplate(D2);
6106 
6107  D2->setAccess(D->getAccess());
6108  D2->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
6109 
6110  addDeclToContexts(D, D2);
6111  updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(**TemplateParamsOrErr);
6112 
6113  if (FoundByLookup) {
6114  auto *Recent =
6115  const_cast<ClassTemplateDecl *>(FoundByLookup->getMostRecentDecl());
6116 
6117  // It is possible that during the import of the class template definition
6118  // we start the import of a fwd friend decl of the very same class template
6119  // and we add the fwd friend decl to the lookup table. But the ToTemplated
6120  // had been created earlier and by that time the lookup could not find
6121  // anything existing, so it has no previous decl. Later, (still during the
6122  // import of the fwd friend decl) we start to import the definition again
6123  // and this time the lookup finds the previous fwd friend class template.
6124  // In this case we must set up the previous decl for the templated decl.
6125  if (!ToTemplated->getPreviousDecl()) {
6126  assert(FoundByLookup->getTemplatedDecl() &&
6127  "Found decl must have its templated decl set");
6128  CXXRecordDecl *PrevTemplated =
6129  FoundByLookup->getTemplatedDecl()->getMostRecentDecl();
6130  if (ToTemplated != PrevTemplated)
6131  ToTemplated->setPreviousDecl(PrevTemplated);
6132  }
6133 
6134  D2->setPreviousDecl(Recent);
6135  }
6136 
6137  return D2;
6138 }
6139 
6140 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitClassTemplateSpecializationDecl(
6141  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *D) {
6142  ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTemplate;
6143  if (Error Err = importInto(ClassTemplate, D->getSpecializedTemplate()))
6144  return std::move(Err);
6145 
6146  // Import the context of this declaration.
6147  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
6148  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D, DC, LexicalDC))
6149  return std::move(Err);
6150 
6151  // Import template arguments.
6152  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 2> TemplateArgs;
6153  if (Error Err =
6154  ImportTemplateArguments(D->getTemplateArgs().asArray(), TemplateArgs))
6155  return std::move(Err);
6156  // Try to find an existing specialization with these template arguments and
6157  // template parameter list.
6158  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
6159  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
6160  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *PartialSpec =
6161  dyn_cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(D);
6162 
6163  // Import template parameters.
6164  TemplateParameterList *ToTPList = nullptr;
6165 
6166  if (PartialSpec) {
6167  auto ToTPListOrErr = import(PartialSpec->getTemplateParameters());
6168  if (!ToTPListOrErr)
6169  return ToTPListOrErr.takeError();
6170  ToTPList = *ToTPListOrErr;
6171  PrevDecl = ClassTemplate->findPartialSpecialization(TemplateArgs,
6172  *ToTPListOrErr,
6173  InsertPos);
6174  } else
6175  PrevDecl = ClassTemplate->findSpecialization(TemplateArgs, InsertPos);
6176 
6177  if (PrevDecl) {
6178  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, PrevDecl)) {
6179  CXXRecordDecl *PrevDefinition = PrevDecl->getDefinition();
6180  if (D->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && PrevDefinition) {
6181  Importer.MapImported(D, PrevDefinition);
6182  // Import those default field initializers which have been
6183  // instantiated in the "From" context, but not in the "To" context.
6184  for (auto *FromField : D->fields()) {
6185  auto ToOrErr = import(FromField);
6186  if (!ToOrErr)
6187  return ToOrErr.takeError();
6188  }
6189 
6190  // Import those methods which have been instantiated in the
6191  // "From" context, but not in the "To" context.
6192  for (CXXMethodDecl *FromM : D->methods()) {
6193  auto ToOrErr = import(FromM);
6194  if (!ToOrErr)
6195  return ToOrErr.takeError();
6196  }
6197 
6198  // TODO Import instantiated default arguments.
6199  // TODO Import instantiated exception specifications.
6200  //
6201  // Generally, ASTCommon.h/DeclUpdateKind enum gives a very good hint
6202  // what else could be fused during an AST merge.
6203  return PrevDefinition;
6204  }
6205  } else { // ODR violation.
6206  // FIXME HandleNameConflict
6207  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::NameConflict);
6208  }
6209  }
6210 
6211  // Import the location of this declaration.
6212  ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = import(D->getBeginLoc());
6213  if (!BeginLocOrErr)
6214  return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
6215  ExpectedSLoc IdLocOrErr = import(D->getLocation());
6216  if (!IdLocOrErr)
6217  return IdLocOrErr.takeError();
6218 
6219  // Create the specialization.
6220  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *D2 = nullptr;
6221  if (PartialSpec) {
6222  // Import TemplateArgumentListInfo.
6223  TemplateArgumentListInfo ToTAInfo;
6224  const auto &ASTTemplateArgs = *PartialSpec->getTemplateArgsAsWritten();
6225  if (Error Err = ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(ASTTemplateArgs, ToTAInfo))
6226  return std::move(Err);
6227 
6228  QualType CanonInjType;
6229  if (Error Err = importInto(
6230  CanonInjType, PartialSpec->getInjectedSpecializationType()))
6231  return std::move(Err);
6232  CanonInjType = CanonInjType.getCanonicalType();
6233 
6234  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(
6235  D2, D, Importer.getToContext(), D->getTagKind(), DC, *BeginLocOrErr,
6236  *IdLocOrErr, ToTPList, ClassTemplate,
6237  llvm::ArrayRef(TemplateArgs.data(), TemplateArgs.size()), ToTAInfo,
6238  CanonInjType,
6239  cast_or_null<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(PrevDecl)))
6240  return D2;
6241 
6242  // Update InsertPos, because preceding import calls may have invalidated
6243  // it by adding new specializations.
6244  auto *PartSpec2 = cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(D2);
6245  if (!ClassTemplate->findPartialSpecialization(TemplateArgs, ToTPList,
6246  InsertPos))
6247  // Add this partial specialization to the class template.
6248  ClassTemplate->AddPartialSpecialization(PartSpec2, InsertPos);
6249  if (Expected<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *> ToInstOrErr =
6250  import(PartialSpec->getInstantiatedFromMember()))
6251  PartSpec2->setInstantiatedFromMember(*ToInstOrErr);
6252  else
6253  return ToInstOrErr.takeError();
6254 
6255  updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(*ToTPList);
6256  } else { // Not a partial specialization.
6257  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(
6258  D2, D, Importer.getToContext(), D->getTagKind(), DC,
6259  *BeginLocOrErr, *IdLocOrErr, ClassTemplate, TemplateArgs,
6260  PrevDecl))
6261  return D2;
6262 
6263  // Update InsertPos, because preceding import calls may have invalidated
6264  // it by adding new specializations.
6265  if (!ClassTemplate->findSpecialization(TemplateArgs, InsertPos))
6266  // Add this specialization to the class template.
6267  ClassTemplate->AddSpecialization(D2, InsertPos);
6268  }
6269 
6270  D2->setSpecializationKind(D->getSpecializationKind());
6271 
6272  // Set the context of this specialization/instantiation.
6273  D2->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
6274 
6275  // Add to the DC only if it was an explicit specialization/instantiation.
6276  if (D2->isExplicitInstantiationOrSpecialization()) {
6277  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(D2);
6278  }
6279 
6280  if (auto BraceRangeOrErr = import(D->getBraceRange()))
6281  D2->setBraceRange(*BraceRangeOrErr);
6282  else
6283  return BraceRangeOrErr.takeError();
6284 
6285  // Import the qualifier, if any.
6286  if (auto LocOrErr = import(D->getQualifierLoc()))
6287  D2->setQualifierInfo(*LocOrErr);
6288  else
6289  return LocOrErr.takeError();
6290 
6291  if (auto *TSI = D->getTypeAsWritten()) {
6292  if (auto TInfoOrErr = import(TSI))
6293  D2->setTypeAsWritten(*TInfoOrErr);
6294  else
6295  return TInfoOrErr.takeError();
6296 
6297  if (auto LocOrErr = import(D->getTemplateKeywordLoc()))
6298  D2->setTemplateKeywordLoc(*LocOrErr);
6299  else
6300  return LocOrErr.takeError();
6301 
6302  if (auto LocOrErr = import(D->getExternLoc()))
6303  D2->setExternLoc(*LocOrErr);
6304  else
6305  return LocOrErr.takeError();
6306  }
6307 
6308  if (D->getPointOfInstantiation().isValid()) {
6309  if (auto POIOrErr = import(D->getPointOfInstantiation()))
6310  D2->setPointOfInstantiation(*POIOrErr);
6311  else
6312  return POIOrErr.takeError();
6313  }
6314 
6315  D2->setTemplateSpecializationKind(D->getTemplateSpecializationKind());
6316 
6317  if (auto P = D->getInstantiatedFrom()) {
6318  if (auto *CTD = P.dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl *>()) {
6319  if (auto CTDorErr = import(CTD))
6320  D2->setInstantiationOf(*CTDorErr);
6321  } else {
6322  auto *CTPSD = cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>(P);
6323  auto CTPSDOrErr = import(CTPSD);
6324  if (!CTPSDOrErr)
6325  return CTPSDOrErr.takeError();
6326  const TemplateArgumentList &DArgs = D->getTemplateInstantiationArgs();
6327  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 2> D2ArgsVec(DArgs.size());
6328  for (unsigned I = 0; I < DArgs.size(); ++I) {
6329  const TemplateArgument &DArg = DArgs[I];
6330  if (auto ArgOrErr = import(DArg))
6331  D2ArgsVec[I] = *ArgOrErr;
6332  else
6333  return ArgOrErr.takeError();
6334  }
6335  D2->setInstantiationOf(
6336  *CTPSDOrErr,
6337  TemplateArgumentList::CreateCopy(Importer.getToContext(), D2ArgsVec));
6338  }
6339  }
6340 
6341  if (D->isCompleteDefinition())
6342  if (Error Err = ImportDefinition(D, D2))
6343  return std::move(Err);
6344 
6345  return D2;
6346 }
6347 
6348 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitVarTemplateDecl(VarTemplateDecl *D) {
6349  // Import the major distinguishing characteristics of this variable template.
6350  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
6351  DeclarationName Name;
6352  SourceLocation Loc;
6353  NamedDecl *ToD;
6354  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
6355  return std::move(Err);
6356  if (ToD)
6357  return ToD;
6358 
6359  // We may already have a template of the same name; try to find and match it.
6360  assert(!DC->isFunctionOrMethod() &&
6361  "Variable templates cannot be declared at function scope");
6362 
6363  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> ConflictingDecls;
6364  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
6365  VarTemplateDecl *FoundByLookup = nullptr;
6366  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
6367  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(Decl::IDNS_Ordinary))
6368  continue;
6369 
6370  if (VarTemplateDecl *FoundTemplate = dyn_cast<VarTemplateDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
6371  // Use the templated decl, some linkage flags are set only there.
6372  if (!hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(FoundTemplate->getTemplatedDecl(),
6373  D->getTemplatedDecl()))
6374  continue;
6375  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundTemplate)) {
6376  // FIXME Check for ODR error if the two definitions have
6377  // different initializers?
6378  VarTemplateDecl *FoundDef = getTemplateDefinition(FoundTemplate);
6379  if (D->getDeclContext()->isRecord()) {
6380  assert(FoundTemplate->getDeclContext()->isRecord() &&
6381  "Member variable template imported as non-member, "
6382  "inconsistent imported AST?");
6383  if (FoundDef)
6384  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundDef);
6385  if (!D->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
6386  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundTemplate);
6387  } else {
6388  if (FoundDef && D->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
6389  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundDef);
6390  }
6391  FoundByLookup = FoundTemplate;
6392  break;
6393  }
6394  ConflictingDecls.push_back(FoundDecl);
6395  }
6396  }
6397 
6398  if (!ConflictingDecls.empty()) {
6399  ExpectedName NameOrErr = Importer.HandleNameConflict(
6400  Name, DC, Decl::IDNS_Ordinary, ConflictingDecls.data(),
6401  ConflictingDecls.size());
6402  if (NameOrErr)
6403  Name = NameOrErr.get();
6404  else
6405  return NameOrErr.takeError();
6406  }
6407 
6408  VarDecl *DTemplated = D->getTemplatedDecl();
6409 
6410  // Import the type.
6411  // FIXME: Value not used?
6412  ExpectedType TypeOrErr = import(DTemplated->getType());
6413  if (!TypeOrErr)
6414  return TypeOrErr.takeError();
6415 
6416  // Create the declaration that is being templated.
6417  VarDecl *ToTemplated;
6418  if (Error Err = importInto(ToTemplated, DTemplated))
6419  return std::move(Err);
6420 
6421  // Create the variable template declaration itself.
6422  auto TemplateParamsOrErr = import(D->getTemplateParameters());
6423  if (!TemplateParamsOrErr)
6424  return TemplateParamsOrErr.takeError();
6425 
6426  VarTemplateDecl *ToVarTD;
6427  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToVarTD, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, Loc,
6428  Name, *TemplateParamsOrErr, ToTemplated))
6429  return ToVarTD;
6430 
6431  ToTemplated->setDescribedVarTemplate(ToVarTD);
6432 
6433  ToVarTD->setAccess(D->getAccess());
6434  ToVarTD->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
6435  LexicalDC->addDeclInternal(ToVarTD);
6436  if (DC != Importer.getToContext().getTranslationUnitDecl())
6437  updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(**TemplateParamsOrErr);
6438 
6439  if (FoundByLookup) {
6440  auto *Recent =
6441  const_cast<VarTemplateDecl *>(FoundByLookup->getMostRecentDecl());
6442  if (!ToTemplated->getPreviousDecl()) {
6443  auto *PrevTemplated =
6444  FoundByLookup->getTemplatedDecl()->getMostRecentDecl();
6445  if (ToTemplated != PrevTemplated)
6446  ToTemplated->setPreviousDecl(PrevTemplated);
6447  }
6448  ToVarTD->setPreviousDecl(Recent);
6449  }
6450 
6451  return ToVarTD;
6452 }
6453 
6454 ExpectedDecl ASTNodeImporter::VisitVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(
6455  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *D) {
6456  // A VarTemplateSpecializationDecl inherits from VarDecl, the import is done
6457  // in an analog way (but specialized for this case).
6458 
6459  SmallVector<Decl *, 2> Redecls = getCanonicalForwardRedeclChain(D);
6460  auto RedeclIt = Redecls.begin();
6461  // Import the first part of the decl chain. I.e. import all previous
6462  // declarations starting from the canonical decl.
6463  for (; RedeclIt != Redecls.end() && *RedeclIt != D; ++RedeclIt) {
6464  ExpectedDecl RedeclOrErr = import(*RedeclIt);
6465  if (!RedeclOrErr)
6466  return RedeclOrErr.takeError();
6467  }
6468  assert(*RedeclIt == D);
6469 
6470  VarTemplateDecl *VarTemplate = nullptr;
6471  if (Error Err = importInto(VarTemplate, D->getSpecializedTemplate()))
6472  return std::move(Err);
6473 
6474  // Import the context of this declaration.
6475  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
6476  if (Error Err = ImportDeclContext(D, DC, LexicalDC))
6477  return std::move(Err);
6478 
6479  // Import the location of this declaration.
6480  ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = import(D->getBeginLoc());
6481  if (!BeginLocOrErr)
6482  return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
6483 
6484  auto IdLocOrErr = import(D->getLocation());
6485  if (!IdLocOrErr)
6486  return IdLocOrErr.takeError();
6487 
6488  // Import template arguments.
6489  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 2> TemplateArgs;
6490  if (Error Err =
6491  ImportTemplateArguments(D->getTemplateArgs().asArray(), TemplateArgs))
6492  return std::move(Err);
6493 
6494  // Try to find an existing specialization with these template arguments.
6495  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
6496  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *FoundSpecialization =
6497  VarTemplate->findSpecialization(TemplateArgs, InsertPos);
6498  if (FoundSpecialization) {
6499  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundSpecialization)) {
6500  VarDecl *FoundDef = FoundSpecialization->getDefinition();
6501  if (D->getDeclContext()->isRecord()) {
6502  // In a record, it is allowed only to have one optional declaration and
6503  // one definition of the (static or constexpr) variable template.
6504  assert(
6505  FoundSpecialization->getDeclContext()->isRecord() &&
6506  "Member variable template specialization imported as non-member, "
6507  "inconsistent imported AST?");
6508  if (FoundDef)
6509  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundDef);
6510  if (!D->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
6511  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundSpecialization);
6512  } else {
6513  // If definition is imported and there is already one, map to it.
6514  // Otherwise create a new variable and link it to the existing.
6515  if (FoundDef && D->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
6516  return Importer.MapImported(D, FoundDef);
6517  }
6518  } else {
6519  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::NameConflict);
6520  }
6521  }
6522 
6523  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *D2 = nullptr;
6524 
6525  TemplateArgumentListInfo ToTAInfo;
6526  if (const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *Args = D->getTemplateArgsInfo()) {
6527  if (Error Err = ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(*Args, ToTAInfo))
6528  return std::move(Err);
6529  }
6530 
6531  using PartVarSpecDecl = VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl;
6532  // Create a new specialization.
6533  if (auto *FromPartial = dyn_cast<PartVarSpecDecl>(D)) {
6534  // Import TemplateArgumentListInfo
6535  TemplateArgumentListInfo ArgInfos;
6536  const auto *FromTAArgsAsWritten = FromPartial->getTemplateArgsAsWritten();
6537  // NOTE: FromTAArgsAsWritten and template parameter list are non-null.
6538  if (Error Err =
6539  ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(*FromTAArgsAsWritten, ArgInfos))
6540  return std::move(Err);
6541 
6542  auto ToTPListOrErr = import(FromPartial->getTemplateParameters());
6543  if (!ToTPListOrErr)
6544  return ToTPListOrErr.takeError();
6545 
6546  PartVarSpecDecl *ToPartial;
6547  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToPartial, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC,
6548  *BeginLocOrErr, *IdLocOrErr, *ToTPListOrErr,
6549  VarTemplate, QualType(), nullptr,
6550  D->getStorageClass(), TemplateArgs, ArgInfos))
6551  return ToPartial;
6552 
6553  if (Expected<PartVarSpecDecl *> ToInstOrErr =
6554  import(FromPartial->getInstantiatedFromMember()))
6555  ToPartial->setInstantiatedFromMember(*ToInstOrErr);
6556  else
6557  return ToInstOrErr.takeError();
6558 
6559  if (FromPartial->isMemberSpecialization())
6560  ToPartial->setMemberSpecialization();
6561 
6562  D2 = ToPartial;
6563 
6564  // FIXME: Use this update if VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl is fixed
6565  // to adopt template parameters.
6566  // updateLookupTableForTemplateParameters(**ToTPListOrErr);
6567  } else { // Full specialization
6568  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(D2, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC,
6569  *BeginLocOrErr, *IdLocOrErr, VarTemplate,
6570  QualType(), nullptr, D->getStorageClass(),
6571  TemplateArgs))
6572  return D2;
6573  }
6574 
6575  QualType T;
6576  if (Error Err = importInto(T, D->getType()))
6577  return std::move(Err);
6578  D2->setType(T);
6579 
6580  auto TInfoOrErr = import(D->getTypeSourceInfo());
6581  if (!TInfoOrErr)
6582  return TInfoOrErr.takeError();
6583  D2->setTypeSourceInfo(*TInfoOrErr);
6584 
6585  if (D->getPointOfInstantiation().isValid()) {
6586  if (ExpectedSLoc POIOrErr = import(D->getPointOfInstantiation()))
6587  D2->setPointOfInstantiation(*POIOrErr);
6588  else
6589  return POIOrErr.takeError();
6590  }
6591 
6592  D2->setSpecializationKind(D->getSpecializationKind());
6593  D2->setTemplateArgsInfo(ToTAInfo);
6594 
6595  if (auto LocOrErr = import(D->getQualifierLoc()))
6596  D2->setQualifierInfo(*LocOrErr);
6597  else
6598  return LocOrErr.takeError();
6599 
6600  if (D->isConstexpr())
6601  D2->setConstexpr(true);
6602 
6603  D2->setAccess(D->getAccess());
6604 
6605  if (Error Err = ImportInitializer(D, D2))
6606  return std::move(Err);
6607 
6608  if (FoundSpecialization)
6609  D2->setPreviousDecl(FoundSpecialization->getMostRecentDecl());
6610 
6611  VarTemplate->AddSpecialization(D2, InsertPos);
6612 
6613  addDeclToContexts(D, D2);
6614 
6615  // Import the rest of the chain. I.e. import all subsequent declarations.
6616  for (++RedeclIt; RedeclIt != Redecls.end(); ++RedeclIt) {
6617  ExpectedDecl RedeclOrErr = import(*RedeclIt);
6618  if (!RedeclOrErr)
6619  return RedeclOrErr.takeError();
6620  }
6621 
6622  return D2;
6623 }
6624 
6625 ExpectedDecl
6626 ASTNodeImporter::VisitFunctionTemplateDecl(FunctionTemplateDecl *D) {
6627  DeclContext *DC, *LexicalDC;
6628  DeclarationName Name;
6629  SourceLocation Loc;
6630  NamedDecl *ToD;
6631 
6632  if (Error Err = ImportDeclParts(D, DC, LexicalDC, Name, ToD, Loc))
6633  return std::move(Err);
6634 
6635  if (ToD)
6636  return ToD;
6637 
6638  const FunctionTemplateDecl *FoundByLookup = nullptr;
6639 
6640  // Try to find a function in our own ("to") context with the same name, same
6641  // type, and in the same context as the function we're importing.
6642  // FIXME Split this into a separate function.
6643  if (!LexicalDC->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
6644  unsigned IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary | Decl::IDNS_OrdinaryFriend;
6645  auto FoundDecls = Importer.findDeclsInToCtx(DC, Name);
6646  for (auto *FoundDecl : FoundDecls) {
6647  if (!FoundDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(IDNS))
6648  continue;
6649 
6650  if (auto *FoundTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(FoundDecl)) {
6651  if (!hasSameVisibilityContextAndLinkage(FoundTemplate, D))
6652  continue;
6653  if (IsStructuralMatch(D, FoundTemplate)) {
6654  FunctionTemplateDecl *TemplateWithDef =
6655  getTemplateDefinition(FoundTemplate);
6656  if (D->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && TemplateWithDef)
6657  return Importer.MapImported(D, TemplateWithDef);
6658 
6659  FoundByLookup = FoundTemplate;
6660  break;
6661  // TODO: handle conflicting names
6662  }
6663  }
6664  }
6665  }
6666 
6667  auto ParamsOrErr = import(D->getTemplateParameters());
6668  if (!ParamsOrErr)
6669  return ParamsOrErr.takeError();
6670  TemplateParameterList *Params = *ParamsOrErr;
6671 
6672  FunctionDecl *TemplatedFD;
6673  if (Error Err = importInto(TemplatedFD, D->getTemplatedDecl()))
6674  return std::move(Err);
6675 
6676  // At creation of the template the template parameters are "adopted"
6677  // (DeclContext is changed). After this possible change the lookup table
6678  // must be updated.
6679  // At deduction guides the DeclContext of the template parameters may be
6680  // different from what we would expect, it may be the class template, or a
6681  // probably different CXXDeductionGuideDecl. This may come from the fact that
6682  // the template parameter objects may be shared between deduction guides or
6683  // the class template, and at creation of multiple FunctionTemplateDecl
6684  // objects (for deduction guides) the same parameters are re-used. The
6685  // "adoption" happens multiple times with different parent, even recursively
6686  // for TemplateTemplateParmDecl. The same happens at import when the
6687  // FunctionTemplateDecl objects are created, but in different order.
6688  // In this way the DeclContext of these template parameters is not necessarily
6689  // the same as in the "from" context.
6690  SmallVector<DeclContext *, 2> OldParamDC;
6691  OldParamDC.reserve(Params->size());
6692  llvm::transform(*Params, std::back_inserter(OldParamDC),
6693  [](NamedDecl *ND) { return ND->getDeclContext(); });
6694 
6695  FunctionTemplateDecl *ToFunc;
6696  if (GetImportedOrCreateDecl(ToFunc, D, Importer.getToContext(), DC, Loc, Name,
6697  Params, TemplatedFD))
6698  return ToFunc;
6699 
6700  TemplatedFD->setDescribedFunctionTemplate(ToFunc);
6701 
6702  ToFunc->setAccess(D->getAccess());
6703  ToFunc->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
6704  addDeclToContexts(D, ToFunc);
6705 
6706  ASTImporterLookupTable *LT = Importer.SharedState->getLookupTable();
6707  if (LT && !OldParamDC.empty()) {
6708  for (unsigned int I = 0; I < OldParamDC.size(); ++I)
6709  LT->updateForced(Params->getParam(I), OldParamDC[I]);
6710  }
6711 
6712  if (FoundByLookup) {
6713  auto *Recent =
6714  const_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl *>(FoundByLookup->getMostRecentDecl());
6715  if (!TemplatedFD->getPreviousDecl()) {
6716  assert(FoundByLookup->getTemplatedDecl() &&
6717  "Found decl must have its templated decl set");
6718  auto *PrevTemplated =
6719  FoundByLookup->getTemplatedDecl()->getMostRecentDecl();
6720  if (TemplatedFD != PrevTemplated)
6721  TemplatedFD->setPreviousDecl(PrevTemplated);
6722  }
6723  ToFunc->setPreviousDecl(Recent);
6724  }
6725 
6726  return ToFunc;
6727 }

6740 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitGCCAsmStmt(GCCAsmStmt *S) {
6741  if (Importer.returnWithErrorInTest())
6742  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::UnsupportedConstruct);
6743  SmallVector<IdentifierInfo *, 4> Names;
6744  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumOutputs(); I != E; I++) {
6745  IdentifierInfo *ToII = Importer.Import(S->getOutputIdentifier(I));
6746  // ToII is nullptr when no symbolic name is given for output operand
6747  // see ParseStmtAsm::ParseAsmOperandsOpt
6748  Names.push_back(ToII);
6749  }
6750 
6751  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumInputs(); I != E; I++) {
6752  IdentifierInfo *ToII = Importer.Import(S->getInputIdentifier(I));
6753  // ToII is nullptr when no symbolic name is given for input operand
6754  // see ParseStmtAsm::ParseAsmOperandsOpt
6755  Names.push_back(ToII);
6756  }
6757 
6758  SmallVector<StringLiteral *, 4> Clobbers;
6759  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumClobbers(); I != E; I++) {
6760  if (auto ClobberOrErr = import(S->getClobberStringLiteral(I)))
6761  Clobbers.push_back(*ClobberOrErr);
6762  else
6763  return ClobberOrErr.takeError();
6764 
6765  }
6766 
6767  SmallVector<StringLiteral *, 4> Constraints;
6768  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumOutputs(); I != E; I++) {
6769  if (auto OutputOrErr = import(S->getOutputConstraintLiteral(I)))
6770  Constraints.push_back(*OutputOrErr);
6771  else
6772  return OutputOrErr.takeError();
6773  }
6774 
6775  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumInputs(); I != E; I++) {
6776  if (auto InputOrErr = import(S->getInputConstraintLiteral(I)))
6777  Constraints.push_back(*InputOrErr);
6778  else
6779  return InputOrErr.takeError();
6780  }
6781 
6782  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> Exprs(S->getNumOutputs() + S->getNumInputs() +
6783  S->getNumLabels());
6784  if (Error Err = ImportContainerChecked(S->outputs(), Exprs))
6785  return std::move(Err);
6786 
6787  if (Error Err =
6788  ImportArrayChecked(S->inputs(), Exprs.begin() + S->getNumOutputs()))
6789  return std::move(Err);
6790 
6791  if (Error Err = ImportArrayChecked(
6792  S->labels(), Exprs.begin() + S->getNumOutputs() + S->getNumInputs()))
6793  return std::move(Err);
6794 
6795  ExpectedSLoc AsmLocOrErr = import(S->getAsmLoc());
6796  if (!AsmLocOrErr)
6797  return AsmLocOrErr.takeError();
6798  auto AsmStrOrErr = import(S->getAsmString());
6799  if (!AsmStrOrErr)
6800  return AsmStrOrErr.takeError();
6801  ExpectedSLoc RParenLocOrErr = import(S->getRParenLoc());
6802  if (!RParenLocOrErr)
6803  return RParenLocOrErr.takeError();
6804 
6805  return new (Importer.getToContext()) GCCAsmStmt(
6806  Importer.getToContext(),
6807  *AsmLocOrErr,
6808  S->isSimple(),
6809  S->isVolatile(),
6810  S->getNumOutputs(),
6811  S->getNumInputs(),
6812  Names.data(),
6813  Constraints.data(),
6814  Exprs.data(),
6815  *AsmStrOrErr,
6816  S->getNumClobbers(),
6817  Clobbers.data(),
6818  S->getNumLabels(),
6819  *RParenLocOrErr);
6820 }

6951  auto ToSwitchLoc = importChecked(Err, S->getSwitchLoc());
6952  if (Err)
6953  return std::move(Err);
6954 
6955  auto *ToStmt =
6956  SwitchStmt::Create(Importer.getToContext(), ToInit, ToConditionVariable,
6957  ToCond, ToLParenLoc, ToRParenLoc);
6958  ToStmt->setBody(ToBody);
6959  ToStmt->setSwitchLoc(ToSwitchLoc);
6960 
6961  // Now we have to re-chain the cases.
6962  SwitchCase *LastChainedSwitchCase = nullptr;
6963  for (SwitchCase *SC = S->getSwitchCaseList(); SC != nullptr;
6964  SC = SC->getNextSwitchCase()) {
6965  Expected<SwitchCase *> ToSCOrErr = import(SC);
6966  if (!ToSCOrErr)
6967  return ToSCOrErr.takeError();
6968  if (LastChainedSwitchCase)
6969  LastChainedSwitchCase->setNextSwitchCase(*ToSCOrErr);
6970  else
6971  ToStmt->setSwitchCaseList(*ToSCOrErr);
6972  LastChainedSwitchCase = *ToSCOrErr;
6973  }
6974 
6975  return ToStmt;
6976 }

7354 ExpectedStmt
7355 ASTNodeImporter::VisitGenericSelectionExpr(GenericSelectionExpr *E) {
7356  Error Err = Error::success();
7357  auto ToGenericLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getGenericLoc());
7358  Expr *ToControllingExpr = nullptr;
7359  TypeSourceInfo *ToControllingType = nullptr;
7360  if (E->isExprPredicate())
7361  ToControllingExpr = importChecked(Err, E->getControllingExpr());
7362  else
7363  ToControllingType = importChecked(Err, E->getControllingType());
7364  assert((ToControllingExpr || ToControllingType) &&
7365  "Either the controlling expr or type must be nonnull");
7366  auto ToDefaultLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getDefaultLoc());
7367  auto ToRParenLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getRParenLoc());
7368  if (Err)
7369  return std::move(Err);
7370 
7371  ArrayRef<const TypeSourceInfo *> FromAssocTypes(E->getAssocTypeSourceInfos());
7372  SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 1> ToAssocTypes(FromAssocTypes.size());
7373  if (Error Err = ImportContainerChecked(FromAssocTypes, ToAssocTypes))
7374  return std::move(Err);
7375 
7376  ArrayRef<const Expr *> FromAssocExprs(E->getAssocExprs());
7377  SmallVector<Expr *, 1> ToAssocExprs(FromAssocExprs.size());
7378  if (Error Err = ImportContainerChecked(FromAssocExprs, ToAssocExprs))
7379  return std::move(Err);
7380 
7381  const ASTContext &ToCtx = Importer.getToContext();
7382  if (E->isResultDependent()) {
7383  if (ToControllingExpr) {
7384  return GenericSelectionExpr::Create(
7385  ToCtx, ToGenericLoc, ToControllingExpr, llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocTypes),
7386  llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocExprs), ToDefaultLoc, ToRParenLoc,
7387  E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack());
7388  }
7389  return GenericSelectionExpr::Create(
7390  ToCtx, ToGenericLoc, ToControllingType, llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocTypes),
7391  llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocExprs), ToDefaultLoc, ToRParenLoc,
7392  E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack());
7393  }
7394 
7395  if (ToControllingExpr) {
7396  return GenericSelectionExpr::Create(
7397  ToCtx, ToGenericLoc, ToControllingExpr, llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocTypes),
7398  llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocExprs), ToDefaultLoc, ToRParenLoc,
7399  E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack(), E->getResultIndex());
7400  }
7401  return GenericSelectionExpr::Create(
7402  ToCtx, ToGenericLoc, ToControllingType, llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocTypes),
7403  llvm::ArrayRef(ToAssocExprs), ToDefaultLoc, ToRParenLoc,
7404  E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack(), E->getResultIndex());
7405 }

7421 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *E) {
7422 
7423  Error Err = Error::success();
7424  auto ToQualifierLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getQualifierLoc());
7425  auto ToTemplateKeywordLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7426  auto ToDecl = importChecked(Err, E->getDecl());
7427  auto ToLocation = importChecked(Err, E->getLocation());
7428  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, E->getType());
7429  if (Err)
7430  return std::move(Err);
7431 
7432  NamedDecl *ToFoundD = nullptr;
7433  if (E->getDecl() != E->getFoundDecl()) {
7434  auto FoundDOrErr = import(E->getFoundDecl());
7435  if (!FoundDOrErr)
7436  return FoundDOrErr.takeError();
7437  ToFoundD = *FoundDOrErr;
7438  }
7439 
7440  TemplateArgumentListInfo ToTAInfo;
7441  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ToResInfo = nullptr;
7442  if (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
7443  if (Error Err =
7444  ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(E->getLAngleLoc(), E->getRAngleLoc(),
7445  E->template_arguments(), ToTAInfo))
7446  return std::move(Err);
7447  ToResInfo = &ToTAInfo;
7448  }
7449 
7450  auto *ToE = DeclRefExpr::Create(
7451  Importer.getToContext(), ToQualifierLoc, ToTemplateKeywordLoc, ToDecl,
7452  E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture(), ToLocation, ToType,
7453  E->getValueKind(), ToFoundD, ToResInfo, E->isNonOdrUse());
7454  if (E->hadMultipleCandidates())
7455  ToE->setHadMultipleCandidates(true);
7456  ToE->setIsImmediateEscalating(E->isImmediateEscalating());
7457  return ToE;
7458 }

7468 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitDesignatedInitExpr(DesignatedInitExpr *E) {
7469  ExpectedExpr ToInitOrErr = import(E->getInit());
7470  if (!ToInitOrErr)
7471  return ToInitOrErr.takeError();
7472 
7473  ExpectedSLoc ToEqualOrColonLocOrErr = import(E->getEqualOrColonLoc());
7474  if (!ToEqualOrColonLocOrErr)
7475  return ToEqualOrColonLocOrErr.takeError();
7476 
7477  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> ToIndexExprs(E->getNumSubExprs() - 1);
7478  // List elements from the second, the first is Init itself
7479  for (unsigned I = 1, N = E->getNumSubExprs(); I < N; I++) {
7480  if (ExpectedExpr ToArgOrErr = import(E->getSubExpr(I)))
7481  ToIndexExprs[I - 1] = *ToArgOrErr;
7482  else
7483  return ToArgOrErr.takeError();
7484  }

7488  return std::move(Err);
7489 
7490  return DesignatedInitExpr::Create(
7491  Importer.getToContext(), ToDesignators,
7492  ToIndexExprs, *ToEqualOrColonLocOrErr,
7493  E->usesGNUSyntax(), *ToInitOrErr);
7494 }

7895  return ToTypeOrErr.takeError();

7897  ExpectedExpr ToSubExprOrErr = import(E->getSubExpr());
7898  if (!ToSubExprOrErr)
7899  return ToSubExprOrErr.takeError();
7900 
7901  Expected<CXXCastPath> ToBasePathOrErr = ImportCastPath(E);
7902  if (!ToBasePathOrErr)
7903  return ToBasePathOrErr.takeError();
7904

7910 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitExplicitCastExpr(ExplicitCastExpr *E) {
7911  Error Err = Error::success();
7912  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, E->getType());
7913  auto ToSubExpr = importChecked(Err, E->getSubExpr());
7914  auto ToTypeInfoAsWritten = importChecked(Err, E->getTypeInfoAsWritten());
7915  if (Err)
7916  return std::move(Err);
7917 
7918  Expected<CXXCastPath> ToBasePathOrErr = ImportCastPath(E);
7919  if (!ToBasePathOrErr)
7920  return ToBasePathOrErr.takeError();
7921  CXXCastPath *ToBasePath = &(*ToBasePathOrErr);
7922 
7923  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
7924  case Stmt::CStyleCastExprClass: {
7925  auto *CCE = cast<CStyleCastExpr>(E);
7926  ExpectedSLoc ToLParenLocOrErr = import(CCE->getLParenLoc());
7927  if (!ToLParenLocOrErr)
7928  return ToLParenLocOrErr.takeError();
7929  ExpectedSLoc ToRParenLocOrErr = import(CCE->getRParenLoc());
7930  if (!ToRParenLocOrErr)
7931  return ToRParenLocOrErr.takeError();
7932  return CStyleCastExpr::Create(
7933  Importer.getToContext(), ToType, E->getValueKind(), E->getCastKind(),
7934  ToSubExpr, ToBasePath, CCE->getFPFeatures(), ToTypeInfoAsWritten,
7935  *ToLParenLocOrErr, *ToRParenLocOrErr);
7936  }
7937 
7938  case Stmt::CXXFunctionalCastExprClass: {
7939  auto *FCE = cast<CXXFunctionalCastExpr>(E);
7940  ExpectedSLoc ToLParenLocOrErr = import(FCE->getLParenLoc());
7941  if (!ToLParenLocOrErr)
7942  return ToLParenLocOrErr.takeError();
7943  ExpectedSLoc ToRParenLocOrErr = import(FCE->getRParenLoc());
7944  if (!ToRParenLocOrErr)
7945  return ToRParenLocOrErr.takeError();
7946  return CXXFunctionalCastExpr::Create(
7947  Importer.getToContext(), ToType, E->getValueKind(), ToTypeInfoAsWritten,
7948  E->getCastKind(), ToSubExpr, ToBasePath, FCE->getFPFeatures(),
7949  *ToLParenLocOrErr, *ToRParenLocOrErr);
7950  }
7951 
7952  case Stmt::ObjCBridgedCastExprClass: {
7953  auto *OCE = cast<ObjCBridgedCastExpr>(E);
7954  ExpectedSLoc ToLParenLocOrErr = import(OCE->getLParenLoc());
7955  if (!ToLParenLocOrErr)
7956  return ToLParenLocOrErr.takeError();
7957  ExpectedSLoc ToBridgeKeywordLocOrErr = import(OCE->getBridgeKeywordLoc());
7958  if (!ToBridgeKeywordLocOrErr)
7959  return ToBridgeKeywordLocOrErr.takeError();
7960  return new (Importer.getToContext()) ObjCBridgedCastExpr(
7961  *ToLParenLocOrErr, OCE->getBridgeKind(), E->getCastKind(),
7962  *ToBridgeKeywordLocOrErr, ToTypeInfoAsWritten, ToSubExpr);
7963  }
7964  case Stmt::BuiltinBitCastExprClass: {
7965  auto *BBC = cast<BuiltinBitCastExpr>(E);
7966  ExpectedSLoc ToKWLocOrErr = import(BBC->getBeginLoc());
7967  if (!ToKWLocOrErr)
7968  return ToKWLocOrErr.takeError();
7969  ExpectedSLoc ToRParenLocOrErr = import(BBC->getEndLoc());
7970  if (!ToRParenLocOrErr)
7971  return ToRParenLocOrErr.takeError();
7972  return new (Importer.getToContext()) BuiltinBitCastExpr(
7973  ToType, E->getValueKind(), E->getCastKind(), ToSubExpr,
7974  ToTypeInfoAsWritten, *ToKWLocOrErr, *ToRParenLocOrErr);
7975  }
7976  default:
7977  llvm_unreachable("Cast expression of unsupported type!");
7978  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::UnsupportedConstruct);
7979  }
7980 }
7981 
7982 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
7983  SmallVector<OffsetOfNode, 4> ToNodes;
7984  for (int I = 0, N = E->getNumComponents(); I < N; ++I) {
7985  const OffsetOfNode &FromNode = E->getComponent(I);
7986 
7987  SourceLocation ToBeginLoc, ToEndLoc;
7988 
7989  if (FromNode.getKind() != OffsetOfNode::Base) {
7990  Error Err = Error::success();
7991  ToBeginLoc = importChecked(Err, FromNode.getBeginLoc());
7992  ToEndLoc = importChecked(Err, FromNode.getEndLoc());
7993  if (Err)
7994  return std::move(Err);
7995  }
7996 
7997  switch (FromNode.getKind()) {
7998  case OffsetOfNode::Array:
7999  ToNodes.push_back(
8000  OffsetOfNode(ToBeginLoc, FromNode.getArrayExprIndex(), ToEndLoc));
8001  break;
8002  case OffsetOfNode::Base: {
8003  auto ToBSOrErr = import(FromNode.getBase());
8004  if (!ToBSOrErr)
8005  return ToBSOrErr.takeError();
8006  ToNodes.push_back(OffsetOfNode(*ToBSOrErr));
8007  break;
8008  }
8009  case OffsetOfNode::Field: {
8010  auto ToFieldOrErr = import(FromNode.getField());
8011  if (!ToFieldOrErr)
8012  return ToFieldOrErr.takeError();
8013  ToNodes.push_back(OffsetOfNode(ToBeginLoc, *ToFieldOrErr, ToEndLoc));
8014  break;
8015  }
8016  case OffsetOfNode::Identifier: {
8017  IdentifierInfo *ToII = Importer.Import(FromNode.getFieldName());
8018  ToNodes.push_back(OffsetOfNode(ToBeginLoc, ToII, ToEndLoc));
8019  break;
8020  }
8021  }
8022  }
8023 
8024  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> ToExprs(E->getNumExpressions());
8025  for (int I = 0, N = E->getNumExpressions(); I < N; ++I) {
8026  ExpectedExpr ToIndexExprOrErr = import(E->getIndexExpr(I));
8027  if (!ToIndexExprOrErr)
8028  return ToIndexExprOrErr.takeError();
8029  ToExprs[I] = *ToIndexExprOrErr;
8030  }
8031 
8032  Error Err = Error::success();
8033  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, E->getType());
8034  auto ToTypeSourceInfo = importChecked(Err, E->getTypeSourceInfo());
8035  auto ToOperatorLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getOperatorLoc());
8036  auto ToRParenLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getRParenLoc());
8037  if (Err)
8038  return std::move(Err);
8039 
8040  return OffsetOfExpr::Create(
8041  Importer.getToContext(), ToType, ToOperatorLoc, ToTypeSourceInfo, ToNodes,
8042  ToExprs, ToRParenLoc);
8043 }

8076 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitCXXDefaultArgExpr(CXXDefaultArgExpr *E) {
8077  ExpectedSLoc ToUsedLocOrErr = import(E->getUsedLocation());
8078  if (!ToUsedLocOrErr)
8079  return ToUsedLocOrErr.takeError();
8080 
8081  auto ToParamOrErr = import(E->getParam());
8082  if (!ToParamOrErr)
8083  return ToParamOrErr.takeError();
8084 
8085  auto UsedContextOrErr = Importer.ImportContext(E->getUsedContext());
8086  if (!UsedContextOrErr)
8087  return UsedContextOrErr.takeError();
8088 
8089  // Import the default arg if it was not imported yet.
8090  // This is needed because it can happen that during the import of the
8091  // default expression (from VisitParmVarDecl) the same ParmVarDecl is
8092  // encountered here. The default argument for a ParmVarDecl is set in the
8093  // ParmVarDecl only after it is imported (set in VisitParmVarDecl if not here,
8094  // see VisitParmVarDecl).
8095  ParmVarDecl *ToParam = *ToParamOrErr;
8096  if (!ToParam->getDefaultArg()) {
8097  std::optional<ParmVarDecl *> FromParam =
8098  Importer.getImportedFromDecl(ToParam);
8099  assert(FromParam && "ParmVarDecl was not imported?");
8100 
8101  if (Error Err = ImportDefaultArgOfParmVarDecl(*FromParam, ToParam))
8102  return std::move(Err);
8103  }
8104  Expr *RewrittenInit = nullptr;
8105  if (E->hasRewrittenInit()) {
8106  ExpectedExpr ExprOrErr = import(E->getRewrittenExpr());
8107  if (!ExprOrErr)
8108  return ExprOrErr.takeError();
8109  RewrittenInit = ExprOrErr.get();
8110  }
8111  return CXXDefaultArgExpr::Create(Importer.getToContext(), *ToUsedLocOrErr,
8112  *ToParamOrErr, RewrittenInit,
8113  *UsedContextOrErr);
8114 }

8533 ExpectedStmt
8534 ASTNodeImporter::VisitUnresolvedLookupExpr(UnresolvedLookupExpr *E) {
8535  Expected<CXXRecordDecl *> ToNamingClassOrErr = import(E->getNamingClass());
8536  if (!ToNamingClassOrErr)
8537  return ToNamingClassOrErr.takeError();
8538 
8539  auto ToQualifierLocOrErr = import(E->getQualifierLoc());
8540  if (!ToQualifierLocOrErr)
8541  return ToQualifierLocOrErr.takeError();
8542 
8543  Error Err = Error::success();
8544  auto ToName = importChecked(Err, E->getName());
8545  auto ToNameLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getNameLoc());
8546  if (Err)
8547  return std::move(Err);
8548  DeclarationNameInfo ToNameInfo(ToName, ToNameLoc);
8549 
8550  // Import additional name location/type info.
8551  if (Error Err = ImportDeclarationNameLoc(E->getNameInfo(), ToNameInfo))
8552  return std::move(Err);
8553 
8554  UnresolvedSet<8> ToDecls;
8555  for (auto *D : E->decls())
8556  if (auto ToDOrErr = import(D))
8557  ToDecls.addDecl(cast<NamedDecl>(*ToDOrErr));
8558  else
8559  return ToDOrErr.takeError();
8560 
8561  if (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
8562  TemplateArgumentListInfo ToTAInfo;
8563  if (Error Err = ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(
8564  E->getLAngleLoc(), E->getRAngleLoc(), E->template_arguments(),
8565  ToTAInfo))
8566  return std::move(Err);
8567 
8568  ExpectedSLoc ToTemplateKeywordLocOrErr = import(E->getTemplateKeywordLoc());
8569  if (!ToTemplateKeywordLocOrErr)
8570  return ToTemplateKeywordLocOrErr.takeError();
8571 
8572  const bool KnownDependent =
8573  (E->getDependence() & ExprDependence::TypeValue) ==
8574  ExprDependence::TypeValue;
8575  return UnresolvedLookupExpr::Create(
8576  Importer.getToContext(), *ToNamingClassOrErr, *ToQualifierLocOrErr,
8577  *ToTemplateKeywordLocOrErr, ToNameInfo, E->requiresADL(), &ToTAInfo,
8578  ToDecls.begin(), ToDecls.end(), KnownDependent);
8579  }
8580 
8581  return UnresolvedLookupExpr::Create(
8582  Importer.getToContext(), *ToNamingClassOrErr, *ToQualifierLocOrErr,
8583  ToNameInfo, E->requiresADL(), ToDecls.begin(), ToDecls.end(),
8584  /*KnownDependent=*/E->isTypeDependent());
8585 }

8587 ExpectedStmt
8588 ASTNodeImporter::VisitUnresolvedMemberExpr(UnresolvedMemberExpr *E) {
8589  Error Err = Error::success();
8590  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, E->getType());
8591  auto ToOperatorLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getOperatorLoc());
8592  auto ToQualifierLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getQualifierLoc());
8593  auto ToTemplateKeywordLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getTemplateKeywordLoc());
8594  auto ToName = importChecked(Err, E->getName());
8595  auto ToNameLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getNameLoc());
8596  if (Err)
8597  return std::move(Err);
8598 
8599  DeclarationNameInfo ToNameInfo(ToName, ToNameLoc);
8600  // Import additional name location/type info.
8601  if (Error Err = ImportDeclarationNameLoc(E->getNameInfo(), ToNameInfo))
8602  return std::move(Err);
8603 
8604  UnresolvedSet<8> ToDecls;
8605  for (Decl *D : E->decls())
8606  if (auto ToDOrErr = import(D))
8607  ToDecls.addDecl(cast<NamedDecl>(*ToDOrErr));
8608  else
8609  return ToDOrErr.takeError();
8610 
8611  TemplateArgumentListInfo ToTAInfo;
8612  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ResInfo = nullptr;
8613  if (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
8614  TemplateArgumentListInfo FromTAInfo;
8615  E->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(FromTAInfo);
8616  if (Error Err = ImportTemplateArgumentListInfo(FromTAInfo, ToTAInfo))
8617  return std::move(Err);
8618  ResInfo = &ToTAInfo;
8619  }
8620 
8621  Expr *ToBase = nullptr;
8622  if (!E->isImplicitAccess()) {
8623  if (ExpectedExpr ToBaseOrErr = import(E->getBase()))
8624  ToBase = *ToBaseOrErr;
8625  else
8626  return ToBaseOrErr.takeError();
8627  }
8628 
8629  return UnresolvedMemberExpr::Create(
8630  Importer.getToContext(), E->hasUnresolvedUsing(), ToBase, ToType,
8631  E->isArrow(), ToOperatorLoc, ToQualifierLoc, ToTemplateKeywordLoc,
8632  ToNameInfo, ResInfo, ToDecls.begin(), ToDecls.end());
8633 }

8635 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitCallExpr(CallExpr *E) {
8636  Error Err = Error::success();
8637  auto ToCallee = importChecked(Err, E->getCallee());
8638  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, E->getType());
8639  auto ToRParenLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getRParenLoc());
8640  if (Err)
8641  return std::move(Err);
8642 
8643  unsigned NumArgs = E->getNumArgs();
8644  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 2> ToArgs(NumArgs);
8645  if (Error Err = ImportContainerChecked(E->arguments(), ToArgs))
8646  return std::move(Err);
8647 
8648  if (const auto *OCE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E)) {
8649  return CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(
8650  Importer.getToContext(), OCE->getOperator(), ToCallee, ToArgs, ToType,
8651  OCE->getValueKind(), ToRParenLoc, OCE->getFPFeatures(),
8652  OCE->getADLCallKind());
8653  }
8654 
8655  return CallExpr::Create(Importer.getToContext(), ToCallee, ToArgs, ToType,
8656  E->getValueKind(), ToRParenLoc, E->getFPFeatures(),
8657  /*MinNumArgs=*/0, E->getADLCallKind());
8658 }

8660 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitLambdaExpr(LambdaExpr *E) {
8661  CXXRecordDecl *FromClass = E->getLambdaClass();
8662  auto ToClassOrErr = import(FromClass);
8663  if (!ToClassOrErr)
8664  return ToClassOrErr.takeError();
8665  CXXRecordDecl *ToClass = *ToClassOrErr;
8666 
8667  auto ToCallOpOrErr = import(E->getCallOperator());

8678  auto ToEndLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getEndLoc());
8679  if (Err)
8680  return std::move(Err);
8681 
8682  return LambdaExpr::Create(Importer.getToContext(), ToClass, ToIntroducerRange,
8683  E->getCaptureDefault(), ToCaptureDefaultLoc,
8684  E->hasExplicitParameters(),
8685  E->hasExplicitResultType(), ToCaptureInits,
8686  ToEndLoc, E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack());

8690 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitInitListExpr(InitListExpr *E) {
8691  Error Err = Error::success();

8694  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, E->getType());
8695  if (Err)
8696  return std::move(Err);

8717  else

8719  }

8726  }

8729  // InitListExpr.

8782 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitCXXDefaultInitExpr(CXXDefaultInitExpr *E) {
8783  ExpectedSLoc ToBeginLocOrErr = import(E->getBeginLoc());
8784  if (!ToBeginLocOrErr)
8785  return ToBeginLocOrErr.takeError();
8786 
8787  auto ToFieldOrErr = import(E->getField());
8788  if (!ToFieldOrErr)
8789  return ToFieldOrErr.takeError();
8790 
8791  auto UsedContextOrErr = Importer.ImportContext(E->getUsedContext());
8792  if (!UsedContextOrErr)
8793  return UsedContextOrErr.takeError();
8794 
8795  FieldDecl *ToField = *ToFieldOrErr;
8796  assert(ToField->hasInClassInitializer() &&
8797  "Field should have in-class initializer if there is a default init "
8798  "expression that uses it.");
8799  if (!ToField->getInClassInitializer()) {
8800  // The in-class initializer may be not yet set in "To" AST even if the
8801  // field is already there. This must be set here to make construction of
8802  // CXXDefaultInitExpr work.
8803  auto ToInClassInitializerOrErr =
8804  import(E->getField()->getInClassInitializer());
8805  if (!ToInClassInitializerOrErr)
8806  return ToInClassInitializerOrErr.takeError();
8807  ToField->setInClassInitializer(*ToInClassInitializerOrErr);
8808  }
8809 
8810  Expr *RewrittenInit = nullptr;
8811  if (E->hasRewrittenInit()) {
8812  ExpectedExpr ExprOrErr = import(E->getRewrittenExpr());
8813  if (!ExprOrErr)
8814  return ExprOrErr.takeError();
8815  RewrittenInit = ExprOrErr.get();
8816  }
8817 
8818  return CXXDefaultInitExpr::Create(Importer.getToContext(), *ToBeginLocOrErr,
8819  ToField, *UsedContextOrErr, RewrittenInit);
8820 }

8822 ExpectedStmt ASTNodeImporter::VisitCXXNamedCastExpr(CXXNamedCastExpr *E) {
8823  Error Err = Error::success();
8824  auto ToType = importChecked(Err, E->getType());
8825  auto ToSubExpr = importChecked(Err, E->getSubExpr());
8826  auto ToTypeInfoAsWritten = importChecked(Err, E->getTypeInfoAsWritten());
8827  auto ToOperatorLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getOperatorLoc());
8828  auto ToRParenLoc = importChecked(Err, E->getRParenLoc());
8829  auto ToAngleBrackets = importChecked(Err, E->getAngleBrackets());
8830  if (Err)
8831  return std::move(Err);
8832 
8833  ExprValueKind VK = E->getValueKind();
8834  CastKind CK = E->getCastKind();
8835  auto ToBasePathOrErr = ImportCastPath(E);
8836  if (!ToBasePathOrErr)
8837  return ToBasePathOrErr.takeError();
8838 
8839  if (auto CCE = dyn_cast<CXXStaticCastExpr>(E)) {
8840  return CXXStaticCastExpr::Create(
8841  Importer.getToContext(), ToType, VK, CK, ToSubExpr, &(*ToBasePathOrErr),
8842  ToTypeInfoAsWritten, CCE->getFPFeatures(), ToOperatorLoc, ToRParenLoc,
8843  ToAngleBrackets);
8844  } else if (isa<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(E)) {
8845  return CXXDynamicCastExpr::Create(
8846  Importer.getToContext(), ToType, VK, CK, ToSubExpr, &(*ToBasePathOrErr),
8847  ToTypeInfoAsWritten, ToOperatorLoc, ToRParenLoc, ToAngleBrackets);
8848  } else if (isa<CXXReinterpretCastExpr>(E)) {
8849  return CXXReinterpretCastExpr::Create(
8850  Importer.getToContext(), ToType, VK, CK, ToSubExpr, &(*ToBasePathOrErr),
8851  ToTypeInfoAsWritten, ToOperatorLoc, ToRParenLoc, ToAngleBrackets);
8852  } else if (isa<CXXConstCastExpr>(E)) {
8853  return CXXConstCastExpr::Create(
8854  Importer.getToContext(), ToType, VK, ToSubExpr, ToTypeInfoAsWritten,
8855  ToOperatorLoc, ToRParenLoc, ToAngleBrackets);
8856  } else {
8857  llvm_unreachable("Unknown cast type");
8858  return make_error<ASTImportError>();
8859  }
8860 }

8942 Error ASTNodeImporter::ImportOverriddenMethods(CXXMethodDecl *ToMethod,
8943  CXXMethodDecl *FromMethod) {
8944  Error ImportErrors = Error::success();
8945  for (auto *FromOverriddenMethod : FromMethod->overridden_methods()) {
8946  if (auto ImportedOrErr = import(FromOverriddenMethod))
8947  ToMethod->getCanonicalDecl()->addOverriddenMethod(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(
8948  (*ImportedOrErr)->getCanonicalDecl()));
8949  else
8950  ImportErrors =
8951  joinErrors(std::move(ImportErrors), ImportedOrErr.takeError());
8952  }

8956 ASTImporter::ASTImporter(ASTContext &ToContext, FileManager &ToFileManager,
8957  ASTContext &FromContext, FileManager &FromFileManager,

8975 std::optional<unsigned> ASTImporter::getFieldIndex(Decl *F) {
8976  assert(F && (isa<FieldDecl>(*F) || isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(*F)) &&
8977  "Try to get field index for non-field.");
8978 
8979  auto *Owner = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(F->getDeclContext());
8980  if (!Owner)
8981  return std::nullopt;
8982 
8983  unsigned Index = 0;
8984  for (const auto *D : Owner->decls()) {
8985  if (D == F)
8986  return Index;
8987 
8988  if (isa<FieldDecl>(*D) || isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(*D))
8989  ++Index;
8990  }
8991 
8992  llvm_unreachable("Field was not found in its parent context.");
8993 
8994  return std::nullopt;
8995 }
8996 
8997 ASTImporter::FoundDeclsTy
8998 ASTImporter::findDeclsInToCtx(DeclContext *DC, DeclarationName Name) {
8999  // We search in the redecl context because of transparent contexts.
9000  // E.g. a simple C language enum is a transparent context:
9001  // enum E { A, B };
9002  // Now if we had a global variable in the TU
9003  // int A;
9004  // then the enum constant 'A' and the variable 'A' violates ODR.
9005  // We can diagnose this only if we search in the redecl context.
9006  DeclContext *ReDC = DC->getRedeclContext();
9007  if (SharedState->getLookupTable()) {
9008  ASTImporterLookupTable::LookupResult LookupResult =
9009  SharedState->getLookupTable()->lookup(ReDC, Name);
9010  return FoundDeclsTy(LookupResult.begin(), LookupResult.end());
9011  } else {
9012  DeclContext::lookup_result NoloadLookupResult = ReDC->noload_lookup(Name);
9013  FoundDeclsTy Result(NoloadLookupResult.begin(), NoloadLookupResult.end());
9014  // We must search by the slow case of localUncachedLookup because that is
9015  // working even if there is no LookupPtr for the DC. We could use
9016  // DC::buildLookup() to create the LookupPtr, but that would load external
9017  // decls again, we must avoid that case.
9018  // Also, even if we had the LookupPtr, we must find Decls which are not
9019  // in the LookupPtr, so we need the slow case.
9020  // These cases are handled in ASTImporterLookupTable, but we cannot use
9021  // that with LLDB since that traverses through the AST which initiates the
9022  // load of external decls again via DC::decls(). And again, we must avoid
9023  // loading external decls during the import.
9024  if (Result.empty())
9025  ReDC->localUncachedLookup(Name, Result);
9026  return Result;
9027  }
9028 }

9044 llvm::Expected<ExprWithCleanups::CleanupObject>

9046  if (auto *CLE = From.dyn_cast<CompoundLiteralExpr *>()) {

9055 
9056 ExpectedTypePtr ASTImporter::Import(const Type *FromT) {
9057  if (!FromT)
9058  return FromT;
9059 
9060  // Check whether we've already imported this type.
9061  llvm::DenseMap<const Type *, const Type *>::iterator Pos =
9062  ImportedTypes.find(FromT);
9063  if (Pos != ImportedTypes.end())
9064  return Pos->second;
9065 
9066  // Import the type.
9067  ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
9068  ExpectedType ToTOrErr = Importer.Visit(FromT);
9069  if (!ToTOrErr)
9070  return ToTOrErr.takeError();
9071 
9072  // Record the imported type.
9073  ImportedTypes[FromT] = ToTOrErr->getTypePtr();
9074 
9075  return ToTOrErr->getTypePtr();
9076 }

9078 Expected<QualType> ASTImporter::Import(QualType FromT) {
9079  if (FromT.isNull())
9080  return QualType{};
9081 
9082  ExpectedTypePtr ToTyOrErr = Import(FromT.getTypePtr());
9083  if (!ToTyOrErr)
9084  return ToTyOrErr.takeError();
9085 
9086  return ToContext.getQualifiedType(*ToTyOrErr, FromT.getLocalQualifiers());
9087 }

9089 Expected<TypeSourceInfo *> ASTImporter::Import(TypeSourceInfo *FromTSI) {
9090  if (!FromTSI)
9091  return FromTSI;
9092 
9093  // FIXME: For now we just create a "trivial" type source info based
9094  // on the type and a single location. Implement a real version of this.
9095  ExpectedType TOrErr = Import(FromTSI->getType());
9096  if (!TOrErr)
9097  return TOrErr.takeError();
9098  ExpectedSLoc BeginLocOrErr = Import(FromTSI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc());
9099  if (!BeginLocOrErr)
9100  return BeginLocOrErr.takeError();
9101 
9102  return ToContext.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(*TOrErr, *BeginLocOrErr);
9103 }
