9105 namespace {
9106 // To use this object, it should be created before the new attribute is created,
9107 // and destructed after it is created. The construction already performs the
9108 // import of the data.
9109 template <typename T> struct AttrArgImporter {
9110  AttrArgImporter(const AttrArgImporter<T> &) = delete;
9111  AttrArgImporter(AttrArgImporter<T> &&) = default;
9112  AttrArgImporter<T> &operator=(const AttrArgImporter<T> &) = delete;
9113  AttrArgImporter<T> &operator=(AttrArgImporter<T> &&) = default;
9114 
9115  AttrArgImporter(ASTNodeImporter &I, Error &Err, const T &From)
9116  : To(I.importChecked(Err, From)) {}
9117 
9118  const T &value() { return To; }
9119 
9120 private:
9121  T To;
9122 };
9123 
9124 // To use this object, it should be created before the new attribute is created,
9125 // and destructed after it is created. The construction already performs the
9126 // import of the data. The array data is accessible in a pointer form, this form
9127 // is used by the attribute classes. This object should be created once for the
9128 // array data to be imported (the array size is not imported, just copied).
9129 template <typename T> struct AttrArgArrayImporter {
9130  AttrArgArrayImporter(const AttrArgArrayImporter<T> &) = delete;
9131  AttrArgArrayImporter(AttrArgArrayImporter<T> &&) = default;
9132  AttrArgArrayImporter<T> &operator=(const AttrArgArrayImporter<T> &) = delete;
9133  AttrArgArrayImporter<T> &operator=(AttrArgArrayImporter<T> &&) = default;
9134 
9135  AttrArgArrayImporter(ASTNodeImporter &I, Error &Err,
9136  const llvm::iterator_range<T *> &From,
9137  unsigned ArraySize) {
9138  if (Err)
9139  return;
9140  To.reserve(ArraySize);
9141  Err = I.ImportContainerChecked(From, To);
9142  }
9143 
9144  T *value() { return To.data(); }
9145 
9146 private:
9147  llvm::SmallVector<T, 2> To;
9148 };
9149 
9150 class AttrImporter {
9151  Error Err{Error::success()};
9152  Attr *ToAttr = nullptr;
9153  ASTImporter &Importer;
9154  ASTNodeImporter NImporter;
9155 
9156 public:
9157  AttrImporter(ASTImporter &I) : Importer(I), NImporter(I) {}
9158 
9159  // Useful for accessing the imported attribute.
9160  template <typename T> T *castAttrAs() { return cast<T>(ToAttr); }
9161  template <typename T> const T *castAttrAs() const { return cast<T>(ToAttr); }
9162 
9163  // Create an "importer" for an attribute parameter.
9164  // Result of the 'value()' of that object is to be passed to the function
9165  // 'importAttr', in the order that is expected by the attribute class.
9166  template <class T> AttrArgImporter<T> importArg(const T &From) {
9167  return AttrArgImporter<T>(NImporter, Err, From);
9168  }
9169 
9170  // Create an "importer" for an attribute parameter that has array type.
9171  // Result of the 'value()' of that object is to be passed to the function
9172  // 'importAttr', then the size of the array as next argument.
9173  template <typename T>
9174  AttrArgArrayImporter<T> importArrayArg(const llvm::iterator_range<T *> &From,
9175  unsigned ArraySize) {
9176  return AttrArgArrayImporter<T>(NImporter, Err, From, ArraySize);
9177  }
9178 
9179  // Create an attribute object with the specified arguments.
9180  // The 'FromAttr' is the original (not imported) attribute, the 'ImportedArg'
9181  // should be values that are passed to the 'Create' function of the attribute.
9182  // (The 'Create' with 'ASTContext' first and 'AttributeCommonInfo' last is
9183  // used here.) As much data is copied or imported from the old attribute
9184  // as possible. The passed arguments should be already imported.
9185  // If an import error happens, the internal error is set to it, and any
9186  // further import attempt is ignored.
9187  template <typename T, typename... Arg>
9188  void importAttr(const T *FromAttr, Arg &&...ImportedArg) {
9189  static_assert(std::is_base_of<Attr, T>::value,
9190  "T should be subclass of Attr.");
9191  assert(!ToAttr && "Use one AttrImporter to import one Attribute object.");
9192 
9193  const IdentifierInfo *ToAttrName = Importer.Import(FromAttr->getAttrName());
9194  const IdentifierInfo *ToScopeName =
9195  Importer.Import(FromAttr->getScopeName());
9196  SourceRange ToAttrRange =
9197  NImporter.importChecked(Err, FromAttr->getRange());
9198  SourceLocation ToScopeLoc =
9199  NImporter.importChecked(Err, FromAttr->getScopeLoc());
9200 
9201  if (Err)
9202  return;
9203 
9204  AttributeCommonInfo ToI(ToAttrName, ToScopeName, ToAttrRange, ToScopeLoc,
9205  FromAttr->getParsedKind(), FromAttr->getForm());
9206  // The "SemanticSpelling" is not needed to be passed to the constructor.
9207  // That value is recalculated from the SpellingListIndex if needed.
9208  ToAttr = T::Create(Importer.getToContext(),
9209  std::forward<Arg>(ImportedArg)..., ToI);
9210 
9211  ToAttr->setImplicit(FromAttr->isImplicit());
9212  ToAttr->setPackExpansion(FromAttr->isPackExpansion());
9213  if (auto *ToInheritableAttr = dyn_cast<InheritableAttr>(ToAttr))
9214  ToInheritableAttr->setInherited(FromAttr->isInherited());
9215  }
9216 
9217  // Create a clone of the 'FromAttr' and import its source range only.
9218  // This causes objects with invalid references to be created if the 'FromAttr'
9219  // contains other data that should be imported.
9220  void cloneAttr(const Attr *FromAttr) {
9221  assert(!ToAttr && "Use one AttrImporter to import one Attribute object.");
9222 
9223  SourceRange ToRange = NImporter.importChecked(Err, FromAttr->getRange());
9224  if (Err)
9225  return;
9226 
9227  ToAttr = FromAttr->clone(Importer.getToContext());
9228  ToAttr->setRange(ToRange);
9229  ToAttr->setAttrName(Importer.Import(FromAttr->getAttrName()));
9230  }
9231 
9232  // Get the result of the previous import attempt (can be used only once).
9233  llvm::Expected<Attr *> getResult() && {
9234  if (Err)
9235  return std::move(Err);
9236  assert(ToAttr && "Attribute should be created.");
9237  return ToAttr;
9238  }
9239 };
9240 } // namespace
9241 
9242 Expected<Attr *> ASTImporter::Import(const Attr *FromAttr) {
9243  AttrImporter AI(*this);
9244 
9245  // FIXME: Is there some kind of AttrVisitor to use here?
9246  switch (FromAttr->getKind()) {
9247  case attr::Aligned: {
9248  auto *From = cast<AlignedAttr>(FromAttr);
9249  if (From->isAlignmentExpr())
9250  AI.importAttr(From, true, AI.importArg(From->getAlignmentExpr()).value());
9251  else
9252  AI.importAttr(From, false,
9253  AI.importArg(From->getAlignmentType()).value());
9254  break;
9255  }
9256 
9257  case attr::AlignValue: {
9258  auto *From = cast<AlignValueAttr>(FromAttr);
9259  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getAlignment()).value());
9260  break;
9261  }
9262 
9263  case attr::Format: {
9264  const auto *From = cast<FormatAttr>(FromAttr);
9265  AI.importAttr(From, Import(From->getType()), From->getFormatIdx(),
9266  From->getFirstArg());
9267  break;
9268  }
9269 
9270  case attr::EnableIf: {
9271  const auto *From = cast<EnableIfAttr>(FromAttr);
9272  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getCond()).value(),
9273  From->getMessage());
9274  break;
9275  }
9276 
9277  case attr::AssertCapability: {
9278  const auto *From = cast<AssertCapabilityAttr>(FromAttr);
9279  AI.importAttr(From,
9280  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9281  From->args_size());
9282  break;
9283  }
9284  case attr::AcquireCapability: {
9285  const auto *From = cast<AcquireCapabilityAttr>(FromAttr);
9286  AI.importAttr(From,
9287  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9288  From->args_size());
9289  break;
9290  }
9291  case attr::TryAcquireCapability: {
9292  const auto *From = cast<TryAcquireCapabilityAttr>(FromAttr);
9293  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getSuccessValue()).value(),
9294  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9295  From->args_size());
9296  break;
9297  }
9298  case attr::ReleaseCapability: {
9299  const auto *From = cast<ReleaseCapabilityAttr>(FromAttr);
9300  AI.importAttr(From,
9301  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9302  From->args_size());
9303  break;
9304  }
9305  case attr::RequiresCapability: {
9306  const auto *From = cast<RequiresCapabilityAttr>(FromAttr);
9307  AI.importAttr(From,
9308  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9309  From->args_size());
9310  break;
9311  }
9312  case attr::GuardedBy: {
9313  const auto *From = cast<GuardedByAttr>(FromAttr);
9314  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getArg()).value());
9315  break;
9316  }
9317  case attr::PtGuardedBy: {
9318  const auto *From = cast<PtGuardedByAttr>(FromAttr);
9319  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getArg()).value());
9320  break;
9321  }
9322  case attr::AcquiredAfter: {
9323  const auto *From = cast<AcquiredAfterAttr>(FromAttr);
9324  AI.importAttr(From,
9325  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9326  From->args_size());
9327  break;
9328  }
9329  case attr::AcquiredBefore: {
9330  const auto *From = cast<AcquiredBeforeAttr>(FromAttr);
9331  AI.importAttr(From,
9332  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9333  From->args_size());
9334  break;
9335  }
9336  case attr::AssertExclusiveLock: {
9337  const auto *From = cast<AssertExclusiveLockAttr>(FromAttr);
9338  AI.importAttr(From,
9339  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9340  From->args_size());
9341  break;
9342  }
9343  case attr::AssertSharedLock: {
9344  const auto *From = cast<AssertSharedLockAttr>(FromAttr);
9345  AI.importAttr(From,
9346  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9347  From->args_size());
9348  break;
9349  }
9350  case attr::ExclusiveTrylockFunction: {
9351  const auto *From = cast<ExclusiveTrylockFunctionAttr>(FromAttr);
9352  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getSuccessValue()).value(),
9353  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9354  From->args_size());
9355  break;
9356  }
9357  case attr::SharedTrylockFunction: {
9358  const auto *From = cast<SharedTrylockFunctionAttr>(FromAttr);
9359  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getSuccessValue()).value(),
9360  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9361  From->args_size());
9362  break;
9363  }
9364  case attr::LockReturned: {
9365  const auto *From = cast<LockReturnedAttr>(FromAttr);
9366  AI.importAttr(From, AI.importArg(From->getArg()).value());
9367  break;
9368  }
9369  case attr::LocksExcluded: {
9370  const auto *From = cast<LocksExcludedAttr>(FromAttr);
9371  AI.importAttr(From,
9372  AI.importArrayArg(From->args(), From->args_size()).value(),
9373  From->args_size());
9374  break;
9375  }
9376  default: {
9377  // The default branch works for attributes that have no arguments to import.
9378  // FIXME: Handle every attribute type that has arguments of type to import
9379  // (most often Expr* or Decl* or type) in the switch above.
9380  AI.cloneAttr(FromAttr);
9381  break;
9382  }
9383  }
9384 
9385  return std::move(AI).getResult();
9386 }

9399 Error ASTImporter::ImportAttrs(Decl *ToD, Decl *FromD) {
9400  if (!FromD->hasAttrs() || ToD->hasAttrs())
9401  return Error::success();
9402  for (const Attr *FromAttr : FromD->getAttrs()) {
9403  auto ToAttrOrErr = Import(FromAttr);
9404  if (ToAttrOrErr)
9405  ToD->addAttr(*ToAttrOrErr);
9406  else
9407  return ToAttrOrErr.takeError();
9408  }
9409  return Error::success();
9410 }
9411 
9412 Expected<Decl *> ASTImporter::Import(Decl *FromD) {
9413  if (!FromD)
9414  return nullptr;
9415 
9416  // Push FromD to the stack, and remove that when we return.
9417  ImportPath.push(FromD);
9418  auto ImportPathBuilder =
9419  llvm::make_scope_exit([this]() { ImportPath.pop(); });
9420 
9421  // Check whether there was a previous failed import.
9422  // If yes return the existing error.
9423  if (auto Error = getImportDeclErrorIfAny(FromD))
9424  return make_error<ASTImportError>(*Error);
9425 
9426  // Check whether we've already imported this declaration.
9427  Decl *ToD = GetAlreadyImportedOrNull(FromD);
9428  if (ToD) {
9429  // Already imported (possibly from another TU) and with an error.
9430  if (auto Error = SharedState->getImportDeclErrorIfAny(ToD)) {
9431  setImportDeclError(FromD, *Error);
9432  return make_error<ASTImportError>(*Error);
9433  }
9434 
9435  // If FromD has some updated flags after last import, apply it.
9436  updateFlags(FromD, ToD);
9437  // If we encounter a cycle during an import then we save the relevant part
9438  // of the import path associated to the Decl.
9439  if (ImportPath.hasCycleAtBack())
9440  SavedImportPaths[FromD].push_back(ImportPath.copyCycleAtBack());
9441  return ToD;
9442  }
9443 
9444  // Import the declaration.
9445  ExpectedDecl ToDOrErr = ImportImpl(FromD);
9446  if (!ToDOrErr) {
9447  // Failed to import.
9448 
9449  auto Pos = ImportedDecls.find(FromD);
9450  if (Pos != ImportedDecls.end()) {
9451  // Import failed after the object was created.
9452  // Remove all references to it.
9453  auto *ToD = Pos->second;
9454  ImportedDecls.erase(Pos);
9455 
9456  // ImportedDecls and ImportedFromDecls are not symmetric. It may happen
9457  // (e.g. with namespaces) that several decls from the 'from' context are
9458  // mapped to the same decl in the 'to' context. If we removed entries
9459  // from the LookupTable here then we may end up removing them multiple
9460  // times.
9461 
9462  // The Lookuptable contains decls only which are in the 'to' context.
9463  // Remove from the Lookuptable only if it is *imported* into the 'to'
9464  // context (and do not remove it if it was added during the initial
9465  // traverse of the 'to' context).
9466  auto PosF = ImportedFromDecls.find(ToD);
9467  if (PosF != ImportedFromDecls.end()) {
9468  // In the case of TypedefNameDecl we create the Decl first and only
9469  // then we import and set its DeclContext. So, the DC might not be set
9470  // when we reach here.
9471  if (ToD->getDeclContext())
9472  SharedState->removeDeclFromLookup(ToD);
9473  ImportedFromDecls.erase(PosF);
9474  }
9475 
9476  // FIXME: AST may contain remaining references to the failed object.
9477  // However, the ImportDeclErrors in the shared state contains all the
9478  // failed objects together with their error.
9479  }
9480 
9481  // Error encountered for the first time.
9482  // After takeError the error is not usable any more in ToDOrErr.
9483  // Get a copy of the error object (any more simple solution for this?).
9484  ASTImportError ErrOut;
9485  handleAllErrors(ToDOrErr.takeError(),
9486  [&ErrOut](const ASTImportError &E) { ErrOut = E; });
9487  setImportDeclError(FromD, ErrOut);
9488  // Set the error for the mapped to Decl, which is in the "to" context.
9489  if (Pos != ImportedDecls.end())
9490  SharedState->setImportDeclError(Pos->second, ErrOut);
9491 
9492  // Set the error for all nodes which have been created before we
9493  // recognized the error.
9494  for (const auto &Path : SavedImportPaths[FromD]) {
9495  // The import path contains import-dependency nodes first.
9496  // Save the node that was imported as dependency of the current node.
9497  Decl *PrevFromDi = FromD;
9498  for (Decl *FromDi : Path) {
9499  // Begin and end of the path equals 'FromD', skip it.
9500  if (FromDi == FromD)
9501  continue;
9502  // We should not set import error on a node and all following nodes in
9503  // the path if child import errors are ignored.
9504  if (ChildErrorHandlingStrategy(FromDi).ignoreChildErrorOnParent(
9505  PrevFromDi))
9506  break;
9507  PrevFromDi = FromDi;
9508  setImportDeclError(FromDi, ErrOut);
9509  //FIXME Should we remove these Decls from ImportedDecls?
9510  // Set the error for the mapped to Decl, which is in the "to" context.
9511  auto Ii = ImportedDecls.find(FromDi);
9512  if (Ii != ImportedDecls.end())
9513  SharedState->setImportDeclError(Ii->second, ErrOut);
9514  // FIXME Should we remove these Decls from the LookupTable,
9515  // and from ImportedFromDecls?
9516  }
9517  }
9518  SavedImportPaths.erase(FromD);
9519 
9520  // Do not return ToDOrErr, error was taken out of it.
9521  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ErrOut);
9522  }
9523 
9524  ToD = *ToDOrErr;
9525 
9526  // FIXME: Handle the "already imported with error" case. We can get here
9527  // nullptr only if GetImportedOrCreateDecl returned nullptr (after a
9528  // previously failed create was requested).
9529  // Later GetImportedOrCreateDecl can be updated to return the error.
9530  if (!ToD) {
9531  auto Err = getImportDeclErrorIfAny(FromD);
9532  assert(Err);
9533  return make_error<ASTImportError>(*Err);
9534  }
9535 
9536  // We could import from the current TU without error. But previously we
9537  // already had imported a Decl as `ToD` from another TU (with another
9538  // ASTImporter object) and with an error.
9539  if (auto Error = SharedState->getImportDeclErrorIfAny(ToD)) {
9540  setImportDeclError(FromD, *Error);
9541  return make_error<ASTImportError>(*Error);
9542  }
9543  // Make sure that ImportImpl registered the imported decl.
9544  assert(ImportedDecls.count(FromD) != 0 && "Missing call to MapImported?");
9545  if (auto Error = ImportAttrs(ToD, FromD))
9546  return std::move(Error);
9547 
9548  // Notify subclasses.
9549  Imported(FromD, ToD);
9550 
9551  updateFlags(FromD, ToD);
9552  SavedImportPaths.erase(FromD);
9553  return ToDOrErr;
9554 }

9557 ASTImporter::Import(const InheritedConstructor &From) {

9561 Expected<DeclContext *> ASTImporter::ImportContext(DeclContext *FromDC) {
9562  if (!FromDC)
9563  return FromDC;
9564 
9565  ExpectedDecl ToDCOrErr = Import(cast<Decl>(FromDC));
9566  if (!ToDCOrErr)
9567  return ToDCOrErr.takeError();
9568  auto *ToDC = cast<DeclContext>(*ToDCOrErr);
9569 
9570  // When we're using a record/enum/Objective-C class/protocol as a context, we
9571  // need it to have a definition.
9572  if (auto *ToRecord = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(ToDC)) {
9573  auto *FromRecord = cast<RecordDecl>(FromDC);
9574  if (ToRecord->isCompleteDefinition())
9575  return ToDC;
9576 
9577  // If FromRecord is not defined we need to force it to be.
9578  // Simply calling CompleteDecl(...) for a RecordDecl will break some cases
9579  // it will start the definition but we never finish it.
9580  // If there are base classes they won't be imported and we will
9581  // be missing anything that we inherit from those bases.
9582  if (FromRecord->getASTContext().getExternalSource() &&
9583  !FromRecord->isCompleteDefinition())
9584  FromRecord->getASTContext().getExternalSource()->CompleteType(FromRecord);
9585 
9586  if (FromRecord->isCompleteDefinition())
9587  if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
9588  FromRecord, ToRecord, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
9589  return std::move(Err);
9590  } else if (auto *ToEnum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(ToDC)) {
9591  auto *FromEnum = cast<EnumDecl>(FromDC);
9592  if (ToEnum->isCompleteDefinition()) {
9593  // Do nothing.
9594  } else if (FromEnum->isCompleteDefinition()) {
9595  if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
9596  FromEnum, ToEnum, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
9597  return std::move(Err);
9598  } else {
9599  CompleteDecl(ToEnum);
9600  }
9601  } else if (auto *ToClass = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(ToDC)) {
9602  auto *FromClass = cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(FromDC);
9603  if (ToClass->getDefinition()) {
9604  // Do nothing.
9605  } else if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *FromDef = FromClass->getDefinition()) {
9606  if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
9607  FromDef, ToClass, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
9608  return std::move(Err);
9609  } else {
9610  CompleteDecl(ToClass);
9611  }
9612  } else if (auto *ToProto = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(ToDC)) {
9613  auto *FromProto = cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(FromDC);
9614  if (ToProto->getDefinition()) {
9615  // Do nothing.
9616  } else if (ObjCProtocolDecl *FromDef = FromProto->getDefinition()) {
9617  if (Error Err = ASTNodeImporter(*this).ImportDefinition(
9618  FromDef, ToProto, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Basic))
9619  return std::move(Err);
9620  } else {
9621  CompleteDecl(ToProto);
9622  }
9623  }
9624 
9625  return ToDC;
9626 }

9628 Expected<Expr *> ASTImporter::Import(Expr *FromE) {
9629  if (ExpectedStmt ToSOrErr = Import(cast_or_null<Stmt>(FromE)))
9630  return cast_or_null<Expr>(*ToSOrErr);
9631  else
9632  return ToSOrErr.takeError();
9633 }
9634 
9635 Expected<Stmt *> ASTImporter::Import(Stmt *FromS) {
9636  if (!FromS)
9637  return nullptr;
9638 
9639  // Check whether we've already imported this statement.
9640  llvm::DenseMap<Stmt *, Stmt *>::iterator Pos = ImportedStmts.find(FromS);
9641  if (Pos != ImportedStmts.end())
9642  return Pos->second;
9643 
9644  // Import the statement.
9645  ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
9646  ExpectedStmt ToSOrErr = Importer.Visit(FromS);
9647  if (!ToSOrErr)
9648  return ToSOrErr;
9649 
9650  if (auto *ToE = dyn_cast<Expr>(*ToSOrErr)) {
9651  auto *FromE = cast<Expr>(FromS);
9652  // Copy ExprBitfields, which may not be handled in Expr subclasses
9653  // constructors.
9654  ToE->setValueKind(FromE->getValueKind());
9655  ToE->setObjectKind(FromE->getObjectKind());
9656  ToE->setDependence(FromE->getDependence());
9657  }
9658 
9659  // Record the imported statement object.
9660  ImportedStmts[FromS] = *ToSOrErr;
9661  return ToSOrErr;
9662 }
9663 
9664 Expected<NestedNameSpecifier *>
9665 ASTImporter::Import(NestedNameSpecifier *FromNNS) {
9666  if (!FromNNS)
9667  return nullptr;
9668 
9669  NestedNameSpecifier *Prefix = nullptr;
9670  if (Error Err = importInto(Prefix, FromNNS->getPrefix()))
9671  return std::move(Err);
9672 
9673  switch (FromNNS->getKind()) {
9674  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
9675  assert(FromNNS->getAsIdentifier() && "NNS should contain identifier.");
9676  return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix,
9677  Import(FromNNS->getAsIdentifier()));
9678 
9679  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
9680  if (ExpectedDecl NSOrErr = Import(FromNNS->getAsNamespace())) {
9681  return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix,
9682  cast<NamespaceDecl>(*NSOrErr));
9683  } else
9684  return NSOrErr.takeError();
9685 
9686  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
9687  if (ExpectedDecl NSADOrErr = Import(FromNNS->getAsNamespaceAlias()))
9688  return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix,
9689  cast<NamespaceAliasDecl>(*NSADOrErr));
9690  else
9691  return NSADOrErr.takeError();
9692 
9693  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
9694  return NestedNameSpecifier::GlobalSpecifier(ToContext);
9695 
9696  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
9697  if (ExpectedDecl RDOrErr = Import(FromNNS->getAsRecordDecl()))
9698  return NestedNameSpecifier::SuperSpecifier(ToContext,
9699  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(*RDOrErr));
9700  else
9701  return RDOrErr.takeError();
9702 
9703  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
9704  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
9705  if (ExpectedTypePtr TyOrErr = Import(FromNNS->getAsType())) {
9706  bool TSTemplate =
9707  FromNNS->getKind() == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate;
9708  return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(ToContext, Prefix, TSTemplate,
9709  *TyOrErr);
9710  } else {
9711  return TyOrErr.takeError();
9712  }
9713  }
9714 
9715  llvm_unreachable("Invalid nested name specifier kind");
9716 }
9717 
9718 Expected<NestedNameSpecifierLoc>
9719 ASTImporter::Import(NestedNameSpecifierLoc FromNNS) {
9720  // Copied from NestedNameSpecifier mostly.
9721  SmallVector<NestedNameSpecifierLoc , 8> NestedNames;
9722  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNS = FromNNS;
9723 
9724  // Push each of the nested-name-specifiers's onto a stack for
9725  // serialization in reverse order.
9726  while (NNS) {
9727  NestedNames.push_back(NNS);
9728  NNS = NNS.getPrefix();
9729  }
9730 
9731  NestedNameSpecifierLocBuilder Builder;
9732 
9733  while (!NestedNames.empty()) {
9734  NNS = NestedNames.pop_back_val();
9735  NestedNameSpecifier *Spec = nullptr;
9736  if (Error Err = importInto(Spec, NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()))
9737  return std::move(Err);
9738 
9739  NestedNameSpecifier::SpecifierKind Kind = Spec->getKind();
9740 
9741  SourceLocation ToLocalBeginLoc, ToLocalEndLoc;
9742  if (Kind != NestedNameSpecifier::Super) {
9743  if (Error Err = importInto(ToLocalBeginLoc, NNS.getLocalBeginLoc()))
9744  return std::move(Err);
9745 
9746  if (Kind != NestedNameSpecifier::Global)
9747  if (Error Err = importInto(ToLocalEndLoc, NNS.getLocalEndLoc()))
9748  return std::move(Err);
9749  }
9750 
9751  switch (Kind) {
9752  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
9753  Builder.Extend(getToContext(), Spec->getAsIdentifier(), ToLocalBeginLoc,
9754  ToLocalEndLoc);
9755  break;
9756 
9757  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
9758  Builder.Extend(getToContext(), Spec->getAsNamespace(), ToLocalBeginLoc,
9759  ToLocalEndLoc);
9760  break;
9761 
9762  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
9763  Builder.Extend(getToContext(), Spec->getAsNamespaceAlias(),
9764  ToLocalBeginLoc, ToLocalEndLoc);
9765  break;
9766 
9767  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
9768  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate: {
9769  SourceLocation ToTLoc;
9770  if (Error Err = importInto(ToTLoc, NNS.getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc()))
9771  return std::move(Err);
9772  TypeSourceInfo *TSI = getToContext().getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(
9773  QualType(Spec->getAsType(), 0), ToTLoc);
9774  if (Kind == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate)
9775  // ToLocalBeginLoc is here the location of the 'template' keyword.
9776  Builder.Extend(getToContext(), ToLocalBeginLoc, TSI->getTypeLoc(),
9777  ToLocalEndLoc);
9778  else
9779  // No location for 'template' keyword here.
9780  Builder.Extend(getToContext(), SourceLocation{}, TSI->getTypeLoc(),
9781  ToLocalEndLoc);
9782  break;
9783  }
9784 
9785  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
9786  Builder.MakeGlobal(getToContext(), ToLocalBeginLoc);
9787  break;
9788 
9789  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super: {
9790  auto ToSourceRangeOrErr = Import(NNS.getSourceRange());
9791  if (!ToSourceRangeOrErr)
9792  return ToSourceRangeOrErr.takeError();
9793 
9794  Builder.MakeSuper(getToContext(), Spec->getAsRecordDecl(),
9795  ToSourceRangeOrErr->getBegin(),
9796  ToSourceRangeOrErr->getEnd());
9797  }
9798  }
9799  }
9800 
9801  return Builder.getWithLocInContext(getToContext());
9802 }
9803 
9804 Expected<TemplateName> ASTImporter::Import(TemplateName From) {
9805  switch (From.getKind()) {
9806  case TemplateName::Template:
9807  if (ExpectedDecl ToTemplateOrErr = Import(From.getAsTemplateDecl()))
9808  return TemplateName(cast<TemplateDecl>((*ToTemplateOrErr)->getCanonicalDecl()));
9809  else
9810  return ToTemplateOrErr.takeError();
9811 
9812  case TemplateName::OverloadedTemplate: {
9813  OverloadedTemplateStorage *FromStorage = From.getAsOverloadedTemplate();
9814  UnresolvedSet<2> ToTemplates;
9815  for (auto *I : *FromStorage) {
9816  if (auto ToOrErr = Import(I))
9817  ToTemplates.addDecl(cast<NamedDecl>(*ToOrErr));
9818  else
9819  return ToOrErr.takeError();
9820  }
9821  return ToContext.getOverloadedTemplateName(ToTemplates.begin(),
9822  ToTemplates.end());
9823  }
9824 
9825  case TemplateName::AssumedTemplate: {
9826  AssumedTemplateStorage *FromStorage = From.getAsAssumedTemplateName();
9827  auto DeclNameOrErr = Import(FromStorage->getDeclName());
9828  if (!DeclNameOrErr)
9829  return DeclNameOrErr.takeError();
9830  return ToContext.getAssumedTemplateName(*DeclNameOrErr);
9831  }
9832 
9833  case TemplateName::QualifiedTemplate: {
9834  QualifiedTemplateName *QTN = From.getAsQualifiedTemplateName();
9835  auto QualifierOrErr = Import(QTN->getQualifier());
9836  if (!QualifierOrErr)
9837  return QualifierOrErr.takeError();
9838  auto TNOrErr = Import(QTN->getUnderlyingTemplate());
9839  if (!TNOrErr)
9840  return TNOrErr.takeError();
9841  return ToContext.getQualifiedTemplateName(
9842  *QualifierOrErr, QTN->hasTemplateKeyword(), *TNOrErr);
9843  }
9844 
9845  case TemplateName::DependentTemplate: {
9846  DependentTemplateName *DTN = From.getAsDependentTemplateName();
9847  auto QualifierOrErr = Import(DTN->getQualifier());
9848  if (!QualifierOrErr)
9849  return QualifierOrErr.takeError();
9850 
9851  if (DTN->isIdentifier()) {
9852  return ToContext.getDependentTemplateName(*QualifierOrErr,
9853  Import(DTN->getIdentifier()));
9854  }
9855 
9856  return ToContext.getDependentTemplateName(*QualifierOrErr,
9857  DTN->getOperator());
9858  }
9859 
9860  case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParm: {
9861  SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage *Subst =
9862  From.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParm();
9863  auto ReplacementOrErr = Import(Subst->getReplacement());
9864  if (!ReplacementOrErr)
9865  return ReplacementOrErr.takeError();
9866 
9867  auto AssociatedDeclOrErr = Import(Subst->getAssociatedDecl());
9868  if (!AssociatedDeclOrErr)
9869  return AssociatedDeclOrErr.takeError();
9870 
9871  return ToContext.getSubstTemplateTemplateParm(
9872  *ReplacementOrErr, *AssociatedDeclOrErr, Subst->getIndex(),
9873  Subst->getPackIndex());
9874  }
9875 
9876  case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParmPack: {
9877  SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage *SubstPack =
9878  From.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack();
9879  ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
9880  auto ArgPackOrErr =
9881  Importer.ImportTemplateArgument(SubstPack->getArgumentPack());
9882  if (!ArgPackOrErr)
9883  return ArgPackOrErr.takeError();
9884 
9885  auto AssociatedDeclOrErr = Import(SubstPack->getAssociatedDecl());
9886  if (!AssociatedDeclOrErr)
9887  return AssociatedDeclOrErr.takeError();
9888 
9889  return ToContext.getSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack(
9890  *ArgPackOrErr, *AssociatedDeclOrErr, SubstPack->getIndex(),
9891  SubstPack->getFinal());
9892  }
9893  case TemplateName::UsingTemplate: {
9894  auto UsingOrError = Import(From.getAsUsingShadowDecl());
9895  if (!UsingOrError)
9896  return UsingOrError.takeError();
9897  return TemplateName(cast<UsingShadowDecl>(*UsingOrError));
9898  }
9899  }
9900 
9901  llvm_unreachable("Invalid template name kind");
9902 }

9904 Expected<SourceLocation> ASTImporter::Import(SourceLocation FromLoc) {
9905  if (FromLoc.isInvalid())
9906  return SourceLocation{};
9907 
9908  SourceManager &FromSM = FromContext.getSourceManager();
9909  bool IsBuiltin = FromSM.isWrittenInBuiltinFile(FromLoc);
9910 
9911  std::pair<FileID, unsigned> Decomposed = FromSM.getDecomposedLoc(FromLoc);
9912  Expected<FileID> ToFileIDOrErr = Import(Decomposed.first, IsBuiltin);
9913  if (!ToFileIDOrErr)
9914  return ToFileIDOrErr.takeError();
9915  SourceManager &ToSM = ToContext.getSourceManager();
9916  return ToSM.getComposedLoc(*ToFileIDOrErr, Decomposed.second);
9917 }

9919 Expected<SourceRange> ASTImporter::Import(SourceRange FromRange) {
9920  SourceLocation ToBegin, ToEnd;
9921  if (Error Err = importInto(ToBegin, FromRange.getBegin()))
9922  return std::move(Err);
9923  if (Error Err = importInto(ToEnd, FromRange.getEnd()))
9924  return std::move(Err);
9925 
9926  return SourceRange(ToBegin, ToEnd);
9927 }
9928 
9929 Expected<FileID> ASTImporter::Import(FileID FromID, bool IsBuiltin) {
9930  llvm::DenseMap<FileID, FileID>::iterator Pos = ImportedFileIDs.find(FromID);
9931  if (Pos != ImportedFileIDs.end())
9932  return Pos->second;
9933 
9934  SourceManager &FromSM = FromContext.getSourceManager();
9935  SourceManager &ToSM = ToContext.getSourceManager();
9936  const SrcMgr::SLocEntry &FromSLoc = FromSM.getSLocEntry(FromID);
9937 
9938  // Map the FromID to the "to" source manager.
9939  FileID ToID;
9940  if (FromSLoc.isExpansion()) {
9941  const SrcMgr::ExpansionInfo &FromEx = FromSLoc.getExpansion();
9942  ExpectedSLoc ToSpLoc = Import(FromEx.getSpellingLoc());
9943  if (!ToSpLoc)
9944  return ToSpLoc.takeError();
9945  ExpectedSLoc ToExLocS = Import(FromEx.getExpansionLocStart());
9946  if (!ToExLocS)
9947  return ToExLocS.takeError();
9948  unsigned ExLength = FromSM.getFileIDSize(FromID);
9949  SourceLocation MLoc;
9950  if (FromEx.isMacroArgExpansion()) {
9951  MLoc = ToSM.createMacroArgExpansionLoc(*ToSpLoc, *ToExLocS, ExLength);
9952  } else {
9953  if (ExpectedSLoc ToExLocE = Import(FromEx.getExpansionLocEnd()))
9954  MLoc = ToSM.createExpansionLoc(*ToSpLoc, *ToExLocS, *ToExLocE, ExLength,
9955  FromEx.isExpansionTokenRange());
9956  else
9957  return ToExLocE.takeError();
9958  }
9959  ToID = ToSM.getFileID(MLoc);
9960  } else {
9961  const SrcMgr::ContentCache *Cache = &FromSLoc.getFile().getContentCache();
9962 
9963  if (!IsBuiltin && !Cache->BufferOverridden) {
9964  // Include location of this file.
9965  ExpectedSLoc ToIncludeLoc = Import(FromSLoc.getFile().getIncludeLoc());
9966  if (!ToIncludeLoc)
9967  return ToIncludeLoc.takeError();
9968 
9969  // Every FileID that is not the main FileID needs to have a valid include
9970  // location so that the include chain points to the main FileID. When
9971  // importing the main FileID (which has no include location), we need to
9972  // create a fake include location in the main file to keep this property
9973  // intact.
9974  SourceLocation ToIncludeLocOrFakeLoc = *ToIncludeLoc;
9975  if (FromID == FromSM.getMainFileID())
9976  ToIncludeLocOrFakeLoc = ToSM.getLocForStartOfFile(ToSM.getMainFileID());
9977 
9978  if (Cache->OrigEntry && Cache->OrigEntry->getDir()) {
9979  // FIXME: We probably want to use getVirtualFile(), so we don't hit the
9980  // disk again
9981  // FIXME: We definitely want to re-use the existing MemoryBuffer, rather
9982  // than mmap the files several times.
9983  auto Entry =
9984  ToFileManager.getOptionalFileRef(Cache->OrigEntry->getName());
9985  // FIXME: The filename may be a virtual name that does probably not
9986  // point to a valid file and we get no Entry here. In this case try with
9987  // the memory buffer below.
9988  if (Entry)
9989  ToID = ToSM.createFileID(*Entry, ToIncludeLocOrFakeLoc,
9990  FromSLoc.getFile().getFileCharacteristic());
9991  }
9992  }
9993 
9994  if (ToID.isInvalid() || IsBuiltin) {
9995  // FIXME: We want to re-use the existing MemoryBuffer!
9996  std::optional<llvm::MemoryBufferRef> FromBuf =
9997  Cache->getBufferOrNone(FromContext.getDiagnostics(),
9998  FromSM.getFileManager(), SourceLocation{});
9999  if (!FromBuf)
10000  return llvm::make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::Unknown);
10001 
10002  std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer> ToBuf =
10003  llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(FromBuf->getBuffer(),
10004  FromBuf->getBufferIdentifier());
10005  ToID = ToSM.createFileID(std::move(ToBuf),
10006  FromSLoc.getFile().getFileCharacteristic());
10007  }
10008  }
10009 
10010  assert(ToID.isValid() && "Unexpected invalid fileID was created.");
10011 
10012  ImportedFileIDs[FromID] = ToID;
10013  return ToID;
10014 }

10016 Expected<CXXCtorInitializer *> ASTImporter::Import(CXXCtorInitializer *From) {
10017  ExpectedExpr ToExprOrErr = Import(From->getInit());
10018  if (!ToExprOrErr)
10019  return ToExprOrErr.takeError();
10020 
10021  auto LParenLocOrErr = Import(From->getLParenLoc());
10022  if (!LParenLocOrErr)
10023  return LParenLocOrErr.takeError();
10024 
10025  auto RParenLocOrErr = Import(From->getRParenLoc());
10026  if (!RParenLocOrErr)
10027  return RParenLocOrErr.takeError();
10028 
10029  if (From->isBaseInitializer()) {
10030  auto ToTInfoOrErr = Import(From->getTypeSourceInfo());
10031  if (!ToTInfoOrErr)
10032  return ToTInfoOrErr.takeError();
10033 
10034  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
10035  if (From->isPackExpansion())
10036  if (Error Err = importInto(EllipsisLoc, From->getEllipsisLoc()))
10037  return std::move(Err);
10038 
10039  return new (ToContext) CXXCtorInitializer(
10040  ToContext, *ToTInfoOrErr, From->isBaseVirtual(), *LParenLocOrErr,
10041  *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr, EllipsisLoc);
10042  } else if (From->isMemberInitializer()) {
10043  ExpectedDecl ToFieldOrErr = Import(From->getMember());
10044  if (!ToFieldOrErr)
10045  return ToFieldOrErr.takeError();
10046 
10047  auto MemberLocOrErr = Import(From->getMemberLocation());
10048  if (!MemberLocOrErr)
10049  return MemberLocOrErr.takeError();
10050 
10051  return new (ToContext) CXXCtorInitializer(
10052  ToContext, cast_or_null<FieldDecl>(*ToFieldOrErr), *MemberLocOrErr,
10053  *LParenLocOrErr, *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr);
10054  } else if (From->isIndirectMemberInitializer()) {
10055  ExpectedDecl ToIFieldOrErr = Import(From->getIndirectMember());
10056  if (!ToIFieldOrErr)
10057  return ToIFieldOrErr.takeError();
10058 
10059  auto MemberLocOrErr = Import(From->getMemberLocation());
10060  if (!MemberLocOrErr)
10061  return MemberLocOrErr.takeError();
10062 
10063  return new (ToContext) CXXCtorInitializer(
10064  ToContext, cast_or_null<IndirectFieldDecl>(*ToIFieldOrErr),
10065  *MemberLocOrErr, *LParenLocOrErr, *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr);
10066  } else if (From->isDelegatingInitializer()) {
10067  auto ToTInfoOrErr = Import(From->getTypeSourceInfo());
10068  if (!ToTInfoOrErr)
10069  return ToTInfoOrErr.takeError();
10070 
10071  return new (ToContext)
10072  CXXCtorInitializer(ToContext, *ToTInfoOrErr, *LParenLocOrErr,
10073  *ToExprOrErr, *RParenLocOrErr);
10074  } else {
10075  // FIXME: assert?
10076  return make_error<ASTImportError>();
10077  }
10078 }

10080 Expected<CXXBaseSpecifier *>
10081 ASTImporter::Import(const CXXBaseSpecifier *BaseSpec) {
10082  auto Pos = ImportedCXXBaseSpecifiers.find(BaseSpec);
10083  if (Pos != ImportedCXXBaseSpecifiers.end())
10084  return Pos->second;
10085 
10086  Expected<SourceRange> ToSourceRange = Import(BaseSpec->getSourceRange());
10087  if (!ToSourceRange)
10088  return ToSourceRange.takeError();

10093  if (!ToEllipsisLoc)
10094  return ToEllipsisLoc.takeError();

10096  *ToSourceRange, BaseSpec->isVirtual(), BaseSpec->isBaseOfClass(),
10097  BaseSpec->getAccessSpecifierAsWritten(), *ToTSI, *ToEllipsisLoc);
10098  ImportedCXXBaseSpecifiers[BaseSpec] = Imported;

10107 Error ASTImporter::ImportDefinition(Decl *From) {
10108  ExpectedDecl ToOrErr = Import(From);
10109  if (!ToOrErr)
10110  return ToOrErr.takeError();
10111  Decl *To = *ToOrErr;
10112 
10113  auto *FromDC = cast<DeclContext>(From);
10114  ASTNodeImporter Importer(*this);
10115 
10116  if (auto *ToRecord = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(To)) {
10117  if (!ToRecord->getDefinition()) {
10118  return Importer.ImportDefinition(
10119  cast<RecordDecl>(FromDC), ToRecord,
10120  ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
10121  }
10122  }
10123 
10124  if (auto *ToEnum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(To)) {
10125  if (!ToEnum->getDefinition()) {
10126  return Importer.ImportDefinition(
10127  cast<EnumDecl>(FromDC), ToEnum, ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
10128  }
10129  }
10130 
10131  if (auto *ToIFace = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(To)) {
10132  if (!ToIFace->getDefinition()) {
10133  return Importer.ImportDefinition(
10134  cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(FromDC), ToIFace,
10135  ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
10136  }
10137  }
10138 
10139  if (auto *ToProto = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(To)) {
10140  if (!ToProto->getDefinition()) {
10141  return Importer.ImportDefinition(
10142  cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(FromDC), ToProto,
10143  ASTNodeImporter::IDK_Everything);
10144  }
10145  }
10146 
10147  return Importer.ImportDeclContext(FromDC, true);
10148 }

10150 Expected<DeclarationName> ASTImporter::Import(DeclarationName FromName) {
10151  if (!FromName)
10152  return DeclarationName{};
10153 
10154  switch (FromName.getNameKind()) {
10155  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
10156  return DeclarationName(Import(FromName.getAsIdentifierInfo()));
10157 
10158  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
10159  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
10160  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
10161  if (auto ToSelOrErr = Import(FromName.getObjCSelector()))
10162  return DeclarationName(*ToSelOrErr);
10163  else
10164  return ToSelOrErr.takeError();
10165 
10166  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName: {
10167  if (auto ToTyOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXNameType()))
10168  return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXConstructorName(
10169  ToContext.getCanonicalType(*ToTyOrErr));
10170  else
10171  return ToTyOrErr.takeError();
10172  }
10173 
10174  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName: {
10175  if (auto ToTyOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXNameType()))
10176  return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXDestructorName(
10177  ToContext.getCanonicalType(*ToTyOrErr));
10178  else
10179  return ToTyOrErr.takeError();
10180  }
10181 
10182  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName: {
10183  if (auto ToTemplateOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXDeductionGuideTemplate()))
10184  return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXDeductionGuideName(
10185  cast<TemplateDecl>(*ToTemplateOrErr));
10186  else
10187  return ToTemplateOrErr.takeError();
10188  }
10189 
10190  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName: {
10191  if (auto ToTyOrErr = Import(FromName.getCXXNameType()))
10192  return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXConversionFunctionName(
10193  ToContext.getCanonicalType(*ToTyOrErr));
10194  else
10195  return ToTyOrErr.takeError();
10196  }
10197 
10198  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
10199  return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(
10200  FromName.getCXXOverloadedOperator());
10201 
10202  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
10203  return ToContext.DeclarationNames.getCXXLiteralOperatorName(
10204  Import(FromName.getCXXLiteralIdentifier()));
10205 
10206  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
10207  // FIXME: STATICS!
10208  return DeclarationName::getUsingDirectiveName();
10209  }
10210 
10211  llvm_unreachable("Invalid DeclarationName Kind!");
10212 }

10226 Expected<Selector> ASTImporter::Import(Selector FromSel) {
10227  if (FromSel.isNull())
10228  return Selector{};
10229 
10230  SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo *, 4> Idents;
10231  Idents.push_back(Import(FromSel.getIdentifierInfoForSlot(0)));
10232  for (unsigned I = 1, N = FromSel.getNumArgs(); I < N; ++I)
10233  Idents.push_back(Import(FromSel.getIdentifierInfoForSlot(I)));
10234  return ToContext.Selectors.getSelector(FromSel.getNumArgs(), Idents.data());
10235 }

10237 llvm::Expected<APValue>
10238 ASTNodeImporter::ImportAPValue(const APValue &FromValue) {
10239  APValue Result;
10240  llvm::Error Err = llvm::Error::success();
10241  auto ImportLoop = [&](const APValue *From, APValue *To, unsigned Size) {
10242  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < Size; Idx++) {
10243  APValue Tmp = importChecked(Err, From[Idx]);
10244  To[Idx] = Tmp;
10245  }
10246  };
10247  switch (FromValue.getKind()) {
10248  case APValue::None:
10249  case APValue::Indeterminate:
10250  case APValue::Int:
10251  case APValue::Float:
10252  case APValue::FixedPoint:
10253  case APValue::ComplexInt:
10254  case APValue::ComplexFloat:
10255  Result = FromValue;
10256  break;
10257  case APValue::Vector: {
10258  Result.MakeVector();
10259  MutableArrayRef<APValue> Elts =
10260  Result.setVectorUninit(FromValue.getVectorLength());
10261  ImportLoop(((const APValue::Vec *)(const char *)&FromValue.Data)->Elts,
10262  Elts.data(), FromValue.getVectorLength());
10263  break;
10264  }
10265  case APValue::Array:
10266  Result.MakeArray(FromValue.getArrayInitializedElts(),
10267  FromValue.getArraySize());
10268  ImportLoop(((const APValue::Arr *)(const char *)&FromValue.Data)->Elts,
10269  ((const APValue::Arr *)(const char *)&Result.Data)->Elts,
10270  FromValue.getArrayInitializedElts());
10271  break;
10272  case APValue::Struct:
10273  Result.MakeStruct(FromValue.getStructNumBases(),
10274  FromValue.getStructNumFields());
10275  ImportLoop(
10276  ((const APValue::StructData *)(const char *)&FromValue.Data)->Elts,
10277  ((const APValue::StructData *)(const char *)&Result.Data)->Elts,
10278  FromValue.getStructNumBases() + FromValue.getStructNumFields());
10279  break;
10280  case APValue::Union: {
10281  Result.MakeUnion();
10282  const Decl *ImpFDecl = importChecked(Err, FromValue.getUnionField());
10283  APValue ImpValue = importChecked(Err, FromValue.getUnionValue());
10284  if (Err)
10285  return std::move(Err);
10286  Result.setUnion(cast<FieldDecl>(ImpFDecl), ImpValue);
10287  break;
10288  }
10289  case APValue::AddrLabelDiff: {
10290  Result.MakeAddrLabelDiff();
10291  const Expr *ImpLHS = importChecked(Err, FromValue.getAddrLabelDiffLHS());
10292  const Expr *ImpRHS = importChecked(Err, FromValue.getAddrLabelDiffRHS());
10293  if (Err)
10294  return std::move(Err);
10295  Result.setAddrLabelDiff(cast<AddrLabelExpr>(ImpLHS),
10296  cast<AddrLabelExpr>(ImpRHS));
10297  break;
10298  }
10299  case APValue::MemberPointer: {
10300  const Decl *ImpMemPtrDecl =
10301  importChecked(Err, FromValue.getMemberPointerDecl());
10302  if (Err)
10303  return std::move(Err);
10304  MutableArrayRef<const CXXRecordDecl *> ToPath =
10305  Result.setMemberPointerUninit(
10306  cast<const ValueDecl>(ImpMemPtrDecl),
10307  FromValue.isMemberPointerToDerivedMember(),
10308  FromValue.getMemberPointerPath().size());
10309  llvm::ArrayRef<const CXXRecordDecl *> FromPath =
10310  Result.getMemberPointerPath();
10311  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < FromValue.getMemberPointerPath().size();
10312  Idx++) {
10313  const Decl *ImpDecl = importChecked(Err, FromPath[Idx]);
10314  if (Err)
10315  return std::move(Err);
10316  ToPath[Idx] = cast<const CXXRecordDecl>(ImpDecl->getCanonicalDecl());
10317  }
10318  break;
10319  }
10320  case APValue::LValue:
10321  APValue::LValueBase Base;
10322  QualType FromElemTy;
10323  if (FromValue.getLValueBase()) {
10324  assert(!FromValue.getLValueBase().is<DynamicAllocLValue>() &&
10325  "in C++20 dynamic allocation are transient so they shouldn't "
10326  "appear in the AST");
10327  if (!FromValue.getLValueBase().is<TypeInfoLValue>()) {
10328  if (const auto *E =
10329  FromValue.getLValueBase().dyn_cast<const Expr *>()) {
10330  FromElemTy = E->getType();
10331  const Expr *ImpExpr = importChecked(Err, E);
10332  if (Err)
10333  return std::move(Err);
10334  Base = APValue::LValueBase(ImpExpr,
10335  FromValue.getLValueBase().getCallIndex(),
10336  FromValue.getLValueBase().getVersion());
10337  } else {
10338  FromElemTy =
10339  FromValue.getLValueBase().get<const ValueDecl *>()->getType();
10340  const Decl *ImpDecl = importChecked(
10341  Err, FromValue.getLValueBase().get<const ValueDecl *>());
10342  if (Err)
10343  return std::move(Err);
10344  Base = APValue::LValueBase(cast<ValueDecl>(ImpDecl),
10345  FromValue.getLValueBase().getCallIndex(),
10346  FromValue.getLValueBase().getVersion());
10347  }
10348  } else {
10349  FromElemTy = FromValue.getLValueBase().getTypeInfoType();
10350  const Type *ImpTypeInfo = importChecked(
10351  Err, FromValue.getLValueBase().get<TypeInfoLValue>().getType());
10352  QualType ImpType =
10353  importChecked(Err, FromValue.getLValueBase().getTypeInfoType());
10354  if (Err)
10355  return std::move(Err);
10356  Base = APValue::LValueBase::getTypeInfo(TypeInfoLValue(ImpTypeInfo),
10357  ImpType);
10358  }
10359  }
10360  CharUnits Offset = FromValue.getLValueOffset();
10361  unsigned PathLength = FromValue.getLValuePath().size();
10362  Result.MakeLValue();
10363  if (FromValue.hasLValuePath()) {
10364  MutableArrayRef<APValue::LValuePathEntry> ToPath = Result.setLValueUninit(
10365  Base, Offset, PathLength, FromValue.isLValueOnePastTheEnd(),
10366  FromValue.isNullPointer());
10367  llvm::ArrayRef<APValue::LValuePathEntry> FromPath =
10368  FromValue.getLValuePath();
10369  for (unsigned LoopIdx = 0; LoopIdx < PathLength; LoopIdx++) {
10370  if (FromElemTy->isRecordType()) {
10371  const Decl *FromDecl =
10372  FromPath[LoopIdx].getAsBaseOrMember().getPointer();
10373  const Decl *ImpDecl = importChecked(Err, FromDecl);
10374  if (Err)
10375  return std::move(Err);
10376  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(FromDecl))
10377  FromElemTy = Importer.FromContext.getRecordType(RD);
10378  else
10379  FromElemTy = cast<ValueDecl>(FromDecl)->getType();
10380  ToPath[LoopIdx] = APValue::LValuePathEntry(APValue::BaseOrMemberType(
10381  ImpDecl, FromPath[LoopIdx].getAsBaseOrMember().getInt()));
10382  } else {
10383  FromElemTy =
10384  Importer.FromContext.getAsArrayType(FromElemTy)->getElementType();
10385  ToPath[LoopIdx] = APValue::LValuePathEntry::ArrayIndex(
10386  FromPath[LoopIdx].getAsArrayIndex());
10387  }
10388  }
10389  } else
10390  Result.setLValue(Base, Offset, APValue::NoLValuePath{},
10391  FromValue.isNullPointer());
10392  }
10393  if (Err)
10394  return std::move(Err);
10395  return Result;
10396 }

10398 Expected<DeclarationName> ASTImporter::HandleNameConflict(DeclarationName Name,
10399  DeclContext *DC,
10400  unsigned IDNS,
10401  NamedDecl **Decls,
10402  unsigned NumDecls) {
10403  if (ODRHandling == ODRHandlingType::Conservative)
10404  // Report error at any name conflict.
10405  return make_error<ASTImportError>(ASTImportError::NameConflict);
10406  else
10407  // Allow to create the new Decl with the same name.
10408  return Name;
10409 }

10427 void ASTImporter::CompleteDecl (Decl *D) {
10428  if (auto *ID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D)) {
10429  if (!ID->getDefinition())
10430  ID->startDefinition();
10431  }
10432  else if (auto *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D)) {
10433  if (!PD->getDefinition())
10434  PD->startDefinition();
10435  }
10436  else if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D)) {
10437  if (!TD->getDefinition() && !TD->isBeingDefined()) {
10438  TD->startDefinition();
10439  TD->setCompleteDefinition(true);
10440  }
10441  }
10442  else {
10443  assert(0 && "CompleteDecl called on a Decl that can't be completed");
10444  }
10445 }

10447 Decl *ASTImporter::MapImported(Decl *From, Decl *To) {
10448  llvm::DenseMap<Decl *, Decl *>::iterator Pos = ImportedDecls.find(From);
10449  assert((Pos == ImportedDecls.end() || Pos->second == To) &&
10450  "Try to import an already imported Decl");
10451  if (Pos != ImportedDecls.end())
10452  return Pos->second;
10453  ImportedDecls[From] = To;
10454  // This mapping should be maintained only in this function. Therefore do not
10455  // check for additional consistency.
10456  ImportedFromDecls[To] = From;
10457  // In the case of TypedefNameDecl we create the Decl first and only then we
10458  // import and set its DeclContext. So, the DC is still not set when we reach
10459  // here from GetImportedOrCreateDecl.
10460  if (To->getDeclContext())
10461  AddToLookupTable(To);
10462  return To;
10463 }

10465 std::optional<ASTImportError>
10466 ASTImporter::getImportDeclErrorIfAny(Decl *FromD) const {

10468  if (Pos != ImportDeclErrors.end())
10469  return Pos->second;
10470  else
10471  return std::nullopt;
10472 }

10474 void ASTImporter::setImportDeclError(Decl *From, ASTImportError Error) {
10475  auto InsertRes = ImportDeclErrors.insert({From, Error});
10476  (void)InsertRes;
10477  // Either we set the error for the first time, or we already had set one and
10478  // now we want to set the same error.
10479  assert(InsertRes.second || InsertRes.first->second.Error == Error.Error);
10480 }

10482 bool ASTImporter::IsStructurallyEquivalent(QualType From, QualType To,
10483  bool Complain) {
10484  llvm::DenseMap<const Type *, const Type *>::iterator Pos =
10485  ImportedTypes.find(From.getTypePtr());
10486  if (Pos != ImportedTypes.end()) {
10487  if (ExpectedType ToFromOrErr = Import(From)) {
10488  if (ToContext.hasSameType(*ToFromOrErr, To))
10489  return true;
10490  } else {
10491  llvm::consumeError(ToFromOrErr.takeError());
10492  }
10493  }
10494 
10495  StructuralEquivalenceContext Ctx(FromContext, ToContext, NonEquivalentDecls,
10496  getStructuralEquivalenceKind(*this), false,
10497  Complain);
10498  return Ctx.IsEquivalent(From, To);
10499 }
